Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SPVARSQ001 - DRS causing communication problems on VM hosts
ProblemDescription: We have had 3 known incidents in the last week of SQL Availability Groups having communication issues (2 have led to the AG failing over) and for 1 incident we suspect it caused a VM to blue screen. On each occasion the times have coincided with SPVARSQ001 being migrated to the host where 1 of the AG nodes resides.  There were performance issues with SPVARSQ001 prior to Christmas, which resulted in it being assigned additional CPU and RAM resource.
Workaround: DRS for spvarsq001 set to "partially automated" stopping it from vMotioning.
RootCause: There have been performance issues with the SQL Database and this is due to disk allocation sizes on all drives are 4K, when they should be 64K for SQL drives.  This change is to move the DB onto better performing drives.
Resolution: The drives have been moved to 64bit disk allocation and this is now working correctly the work was completed under RFC18637

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Performance problem in logout page
ProblemDescription: There were some instances observerd in LIVE environment which shows that metrica portal(https://www.metritests.com/metrica/) logout page is taking too long to load. we have also replicated the issue in our local environment. Attached is the video file of the replication.    We have investigated the issue and found that there is a timer code written in the logout.aspx page which is causing the problem. Below mentioned is the code area which is causing the problem. In the code the only suspicious item that can trigger this delay seems to be possible from this timer. A situation where the timer might take more than 1 second to post the initial request and thus queues up multiple requests which leads to such delay.    File name: logout.aspx.cs  File path: Metrica    protected void Timer1_OnTick(object sender, EventArgs e)          {              FormsAuthentication.SignOut();              Institution institution = InstitutionHelper.GetCurrentInstitution(true);              Session.Abandon();              if ((institution != ) && (institution.IsLoaded))              {                  Response.Redirect(MetricaSoftware.Web.ApplicationManager.ApplicationPath + "/" + institution.InstitutionId + ".aspx");              }              else              {                  Response.Redirect(MetricaSoftware.Web.ApplicationManager.ApplicationPath + "/default.aspx");              }          }      File Name: logout.aspx  File path: Metrica    <asp:Timer ID="Timer1" runat="server" Interval="1000" ontick="Timer1_OnTick"></asp:Timer>
RootCause: Unidentified
Resolution: No further action, last incident 436922 raised on 09/01/2017.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: PRDB Extract Job Failure due to exceeded candidate name accepted by PRDB from SAP
ProblemDescription: Currently SAP, CECP allows 80 chars (FNAME+LNAME), however PRDB can only accept 60 (FNAME+LNAME). Due to 2 candidates name being 68 and 64 chars long, the extract job was unable to push all candidate result to ESOLCR
Workaround: To remove these candidates in PRDB and then allow the job to run for others or reduce the full name with in the limit of 60 chars.  Once the PRDB job starts running the missing candidates and results will appear in ESOLCR.
RootCause: There is no consistency in the upper limit of characters between ECC and PRDB. This is causing jobs to fail due to exceeded length in candidate name.
Resolution: An additional validation is to be included to restrict the length from 80 to 60 in CECP. This is to be carried out in CR9000476

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ICE Grading - CAP Data removed from Previous series in EPSCandidate grades
ProblemDescription: During ICE grading of November 2016, it was noticed that CAP records was removed of candidates from previous series. For candidate provided in Incident#438124 - November 2016/TH177 cand #0007), it was found that CAP record was removed due to candidate -UCI changed during linking with November 16 candidate after June 2016 results.    There are the rest of similar candidates shared in I#438124 and their CAP records were deleted due to different reason.  No. Centre Candidate Unique identifier Candidate number/J16 ICE Outcome  1 EA016 UCLES-92838178                      45   2 IN747 UCLES-91199266                      1   3 IN747 UCLES-91199268                      2   4 NG167 UCLES-92071906                      38   5 NG272 UCLES-89766408                        8   6 TH177 UCLES-89993782                      11     In a mail attached in I#438124, it seems due to removal of overarched ICE syllabus, CAP record can be removed. In an investigation it seems true.In EPS database table, CAP records are maintained for each candidate in a single table but is kept separated for different session via a field-value of this table. Though  in the screen of ICE overarching, if we expand each candidate, overarched syllabuses are shown at candidate level but with different overarched-count for different session. As a reference of this, scenarios along with related screens in I#438124 activity-history on 07 February 2017 17:32  can be referred.The reason of the problem is described in I#438124 activity-history on  23 January 2017 17:37.    Though there is a PR - 1717 but this is a bit different scenario because CAP record is removed after grading for previous series.  As discussed with customer, this problem is raised to have a root cause and a resolution for this type of scenario.
Workaround: CAP records is populated for those candidates for previous session.    As an alternative workaround, the process of removing overarched by choosing current series syllabus can restrict CAP removal of previous series.Detail process is described in I#438124 activity-history dated on 07 February 2017 11:33.
RootCause: The incident was caused by removal of the over-arching ICE syllabus for a series rather than for a single syllabus, so removing the CAP records for these candidates.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Module Grades being output incorrectly on SORs for CPE
ProblemDescription:
Some results appearing on SORs are different from candidates' actual results
20/07/17 - Additionally, linking ITSM incident #487352.

#WaterLine YES
#Super Results
#Workaround YES

RootCause: Initially, the module names were sorted with start date but not along with the module grades and that caused the mismatch. The function “SortbyKey” is replaced with function “FormatbyExample” after which modules are getting mapped correctly. This also ensures that if there are more modules or for different POS structure, it won’t create any issues further in future.

Fix implemented in the JAN MTR - RFC 19097

Subject: IWAS - Audit trail report is not getting restricted by Centres.
ProblemDescription: When the user type is “PARTNER”, the audit trail report is getting restricted by centres filtered by the corresponding partner type (i.e. IDP, BC, CEII etc.) but in case of user type ‘PARTNER_READ’ and ‘PARTNER_WRITE’ the report contains data for all centres irrespective of partner type when “All Centres” is selected in centre dropdown list. Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CIE Direct Admin- EAR's do not always complete if all documents uploaded using Bulk Upload facility
ProblemDescription: CIE Direct Admin- EAR's do not always complete if all documents uploaded using Bulk Upload facility.  If all documents for an EAR are in the same zip file and the acknowledgement letter is not placed before all other documents for a single EAR then that EAR will not complete in CIE Direct following the upload.
Workaround: Acknowledgement letters can be uploaded separately first. (this is in fact the supposed business process).  If an acknowledgement letter has already been uploaded then trhe bulk upload facility can be used for the remaining documents with issue.  If any enquries do not get completed a database script can be run by the support team to "complete" them.
RootCause: The issue arises if all documents for an EAR are uploaded in the same zip file.  The end user does not control the order in which the letters appear in the file nor can they accruately determine this order.  If the Acknowledgement letter for an EAR does not come first in the file then the EAR will not complete.
Resolution: System worked as designed, Workaround is the resolution. Users must use business process to avoid these incidents occurring.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cambridge Technicals the marks are not feeding through to CAAP, this is leaving the records in suspe
ProblemDescription: Cambridge Technicals the marks are not feeding through to CAAP, this is leaving the records in suspense with no marks.  As per current code logic if entry date is over for Cambridge Technicals scheme. And we make an entry for a candidate after the entry closing date. Then no attendance list will be generated for this newly entered candidate.    But if we will add the candidate in the attendance list then marks cannot be entered for this candidate if the attendance list is already in submitted state (Submitted to the examiner).  Hence for this candidate marks will not feed through to CAMS CAAP.  If we will add the candidate before submitting to the examiner then we can enter marks for this candidate and the data will go through to CAMS CAAP.    Please find the root cause document attached.
Workaround: From CAMS CAAP application CAMS Admin users are entering the marks manually for these newly added candidates.
RootCause:
Root Cause:    1st – Business has requested us to open the session for making an entry for a new candidate by extending the entry closing date from back-end.   2nd – As per business logic this late entry candidate will be missed in the attendance list which has been generated before the entry has been created.   3rd – Business has requested us to add the new candidate in the attendance list from back-end.  But if we will add the candidate in the attendance list then marks cannot be entered for this candidate if the attendance list is already in submitted state (Submitted to the examiner).   Hence for this candidate marks will not feed through to CAMS CAAP.  If we will add the candidate before submitting to the examiner then we can enter marks for this candidate and the data will go through to CAMS CAAP.

Session closed too soon, so late entries came in as pirates meaning pirate entry processing was done meaning data not added to the marksheet.
Resolution: Process change - OCR to send message asking for attendance list to only be submitted when all entries are made. There will be some genuine pirates that come in, so will need to manage via workaround. Session also left open for longer so late entries are treated as late entries, rather than pirates.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Default cost centre derived in BW independently from data maintained in ECC
ProblemDescription: Default cost centre derived in BW independently from data maintained in ECC.  For some financial postings, a cost centre is derived in ECC. The derivation is based on a value table that is maintained manually.  In BW, the same process is mirrored: a value table is manually maintained and used to derive the cost centre.  The problem is that it is possible to have different values in the ECC table and in the BW tables which creates discrepancy between the two systems.  It would be better to have a custom extractor to upload the table from ECC into BW so that there are always aligned. There is still a risk of a discrepancy but this is minimal (if the table is changed in the middle of the day in ECC)
Workaround: Maintained the data manually in BW when informed that there had been a change in ECC.
RootCause: Data is maintained separately in SAP ECC and BW. It needs to be extracted into BW to avoid the issue from happening
Resolution:
Resolved via CR 9000798

The solution will require a change in design and this will be carried out under Change Request 9000798.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Issue while converting entry from reserve to named
ProblemDescription:
Few issue observed while converting reserved entry to convert entry    
1. KAD (Key Assessment Date) was missing in HRP9003  
2. HRP1728 – SubType 9001, HS_STATE update   
3. Name is not converting properly

#WaterLine YES
#Super Key Business Process Impact
#Workaround YES
Workaround: update the table for HRP1728 by running the script.
RootCause:
If a Named entry is created by the user, Infotype 1728 would be updated with the sub types CS01 and CS03.
When any Reserve candidates in CECP are amended as a Named entry, then the field “HS_STATE” in Infotype 1728 would be changed from A (active) to I (Inactive) of sub type 9001.
SoR Printing Program (ZEXPR_CERTIFICATE_PRINT) considers the field “HS_STATE” of Infotype 1728 to print SoR ,provided “HS_STATE” is in “I” -Inactive status of sub type 9001 and the statuses of other two subtypes CS01 & CS03 should be active (Job for reference: Z_DA_E_LIVE_CERTIFICATE_PRINT).
Resolution:
Fix deployed in the DEC MTR , RFC 18703
As part of PR#2910 solution, Errors for “Start date is after end date” and “Billing document is already cancelled” have been addressed and deployed into production environment
Technical analysis :For “Start date is after end date
BPM RFC Z_BAPI_CHANGE_REG_BOOKING triggers the above error. Standard function module HRIQ_HS_STATUS_SAVE which is called within BPM RFC ends with start date is after end date error.
The standard function module is checking for validity date which considers the system date as start date and academic calendar date as end date. Calendar date is calculated by standard function module HRIQ_ACAD_SESSION_DATES_GET. Observed that calendar end date is picked as last date of the week (week which holds the assessment date).
If any student detail changes take place after the above maintained Academic Calendar, system will get the results in above said error. 
Technical analysis :
Changes done in RFC Z_EXP_RFC_UPD_ENTRYORDER in routine process_entry_data and added a condition to check whether the billing document has already been considered for cancellation by previous entry line item, if so skips cancellation for current line item execution.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: The Batch_ID field doesn’t work in the Candidate Override UI in HANA
ProblemDescription: The Batch_ID field doesn’t work in the Candidate Override UI in HANA.    Technically, HANA Procedure GET_POST_CALC_ERROR_SUMMARY_DATA needs to be modified to use parameter IT_BATCH_ID in the query for TT_POST_CALC_ERROR_SUMMARY.
RootCause:
Batch_ID field in Candidate Override in the selection screen is not working  and as a result giving output 
even with invalid Batch_ID.
•In Candidate Override tab of Manage marks tab in RD portal Batch_ID is not working .• The selection screen gives search result even with invalid Batch_ID which means the input which user is giving in selection screen is coming to HANA via ABAP method but is not being used in fetching the data according to the input provided.• In the ABAP method "RESDET"."ucles.rd.procs.calc::GET_POST_CALC_ERROR_SUMMARY_DATA" 
HANA procedure has been called and it is passing the inputs got from selection screen to HANA procedure.

In the HANA procedure there is a select statement which fetches data for the UI selection screen, but in that statement Join with table is missing from where we have to fetch Batch_ID
Resolution:
1.CANDIDATE_ENTRY table should be joined with STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH  table
(Join condition: CANDIDATE_ENTRY.CANDIDATE_ENTRY_UID =STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH.RECONCILED_CANDIDATE_ENTRY_UID).

2.In next step the join will be STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH table to    STAGING_BATCH_ADDITIONAL_DETAIL table
(Join condition: STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH. STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH_GUID = STAGING_BATCH_ADDITIONAL_DETAIL. STAGING_CAND_ENTRY_MEASURE_BATCH_GUID)

to fetch Attribute value where Attribute type = 'BATCH_ID'

3. Output table type should be changed according to new output columns present after join.

4. The join condition should be like if the input Batch_ID matches with one present in our HANA table then only it should give search result otherwise it should not fetch any data. This change will allow procedure to fetch data according to the Batch_ID provided by the user. Although it is not a mandatory criteria for search but if it is given by user as input it should fetch data accordingly.

RFC# 31348

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Results Enquiries appear as duplicates on SAP
ProblemDescription: As you see below, the highlighted Results Enquiries (ZI) appear as duplicate enquiries on SAP. They are all for component level. Please, investigate:
RootCause:
Duplicate Result Enquiry- Clinical check (ZI) cases are getting created from portal for a single candidate. 
Expectation is that a single ZI case should get created per candidate and for relevant composite module. The duplication is occurring rarely and is not replicable.
Resolution:
To prevent the creation of duplicate Result Enquiry cases for the same candidate, a check has to be invoked at RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION  level, to identify whether there is already ZI case created for the same candidate. If one such ZI case is already being created before, for the same candidate, then creation of one more ZI case for the same candidate shall not be allowed.

System will try to retrieve already created ZI case for the current candidate BP, from Quality notification header table and Quality Notification Items table. If valid ZI case exists for the current candidate BP then a flag shall be set. Before calling the RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION, the value of the flag needs to be checked, If it set as ‘X’, then system will bypass the call to the RFC. Thus creation of duplicate Result Enquiry cases can be prevented.

The changes needs to be done at line number: 205 within RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION

Moreover, system will prompt the user with a pop up ‘Results Enquiry - Clerical Check (Stage 1) case is already being created for the candidate’, if the user is trying to create duplicate case ‘ZI’ for the same candidate BP from different sessions or multiple users are working on the same candidate.

Deployed via Feb Mini MTR,  RFC 33537

ProblemDescription: Candidate Unit Achievement Reports area not generating for some candidates (approximately 50% of those checked). Cause was data inconsistencies, so resolution was to :- Modify Candidate Unit Achievement report so can run before results release, so checks can take place and any data inconsistencies investigated/resolved before results release. Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Fixing Transport Layer (TLS) Encryption Weaknesses on the F5 Load Balancers
ProblemDescription: For SSL/TLS Offloading, the F5 Load Balancers can be forced to used ecnryption mechansims that are considered insecure. They are:    1. Support for either DES or 3DES;  2. Support for CBC mode cipher suites in combination with earlier TLS versions - dubbed the 'BEAST' vulnerability.    Attached are screenshots and information about what has been identified and what needs to be done.    This will affect all sites that are SSL/TLS offloaded by the F5 Load Balancer
Workaround: None
RootCause: This is due to the default ssl profile configuration being in use for SSL offload
Resolution:
1. Creation of new SSL profiles on external load balancer.
2. Updated Load Balancer standards.
3. Highlighted changes to Network engineers.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-1389 - CB SELT IELTS candidate missing name in C+
ProblemDescription: Candidate details message  from IWAS contains the candidate details along with a dummy component enrolment. BizTalk uses candidate details message to create the candidate details file  for Marks Manager(MM).  Candidate enrolment message from IWAS contains the candidate details along with the component enrolments. BizTalk uses the candidate enrolment message to create the Candidate priming message for C+ for each of the component enrolments and also creates candidate enrolment files for MM.    Now the question that arises is why BizTalk uses candidate enrolment message to prime C+. The reason is Connect Plus treats  candidate entry for each component as a unique entry unlike Mark Manager. As such candidate details along with enrolment need to be sent for priming to C+ for each enrolment of the candidate. This information is only available in candidate enrolment message from IWAS. Candidate details message cannot be used to prime C+.    Currently IWAS does not generate enrolment message for candidate details change and as a result C+ is not updated.
Workaround: Re-pushing the canidates with the enrolment details will allow BizTalk to push the updated candidate details. However as buisness confirmed no worarond has been implemented for Incident# 451270.
RootCause: This was not accounted for when specifying the requirements for the interfaces to C+. it has been confirmed C+ has the capability to accept changes.
Resolution: Solution to be addressed under IELTS-1389.

Subject: EDI results file from CAMS CAAP containing incorrect information.
ProblemDescription: The generation of the Cambridge Technicals EDI Results File for the January 2017 session has their results for the Engineering qualification were showing incorrect on the EDI extract produced. AssessmentTypes  The information from the above mentioned tables is extracted and feed into a temporary table (tempEDIResult) using a query (QueryCreateTempEDIResult). The file in which the query is invoked is ‘CEDIFile.pas’. See the attached query.

Resolution: Code Change. RFC 17475

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Two examiners are marking the same candidate response and giving two different marks.
ProblemDescription: This is a problem with the marking sessions and examiner marking part. A candidate response should be presented to only one examiner only and should be marked only once. But in this case two different examiners are seeing the same response and marking them resulting in multiple marks for the same response.    We can able to replicate the issue in our local as well as SUP environments. As stated earlier also, it was intermittent and the frequency of replication was very low after several tries. Most of the replication falls under one category mentioned below  "When two different examiners at the same time selects the same marking session to retrieve items to mark"    Please find one such incident where we have replicated the problem. See attachment 'Incident# 448762.png'.  After investigation, we can find that both the examiners were trying to fetch next item for marking and have initiated the request(by clicking on the same marking session link) at the same point of time. As a result two calls were generated and they were processed at similar instances which resulted in inserting two identical records in the back-end database.    As per our investigation, thread locking mechanism(for preventing parallel processing of requests) implemented in the code is not functioning properly.
RootCause: Code changes identified and provided to Metrica team further action under MET-6963
Resolution: Code fix applied as part of v17.4 on 05/09/2017, RFC 17799.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: When ODS Master fails or is stopped data is missing.
ProblemDescription: When ODS Master fails or is stopped data is missing.  On the next successful ODS Master run the data is not recreated until a backfill is run.
Workaround: Backfill process agreed that ARD advise. The Service Desk have confirmed their procedure has been amended to raise an incident for this on overrun or failure of ODS Master Load. See email activity.  Keep PR open until resolution has been seen to work.
RootCause:
The table [StaticData].[Candidates]  and [StaticData].[CandidateInfo] share the same Extraction packages Extract_MEPS_Candidates and Extract_OEPS_Candidates. The load for [StaticData].[Candidates]  happens prior to load for  [StaticData].[CandidateInfo].
So when the [StaticData].[Candidates]   is loaded the Status of both the packages are set as ‘’L’’ in the [ctrl].[ExtractState]. If the ODS Master job is stopped before the load for [StaticData].[CandidateInfo] completed then in the next run the extracted packages will not re-extract from the failed point since the state for the packages are already set as ‘’L’’
Resolution:
We need to change the package Load_StaticData_Candidates so that the State for the package in [ctrl].[ExtractState] table is not set to “L”. We also have to make sure that the for package [StaticData].[CandidateInfo] the State for the package in [ctrl].[ExtractState] table is set to “L”
Fix released into PRD under, RFC20455.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SXI_Monitor Error in ERP
ProblemDescription: Please find below the Error. Attached payload details for reference.               Regards,  Ramya.    Category: SAP  Subcategory: ERP - ASPs
Workaround:
• At the code level, once the equipment scoris flag status gets updated with C- Completed then they are converting the IDoc(Batch ID coming from Scoris) status to 39 from 03 by calling standard program: RC1_IDOC_SET_STATUS.
• As we are already getting the idoc numbers  now we can easily check the status of those idocs before converting the status to 39 or 40.
• If the UCLES_CONSIG_NUM(equipment numbers) of those idocs are having scoris flag status set as ‘C’, in the system then only we will check the current idoc status for those equipment's.
•If status is 12 or 03 then we will convert the idoc status to from 03 or 12 to 39, else 40.
RootCause:
1. Upon checking the proxy class found below observation in Candidate Script packet response:
• The equipment’s SCORIS flag status is getting updated,
• If the SCORIS flag status is ‘C- Completed’, IDoc (BATCH ID) status changes from 03 to 39,
•      If the SCORIS flag status is ‘F-Failed/I-Ignored , IDoc (BATCH ID) status changes from 03 to 40.
2. In some of the cases the SCORIS flag status for the equipment is getting updated with ‘C’, but the IDOC status for that equipment is getting changed from 03 to 12 instead of 39.
3.There is delay in synchronous proxy call response to reach from PI to ECC.
4.However this issue is happening very rarely. Lastly it occurred on ‘13.12.2017’.
Resolution:
• At the code level, once the equipment scoris flag status gets updated with C- Completed then they are converting the IDoc(Batch ID coming from Scoris) status to 39 from 03 by calling standard program: RC1_IDOC_SET_STATUS.

• As we are already getting the idoc numbers  now we can easily check the status of those idocs before converting the status to 39 or 40.
• If the UCLES_CONSIG_NUM(equipment numbers) of those idocs are having scoris flag status set as ‘C’, in the system then only we will check the current idoc status for those equipments.
• If status is 12 or 03 then we will convert the idoc status to from 03 or 12 to 39, else 40.

RootCause:
1) Ensure that each VM in the cluster is built on different ESX Host. Ensure that these been set to "Soft Affinity".
2) Ensure that both the Heartbeat addresses are configured on a separate network interfaces to that associated with the hostname.
3) Create 2 "ping" resources on the cluster
4) Turn off IPv6 on all but the loopback interface on each node
5) Set the following parameters;
• stonith-timeout=120s
• op monitor interval=120s
• op defaults timeout=120s
• resource-stickiness=1000
6) Create 2 fencing resources instead of the singular resource.
7) Ensure that the latest versions of cman, pcs, pacemaker and resource_agents_sap are running
Resolution:
Amend various cluster parameter settings.
Delivered as part of the SAP Hana project, RFC15839

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Records missing from ISPWarehouse table vQPSessAC
ProblemDescription: Records missing from ISPWarehouse table vQPSessAC    CIE have discovered that records are missing from ISPWarehouse table vQPSessAC (ODS table QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents). It appears that the records have been removed from ISP since the ODS deployment on 7th March, although this has not been 100% confirmed. However, CIE are confident that the records were available on 22nd February, and were missing by 14th March. We suspect that changes to the way IsDeletedFromSource flags are applied have gone wrong in this table.    176 components that were marked on-screen in the November 2016 session cannot be found in vQPSessAC, and 8 components from the live March 2017 session. A list is attached.    As an example, we have undertaken some investigation into component 9389/11 in November 2016:  Assessmentcode=9389  ComponentID=11  SessionID=10530  SessionAssessmentComponentID=1478628    This SessionAssessmentComponentID does not exist in table vQPSessAC. However, it does exist in table QuestionPaperItemGroups and is linked with QuestionPaperID=6019912.    QuestionPaperID=6019912 exists in vQPSessAC, associated with SessionAssessmentComponentID=1422966. But this SessionAssessmentComponentID does not exist in table SessionAssessmentComponents. It is presumably an old version of the assessment and is deleted from source (SessionAssessmentComponents.IsDeletedFromSource=1).    So it looks like there is a problem with records being marked as deleted in vQPSessAC – an old record persists in the table and the live record is no longer available. We know that the record linking the live SessionAssessmentComponentID to the live QuestionPaperID existed until a few weeks ago, as reporting was working correctly. Exactly the same SAS queries now return no records for component 9389/11.
RootCause:
It is long standing issue in ODS which should be fixed in subsequent release. Nick asked to get a PR for the issue and after which the incident was closed. This needs to be analysed and set for subsequest release. Priority to be discussed with business users.

Problem Analysis and Resolution #
Assumption: All of my investigation is conducted from the ODS side. So, whatever view is used in the DB ISPwarehouse, for that, I am using the table name from ODS_WH DB, as ODS_WH is the warehouse where all data are loaded finally. In the problem Description it have been said that records are missing from ISPWarehouse table vQPSessAC table, which is actually a view from ODS perspective. This is the view upon table [Session].[QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents] which is in DB ODS_WH.
Throughout this document I have used the table [Session].[QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents] where the records are missing.
Analysis: The source from where the data is loaded in the table [Session].[QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents] is another transformation table “[etl].[Session_QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents]” which is in staging database. I have checked in this table whether any entries for the SessionAssessmentComponentID 1478628 is available or not. But found it is not available.
 
So, I suspect that something is wrong in loading the etl table. So, I investigated to know how the table [etl].[Session_QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents] is populated. I found that it is populated by CIE data from staging table and being looked up with the table “[etl].[Session_QuestionPaperSessionAssessmentComponents].
Below is the screenshot for the output of Lookup table and the staging table :
 
The above action is done through SSIS package. We can see for both of the output, AssessmentCode, SessionID, ComponentID, BusinessstreamID, ComponentVersionNumber are all same. The only difference is in the value for AssessmentVersionNumber, which is 3 for the SessionAssessmentComponent = 1478626, which matches with the actual data coming from the staging table. See value for ASV_VER_NO. But in the lookup this AssessmentVersionNumber field has not been used to join both tables. That’s why the SSIS is returning the first row with the SessionAssessmentComponentID 1422966, which is technically wrong because as stated it is presumably an old version of the assessment and is deleted from source.
Resolution:
Release or Break fix. Acceptable to Nick Raikes on email 13 Dec 17

Fix released into PRD - RFC20455

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IDAM Stability
ProblemDescription: IDAM Stability    IDAM had an outage at 9:05am 05/05/2017
Workaround: Web services (OIM) are manually started again.
RootCause: The cause was/is that the DB connection pool setting in PRD are set very low (the default setting). This caused the connection to be overloaded and shutdown. See the error below:    <05-May-2017 08:50:43 o'clock BST> <Error> <XELLERATE.DATABASE> <BEA-000000> <Class/Method: DirectDB/getConnection encounter some problems: Error while retrieving database connection.Please check for the follwoing  Database server is running.  Datasource configuration settings are correct.  java.sql.SQLException: DirectConnection The connection is not valid or it is closed          at com.thortech.xl.util.DirectDB.getConnection(DirectDB.java:179)          at com.thortech.xl.dataobj.util.ADPClassWatchDog.getMaxUpdateTimestamp(ADPClassWatchDog.java:50)          at com.thortech.xl.dataobj.util.ADPClassWatchDog.run(ADPClassWatchDog.java:145)  >  java.sql.SQLRecoverableException: Connection has been administratively disabled.
Resolution: Change configuration values for the IDAM DB connection pool settings from  Current settings for OIMOperationsDB:    • Minimum Connections : 32  • Maximum Connections : 50  • Initial Connections : 32    Should be set atleast to:    • Minimum Connections : 150  • Maximum Connections :200  • Initial Connections :150    These new values will be enabled Wednesday 10/05 afternoon

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS IWAS - Technical Exception returned when submitting scores with more than one absentee - IELTS
ProblemDescription: IELTS IWAS - Technical Exception returned when submitting scores with more than one absentee.  This issue appears to be specific to cases where a centre is trying to submit more than one candidate as AB. If you submit a score set which contains a single, or no AB, candidates then there is no issue.  If there is more than AB candidate in the score set being submitted then a Technical Exception error is thrown.
Workaround: set LS_RESULT.R_CANDIDATE_2_ID to -1 for the absent candidates in the LS_RESULT table
RootCause: In the Life Skills results entry screen, when the 2nd candidate is changed to AB, a background process gets all candidates who have a 2nd candidate set as AB, this is then set to null in the database. This causes a Null Pointer Exception when the results are submitted in the results entry
Resolution:
The background process is not executed whenever the 2nd candidate is changed to AB or RF

Under Rfc 17386

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Fail to connect to IWAS production database
ProblemDescription: Fail to connect to IWAS production database. From 10:38am 9th May, database connection to the IWAS production database (ieltprd1 on spjntor002) has not been possible remotely or locally. CPU is 100%. Listener is fine as we can tnsping to the listener.
Workaround: Database and server restarted.   Processes were checked and the HWM stood at 700 (max allowable 1200), however database processes was increased to 1800 as one of the reasons of hitting this TNS error can be due to the process number is reaching the limit.
RootCause: Ultimately the root cause was the code change that was applied in Late April / early May (under PR 3874). Even though this should not cause the database to hang, there has been no reoccurrence since the code was "fixed".
Resolution: Code was changed and steps have been identified to help diagnose the hung database if it were to reoccur.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ‘Provisional vs Actual Entries’ report is facing performance issue.
ProblemDescription: IWAS users are currently not able to generate ‘Provisional vs Actual Entries’ report from application. While investigating and replicating this, it is found that the above report conditionally includes ‘allocation group’ by checking if the given span of test dates are falling after ‘01-MAY-17’. If any such test date is found, it executes a specific query which sometimes is not giving the final output. If the criteria with which the user is requesting this report takes the entire test dates before ‘01-MAY-17’, another query is getting executed which sometimes is taking a long response time to generate the report from application end.
Workaround: If required, a similar extract could be generated which will fetch less number of data under more restricted criteria.
RootCause: : report allowed for queries to be run with huge results to the point of impacting DB availability
Resolution:
Optimised queries to reduce cost and improve performance.
RFC18686

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Create Multiple MessageBox in Production
ProblemDescription: Once the load goes up in BizTalk environment, bottleneck starts to appear in SQL server. Msgbox connectivity issues appears, deadlock on messagebox db starts to appear which impacts the processing of messages especially in a high load scenario.
Workaround: The single most significant optimization step when dealing with scaling the BizTalk Message Box is adding new message boxes even when they are created in the same SQL Instance, with the added benefit of being the most simple to implement. We will need to
RootCause: A single MessageBox configuration does not provide the capacity and performance for an ever increasing Biztalk platform.This requires multiple message box configuration to provide more capacity and resilience to the Platform.
Resolution:
Add two message box to BizTalk with 1 Master and 2 slave configuration.

RFC no. is 18138

ProblemDescription: Several Examiners reported that the BULATS Candidate Speaking responses were not accessible when they were about to mark the speaking tokens. The Play button on the application was greyed out and they were not able to mark the candidate speaking tokens. Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BPC reports not aligned in landscape
ProblemDescription: A decision was taken by Finance and CoE to stop direct changes being made in the BPC production system.  A CR was approved to make changes to ~ 11 BPC reports.  The CR was prioritised along with others however the requested date was found to be incorrect and Finance created an incident ticket.  Approval was given to make the changes directly in the production system on the understanding that the changes would be documented and rekeyed in dev and progressed through to production retrospectively.  The incident has been closed (463375).  The original CR had two parts and both parts are in production (CR9000463).  In addition, the reports in BPC are not always reporting correctly due to the BPC 'context' issue - logged under OSS message 168048 - the SAP proposed solution to which is to upgrade the EPM patch.  The reports have been updated in the dev system but have not been transported through to production as expected.  It is not possible to test the reports in any system due to the 'context' issue.  The BPC consultant (Sumit Rajdev) proposes that the report changes should be moved through to production in line with the EPM patching activities.  Any associated documentation should also be checked for completeness.
Workaround: n/a
RootCause:
This PR was created to store the following information:

A decision was taken by Finance and CoE to stop direct changes being made in the BPC production system.
A CR was approved to make changes to ~ 11 BPC reports.  The CR was prioritised along with others however the requested (implementation) date was found to be incorrect and Finance created an incident ticket.  Approval was given to make the changes directly in the production system on the understanding that the changes would be documented and rekeyed in dev and progressed through to production retrospectively.  The incident has been closed (463375).  The original CR had two parts and both parts are in production (CR9000463).
In addition, the reports in BPC are not always reporting correctly due to the BPC 'context' issue - logged under OSS message 168048 - the SAP proposed solution to which is to upgrade the EPM patch.
The reports have been updated in the dev system but have not been transported through to production as expected.
It is not possible to test the reports in any system due to the 'context' issue.
The BPC consultant (Sumit Rajdev) proposes that the report changes should be moved through to production in line with the EPM patching activities.  Any associated documentation should also be checked for completeness.
Resolution:
all relevant BPC reports involved have been transported through from the development system to production via subsequent CRs – all systems in the BAU landscape are now in line.  (The BPC context issue referred to has also been fixed.)

This was addressed through CR621 - BPC Budget 2019 Template and Report Changes, which was deployed through RFC 19765 on 15/03/18.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865

ProblemDescription: Transactional Replication between the epsstaging and the product manager database becomes out of synch on UTLPRD03A.  This has happened twice, so far.  Inc - 394594  Inc - 471312

ProductManager

CentreAssessmentManagerCache
ProductManagerCache
ReferenceData
EPSstaging

Subject: Poor performance of Z_M3_R_CREATE CERTIFICATE XML
ProblemDescription:
On the 1st June 2017, the Z_M3_R_CREATE CERTIFICATE XML job tried t process 32,000+ candidates when creating the XML and kept  failing with memory issues. The way the program is performing needs to be analysed and improvements suggested to prevent poor performance in the future

#WaterLine YES

Subject: Provisional Marks - duplicate marks for the same item
ProblemDescription: In provisional(pending) marks data, there are several occurrences of marked scripts (PIMQuestionPaperItemGroupID) where an item has more than one distinct mark recorded against it.  The attached example (sas/sql code & spreadsheet) shows the records from the ItemMarks table in the provisional schema corresponding to three PIMQuestionPaperItemGroupIDs. The first (PIMQuestionPaperItemGroupID=3789372) is the original mark for the script (PIMMarkingModeID=1); the other two are updates (PIMMarkingModeID=9).    For both of the updates, there are duplicate records for each MarkSchemeID. Also for MarkSchemeID=279936 (highlighted in the spreadsheet), there are  two distinct marks recorded in each case, and this will cause  problems for business
RootCause: sometimes there are two records for the same candidate in a single XML which leads to multiple entry in the PIMRD tables of ODS. Since we are getting some XML where duplicate candidates are there but different groupingReferenceId or different MarkingDate we can do the joining on <ns0:whenProduced> , <ns0:markingGroupResponseDisplayId> , groupingReferenceId and MarkingDate in order to remove the duplicates.
Also we will select only the ItemMarks with the latest MarkingDate

For achieving this we have to alter the function destructureIm() and stored Procedure processProvisionalItemMarks

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Priority group used for holding page not reverting when primary server recovers
ProblemDescription: DFD.  Priority group used for holding page not reverting when primary server recovers
Workaround: Disable holding page server in the priority group for DFD.
RootCause:
Issue is due to slow ramp time pool setting being enable along side priority group activation, In most production environments, the rate at which connections are received is sufficient for the Slow Ramp Time setting to act as a timer. However, in environments with a low connection rate, a pool configured to use priority groups could experience unexpected behavior. For example, a lower priority pool member may remain in the active priority group longer than the Slow Ramp Time setting indicates,.

The Slow Ramp Time feature (enabled by default) is used to slowly increase the number of connection requests that are load balanced to a new pool member. The Slow Ramp Time setting controls the percentage of connections that are sent to a new pool member by specifying the duration, in seconds, that a pool member is in slow ramp mode. For example, if the Slow Ramp Time setting is set to 10 seconds (the default setting), when a newly enabled pool member has been available for one second, the system begins load balancing 1/10 of the connections that would have been sent to the new pool member had the Slow Ramp Time setting been disabled. Each second thereafter, the system increases the amount of traffic load balanced to the new pool member. So, after the pool member has been available for nine seconds, the system is load balancing 90 percent of the normal load to that pool member. When the pool member has been available for longer than the Slow Ramp Time value, the pool member receives its full proportion of the incoming traffic.

When TMM is updating the slow ramp status for a pool member, if the slow ramp time has elapsed, TMM clears the slow ramp flag. Depending on the rate at which connections are received, a new pool member's slow ramp flag may remain set longer than the duration of the Slow Ramp Time setting specifies because TMM checks the slow ramp flag status only while processing connection requests.
Resolution: Disable Slow Ramp Time on DFD under RFC 17512.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: DC10 Scanning database. Report performance issue.
ProblemDescription: DC10 Scanning database. Report performance issue.  When the Oracle database determines that the DM_SYSOBJECT_R and DM_SYSOBJECT_S tables have stale stats, it reanalyzes them. From time to time, this cause the report below to run slowly. By reverting the stats back to the previous ones, the report once again is performant. As a workaround, we have set the stats not to publish for these two tables.    This is the query :    select distinct 1 "not_folder", upper(dm_sysobject.object_name) "attr1", dm_sysobject.object_name, dm_sysobject.title, dm_sysobject.r_object_type "r_object_type", dm_repeating.keywords, dm_sysobject.a_content_type, dm_sysobject.r_content_size, dm_sysobject.r_modify_date, dm_sysobject.owner_name, dm_sysobject.r_lock_owner, dm_sysobject.r_object_id from dm_sysobject_sp  dm_sysobject, dm_sysobject_r dm_sysobject_r2, dm_folder_rp dm_folder_r1, dm_sysobject_rp dm_repeating where (dm_sysobject.r_object_type not like '%dm_smart_list%' and dm_sysobject.r_object_id not like '0b%' and dm_sysobject.r_object_id not like '0c%' and  ( ((dm_sysobject.object_name='13328950')) )  and dm_sysobject.r_object_id = dm_sysobject_r2.r_object_id and dm_sysobject_r2.i_folder_id = dm_folder_r1.r_object_id and dm_folder_r1.i_ancestor_id = '0c9abbc5800089b4') and (dm_sysobject.i_has_folder = 1 and dm_sysobject.i_is_deleted = 0) and dm_repeating.r_object_id=dm_sysobject.r_object_id union all select distinct 0 "not_folder", upper(dm_folder.object_name) "attr1", dm_folder.object_name, dm_folder.title, dm_folder.r_object_type "r_object_type", dm_repeating.keywords, dm_folder.a_content_type, dm_folder.r_content_size, dm_folder.r_modify_date, dm_folder.owner_name, dm_folder.r_lock_owner, dm_folder.r_object_id from dm_folder_sp  dm_folder, dm_sysobject_r dm_sysobject_r2, dm_folder_rp dm_folder_r1, dm_folder_rp dm_repeating where (dm_folder.r_object_type not like '%dm_smart_list%' and  ( ((dm_folder.object_name='13328950')) )  and dm_folder.r_object_id = dm_sysobject_r2.r_object_id and dm_sysobject_r2.i_folder_id = dm_folder_r1.r_object_id and dm_folder_r1.i_ancestor_id = '0c9abbc5800089b4') and (dm_folder.i_has_folder = 1 and dm_folder.i_is_deleted = 0) and dm_repeating.r_object_id=dm_folder.r_object_id order by 1, 2, 12     Pr3799 was open prevoiusly
Workaround: Currently the stats for the two tables are not being published.  Also, the application team have rewritten the report in a different way to produce the same results but more consistently. This code is being moved through the environments to production.
RootCause: Intermittent slow running reports.: We identified the stale statistics issue with the two main tables used in the report.
Resolution:
Development team changed the code and the logic behind this report.
Application has been working fine and we have not observed any slowness.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica test set up requires the AutoSaave Interval to be a mandatory field
ProblemDescription: Metrica test set up requires the AutoSaave Interval to be a mandatory field.    Incident analysis:  Due to the absence of the auto save property, these responses were not get saved in the database.  There is two cases here because of which candidates encountered error.  1.       Candidates who has tried doing some activity in between the 20th minute and 40th minute:  Metrica session timeouts at 20th minute. Metrica does a database check in each call and if the session gets expired, this database check fails. Hence system directs it to the error page and candidate response does not get saved.  2.       Candidates whose tests has reached 40 minutes time mark: In this case also, there is a database check happens. And the same scenario as above, here also data did not get saved in the database and candidate is shown the error page.    These database calls are there to match some backend database data with the data stored in the session each time candidate do an activity from the front end like nextButtonClick, PreviousButtonClick, EndTest etc. I have checked the production database and found that, most of the candidates within the session have tried re opening their windows after 20 minutes and before 40 minutes of the test. This means, I guess they have tried closing their windows few seconds back. And when they tried to close the window, as 20 minutes has already been passed, they have seen the error “There was a problem launching this test, please close the window and try again.” without their response being saved in the database.
Workaround: Cambridge English to ensure process to set up test date highlights the need to set a value.
RootCause: Code area identified and provided to Metrica team further action under MET-7155
Resolution: Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-7155

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: High memory utilisation on PRD & STG Internal Checkpoint firewall
ProblemDescription: High memory utilisation on PRD Internal Checkpoint firewall
Workaround: None
RootCause: https://supportcenter.checkpoint.com/supportcenter/portal?eventSubmit_doGoviewsolutiondetails=&solutionid=sk98590&partition=Advanced&product=Identity    Following a policy install, CPU usage by pdpd ramps up to 100% and memory usage increases too.  This is a result of the policy install triggering an "update all" command so the gateways reassess AD audit log data.    This is not recommended in large scale environments such as hours, as defined in Best Practice for Identity Awareness from the vendor:https://supportcenter.checkpoint.com/supportcenter/portal?eventSubmit_doGoviewsolutiondetails=&solutionid=sk88520#General Guidelines - Disable User Updates during policy installation    "Disabling User Updates during policy installation is possible starting in R77.10.    During policy installation, a process of updating all users' Access Roles and their group affiliation is performed. For a large scale environment, it is recommended to disable these user group updates during policy installation."
Resolution:

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-9135 - Candidate result gets locked due to discrepancies found at result components.
ProblemDescription: It has been found in one instance that ‘Writing’ component scores of a reported candidate got reverted to the previous result status soon after confirming the entire result from ‘Confirm Results’ section. There was no specific audit to find out what lead to these discrepancies but it could be seen that components other than ‘Writing’ were confirmed separately and ‘Writing’ component was confirmed later within a gap of milliseconds.    Please find the attached 5 extracts depicting the result and component audits of the reported candidate.
Workaround: In order to clear out the result from locked condition, a wipe out script was needed and post execution of it, the Centre was asked to mark the candidate afresh.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: No valid Kerberos token under klist when su'ing to a service account using dzdo
ProblemDescription: No valid Kerberos token under klist when su'ing to a service account using dzdo. Attempting a kdestroy fails. You have to destroy your token whilst still logged on as your sup account and then run dzdo su *user*.
Workaround: Destroy your token whilst still logged on as your sup account and then run dzdo su *user*.
RootCause:
Issue is due to the use of "su"

For  backward  compatibility su defaults to not change the current directory and to only set the environment variables HOME and SHELL (plus USER and LOGNAME if the target user is not root).

Because of this behavior su alone will not provide acces to the users kerberos token
Resolution: Advised users to use su -l "user"

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Resource busy errors when running job STS_O_REFDES_JOB and STS_M_REFDES_JOB on STSPRD01.
ProblemDescription:
Frequent message "resource busy and acquire with NOWAIT specified or timeout expired" when running job STS_O_REFDES_JOB and STS_M_REFDES_JOB on STSPRD01 database. This job runs every 30min between 8:15 AM to 7:45 PM BST and 6:00 AM to 21:30 PM BST respectively for O side and M side EPS.

Root Cause Analysis:
This happens when the jobs are executing the following statement in package STSAUTOMATION:
45:     execute immediate 'ALTER TABLE STSPACKET NOLOGGING';
257:   execute immediate 'ALTER TABLE STSPACKET LOGGING';

Investigative analysis: 
Is there a real need to set the table to NOLOGGING (which requires a lock on the table)? This risks any recovery especially if the timeout occurs when trying to set the table back into LOGGING mode as it might continue in a NOLOGGING state. 

The main concern was that if anything happens to the DB, you’ll only recover the data affected from the last hot backup (which are created every 10 min), not from the backup archive logs.

As STS receive data from MEPS, OEPS and SAP end, the volume of the data is too high and with respect to the current implementation, three benefits listed below as the said jobs are executed in each 15 min in STSPRD01:
1. Space is saved in the redo log files (UAT DB was down due to high volume of redo log generation).
2. The time for insert/update statement execution is decreased as each job needs to complete within 15 min.
3. Performance improves for parallel creation of large tables (i.e. STSITEM, STSSCRIPT etc.).
Mail chain regarding primary investigating of this issue attached (RE  Incident# 476913.msg).
Workaround: Need to unlock STSPACKET table to execute next scheduled jobs.
RootCause:
Root Cause Analysis:
This happens when the jobs are executing the following statement in package STSAUTOMATION:
45:     execute immediate 'ALTER TABLE STSPACKET NOLOGGING';
257:   execute immediate 'ALTER TABLE STSPACKET LOGGING';

Investigative analysis: 
Is there a real need to set the table to NOLOGGING (which requires a lock on the table)? This risks any recovery especially if the timeout occurs when trying to set the table back into LOGGING mode as it might continue in a NOLOGGING state. 

The main concern was that if anything happens to the DB, you’ll only recover the data affected from the last hot backup (which are created every 10 min), not from the backup archive logs.

As STS receive data from MEPS, OEPS and SAP end, the volume of the data is too high and with respect to the current implementation, three benefits listed below as the said jobs are executed in each 15 min in STSPRD01:

2. The time for insert/update statement execution is decreased as each job needs to complete within 15 min.
3. Performance improves for parallel creation of large tables (i.e. STSITEM, STSSCRIPT etc.).
Mail chain regarding primary investigating of this issue attached (RE  Incident# 476913.msg).
Resolution: STS-48 to handle.

Subject: Ensure that ODS uses optimal QEPs for backfills.
ProblemDescription:
Ensure that ODS selects optimum QEPs when running an ODS refresh.  Determine if it is feasible to refresh all ODS stats or if only key tables can be refreshed during the available window. 

Further investigation identified that the root cause was that the performance bottleneck was in EPS view ODS_M(O)_CAND_MARK_ELEMENT_MARKS.
Workaround: None.  It is likely that ODS will select an inefficient QEP based on stale table stats resulting in ODS processing exceeding the
RootCause: This problem only occurs when ODS calls this EPS view during a back fill process.  In the normal daily process ODS will call this EPS view to select data that has changed in a 24 hour period.  When this occurs the EPS view performance is acceptable.  However, when discrepancies are detected between ODS and EPS, ODS will run a back fill process that selects data from EPS that has changed over 60 days.  When this occurs the performance of the EPS view is not acceptable and causes issues with the timetable of the subsequent jobs.
Resolution: This EPS view has already undergone extensive tuning and it was felt that the performance could not be improved sufficiently by trying to tune any further.  The solution was to utilize the details of the discrepancy report that is produced by ODS.  The idea is to take these details and load them into a new table in EPS and then use this new table in the EPS view.  When ODS then requires to do a back fill, this table is loaded with the details of the discrepancies but the ODS job is run as a normal daily job.  This improves the performance of the EPS view because it only has to process about 50000 records rather than the several million records that would have been selected over a 60 day period.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: No CD's allocated to material order.
ProblemDescription:
Material order 30054508 was created automatically by the system on 09.06.2017 for entry order 20050713. This is the only material order for entry order 30054508. 

No CD’s were allocated to this material order. It also showed up on the spool report showing that maximum quantities has already been sent. 

Entry order header data: 
On the spool report for 09.06.2017 it showed that the maximum quantity has already been sent: 
As a result of the above, we did not become aware that the centre will not receive cd’s until they contacted us asking for it. 
We changed line 100 in order to despatch the cd’s, but it is still visible in the header data that nothing was allocated to this material order. 
1. Investigate why 0 cd’s was allocated to this material order? 
2. Investigate why the spool message indicated that the maximum quantity had already been sent? (This prevented us from investigating and sending the cd’s) 

This is related to incident #488287 in ITSM.
Workaround: Manually change the CD quantity
RootCause:
The issue occurs only when the Named Entry Order headers are updated with Calculated CD qty as “0” for Non YLE materials. This is a random occurrence and is not happening regularly but the impact to the business is high, as no CD will be sent to them. There were around 40 to 50 instances in production as on date from 2015.

The FM “Z_PRE_DEFAULT_CD_QUANTITY” is responsible for the calculation of CD quantity based on the entry quantity and PAC count combination. On analyzing the live example of Production, found that the payload from PI has been sent blank value and in ECC ,it got updated with zero qty in the entry order header.


FM: Z_EXP_RFC_GET_BOOKING_DETAILS  and  Z_PRE_DEFAULT_CD_QUANTITY
Resolution:
In order to avoid the above situation, a new custom report would be created to update the calculated CD qty value for the Entry Orders placed for Non YLE ,which was initially assigned with the calculated CD qty as “0”. The report first pulls the list of entry order records with calculated CD qty as “0”. The background job scheduled for the custom report is responsible for the update of CD quantity in the respective entry order header and the spool log retrieves the value of both success and failure records. 

For success records, the calculated (provisional) CD qty would be updated .Whereas for failure records, the respective error message would be captured in the report log .This custom report can be scheduled in production as part of Daily check where the data errors can be rectified easily. This also provides privilege to the user to have a track over Entry orders with missed CD’s for a particular time period.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP Urgent Cart in Error
ProblemDescription: We have a cart that needs to be processed (Cart:1000087838) It has progressed through approval (passed Bruno) and it now showing in error. PLease can this be resolved ASAP.
Workaround:
As per the design, When a substitute approver approves the shopping cart, system will check whether the substitute approval limit is >= Shopping cart value. If it’s less than the shopping cart value, then system will add additional approval level with original approvers manager as approver. In this case, original approver (LEBUSS) himself being the head of the organization, system could not find the manager for LEBUSS and hence system is throwing error. 

In order to avoid this issue, whenever LEBUSS is substituted with LAQUEB, then LAQUEB’s approval limit should be increased to avoid this issue. Also we need to re-submit this cart or delete the existing one and create a new cart to take it to PO.
RootCause: As per the design, When a substitute approver approves the shopping cart, system will check whether the substitute approval limit is >= Shopping cart value. If it’s less than the shopping cart value, then system will add additional approval level with original approvers manager as approver. In this case, original approver (LEBUSS) himself being the head of the organization, system could not find the manager for LEBUSS and hence system is throwing error.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Failed result transfer errors in the system
ProblemDescription: Results failed to get transferred from HANA to ECC
Workaround: Script execution on HANA.
RootCause:
The error was due to multiple instances of BODS job (responsible to transfer results from HANA to ECC) running at the same time as the data load on a single instance was causing other job instances to fail consequently (as all the instances were trying to pick up the same set of results while none of the instances was able to execute completely).

The JOB_RESULTS_CASE_STATUS_TRANSFER failed for 4 hours in RFC call to ECC by Interface “Z_POS_TRANSFER_TO_ECC” and all the consecutive instances (as the initial run time of 1 minute per instance was not enough to transfer data load/ records) which resulted in failure of results transfer of the candidates from HANA to ECC.
Resolution:
In order to resolve the above issue, following changes done at BODS end:

1. For the BODS job since handing huge data at one go was a bit troublesome, the job schedule was changed to run every 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.

2. The BODS job has been amended to put in a validation such that only one instance of the job is active at any given time. This is to avoid the same set of results from being picked multiple times from HANA to be pushed to ECC.

3. To monitor this issue now BODS and HANA team keeps regular check at thresholds approval activity.

4. The fix is working fine and no recent issue of result failure is observed.

RFC 17487 & 17515. Fix applied both PR's 5059 & 4004.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Duplicate UCI Issue in our CEE Feeds to RM
ProblemDescription:
EPS has a stored procedure (esmqry.GETCEE) that ESM will call to get the candidate details for the CEE feeds that are sent to RM.

At the moment this procedure gets the session, assessment, component, centre details from centre_sess_comp_entries table, and the candidate details from the candidates table.  For the candidate details it will look for a value in the column tt_external_uid, if a value exists it will use this for the UCI number, if a value does not exist, it will look for a value in the unique_identifier column and then use this value for the UCI number.

Currently the tt_external_uid and the unique_identifier columns on OPRD are the same, so only one value can be sent in the CEE feed to RM.  The same does not apply to MPRD.  UK centres submit their own unique ID, which is the value in the tt_external_uid column and this can be the same as they have submitted for an OCR entry, and it is this which is causing the current duplicate UCI issue.

Even though we send the session, assessment, component details in the CEE feed, RM do not use this information for indexing scripts, they only use the UCI number that we send in the feed.

Donna Durose recommends that we change the EPS stored procedure esmqry.GETCEE so that if it is fetching candidate details for CIE to always use the unique_identifier column.  This should be fairly straight forward as the rest of the details fetched by this procedure would be unique to CIE (eg session, assessment, component), so we should be able to use this data to identify CIE candidates.

The only other option, would be to change the Entry File Formats but this would be a much bigger, more complicated job.

(No BTS incident but this relates to RM Service Call 5618415)
Workaround: There is no workaround currently. This has affected 9 candidates in the June 2017 session, which OCR and CIE will have to manage out.
RootCause: Currently the tt_external_uid and the unique_identifier columns on OPRD are the same, so only one value can be sent in the CEE feed to RM. The same does not apply to MPRD. UK centres submit their own unique ID, which is the value in the tt_external_uid column and this can be the same as they have submitted for an OCR entry, and it is this which is causing the current duplicate UCI issue.
Resolution: Donna Durose recommends that we change the EPS stored procedure esmqry.GETCEE so that if it is fetching candidate details for CIE to always use the unique_identifier column. This should be fairly straight forward as the rest of the details fetched by this procedure would be unique to CIE (eg session, assessment, component), so we should be able to use this data to identify CIE candidates.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Incomplete measures - RDS to SAP Marks Push
ProblemDescription: candidates have full marks in RDS, however these have not pushed through to SAP
Workaround: Manual repush of candidate and updating marks in HANA.
RootCause: Whenever a candidate has full set of marks packaged and ready to transfer (Status_code =’NOT_TRANSFERRED’) waiting for BODS job to transfer the result, in the meanwhile if new marks come from some high priority input channel and makes another set of marks and is ready to transfer, this simultaneous result sets getting transferred from HANA for a candidate cannot be handled at ECC which is causing duplicate appraisal id creation and missing of some modules marks(which will eventually come as failure in HANA).
Resolution:
New feature
In the design there is a procedure for packaging of results on the basis of measures received for each candidate "RESDET"."ucles.rd.procs.common::PACKAGING" and to set status_code as ‘NOT_TRANSFERRED’ as highlighted in screenshot below:The logic applied is to prevent packaging of results for any candidate_uid to become ready to transfer if there is one or more candidate_measure_uid is present with status_code = ‘NOT_TRANSFERRED’ in "RESDET"."ucles.rd.data::RESULT_TRANSFER" table i.e. to prevent packaging and creation of second set of results for a candidate respectively.

Below is the proposed join conditions :
In tt_package_ready_set, we are receiving candidate_uid from previous steps of procedure and checking if the measuredef set is really complete and the counts are equal. Taking these candidate_uids, we joinned candidate_entry and candidate_measure table to see if any corresponding candidate_measure_uid is present in "RESDET"."ucles.rd.data::RESULT_TRANSFER" table with status_code ='NOT_TRANSFERRED’ and exclude the candidate_uid for further processing using NOT EXISTS.
Only those Candidate_uid will pass from here which do not have any corresponding measures/ results already in 'NOT_TRANSFERRED' status and until this one gets transferred next set of results will not package.

ProblemDescription:
There are two times the candidate details will be sent from SAP to Legacy portal ESOLCR.
1.       whenever candidates are created/ changed.
2.       At the time of Result publish

The above activity  are handled in two different jobs to push the candidate details to legacy portal ESOLCR. This will enhance the candidates to register in the Legacy portal.

The process is whenever candidates are created/ changed, the 2am BODS job will push all the candidates details to legacy portal PRDB/ESOLCR. 
The root cause is, this job is getting failed some time with the following errors.

                This error occurs if the maximum runtime of a program set by system profile parameter exceeds its limit.

502720

470696

It has been observed that ‘Examiner Utilisation Report’ is getting technical exception while generating the same for few of the selected test sessions from dropdown list due to the fact that some non-centre writing examiners, those are being tagged to candidates for that session through Mark Manager, are not present at the relevant IWAS examiner table (CA_ADMIN.EXAMINER).

Please find the attached mail communication providing the analysis done on one such instance that was being reported through Incident# 460360.
Workaround: The said report could alternately be generated by specifying the date range while using the same interface of the application. If needed, the same could also be provided through backend script. There is another workaround for this; i.e. adding those missing external writing examiners individually from the application.
RootCause: As hub examiners were added via MM and not via IWAS, they are held in separate tables are not validated correctly since code for the same was not implemented.
Resolution: We implemented logic for the same to avoid any TE.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS - Absents overwriting Marks for CB Sessions
ProblemDescription: Cambridge English deleted the timetable component for a CB session and then recreated it.  Unfortunately Biztalk does not process DELETES to ConnectPlus so there was 2 Test Instance IDs in ConnectPlus for the one session.  It was noticed by a another user in Cambridge English so we manually resent all the candidate entries to ConnectPlus so the entries were attached to correct Test Instance ID.  Unfortunately, what we did not realise is that the timetable components were deleted and recreated again which created a 3rd Test Instance ID in ConnectPlus.  The test was sat on 8th July and marks processed as expected and were loaded to EPS.  As per process, 4 days later Biztalk polled ConnectPlus for the Candidate Attendance Status and these were processed but ESM and EPS do not take into account the Test Instance ID so all marks in EPS were overwritten with an Absent.
Workaround: Delete the Absents from ESM and replay the marks through Aggregation.
RootCause: see Resolution below
Resolution:
(from Donna Durose) Amend a trigger on the working_raw_marks table so that if a mark exists in EPS, then an Absent cannot overwrite this.  Only a manually keyed Absent can overwrite a mark - I believe this is already in place for Paper Based (PB) sessions

7/2/18: I believe Cambridge English are in the process of raising a change request with RM so that ConnectPlus / Biztalk processes DELETE records therefore this issue should not arise again, plus they are slowly moving all their products over to SAP.  I think this PR can be closed now.
Donna

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Missing Mark annotations not pulling through to VCI screen where unit / component mark element is 01
ProblemDescription:
During End to End UAT for the June 2017 series I have discovered that there is a defect with the View consolidated Issues (VCI) screen. The screen brings together data from marks consolidation issues/scenarios, which are identified via the Excheck (missing script investigation) process or checks of missing mark data bases and the annotations we add to EPS.

When the VCI was first developed any missing mark investigations (MIB) that fitted certain criteria would add to the VCI and bring the missing mark annotations with them, it seems that one of the triggers for this to happen was the unit/component having a Mark Element of 1. Recently for some reason unknown, when Units and components are set up they use the Mark Element 01. It appears that where the 01 mark element is used annotation do not feed through to the VCI.

Once a product (unit/component) has been set up with a Mark Element then the Mark Element cannot be changed, this means that for the VCI to be populated with annotations for both mark elements the trigger needs changed so that it accepts both 1 and 01 mark elements.
RootCause: The screen was designed to work in this way - we will change the code to satisfy the requirement described above.
Resolution:
Doug C to email confirming closure see activity history
Fix was part of December '17 release 
Deployed under RFC 19227

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-2937 - IWAS is not accepting centre specific General Training versions from Base Data
ProblemDescription:
It is observed that IWAS is currently not able to handle centre specific General Training versions that are mentioned explicitly in some centres with each Base Data release from IBASE.

With last production deployment in IBASE (IELTS Release 2 Sprint 4), zone details are no longer coming with centres through Base data. However, we found that IWAS is still trying to validate these centres for question paper zone code in centre details with the zone ids of the fixed dates that are coming through Base Data itself. So, expectedly, the condition is never satisfied to true to accept these centre specific versions for General Training module and thus, IWAS does not keep these records into the relevant table so that the centre could able to see the module while creating any test session.

Please find the attached document (INC#505880_Technical_Overview.docx) highlighting the area to replicate this issue.
Workaround: Scripts are executed to explicitly insert those missing records for those centres for General Training module with relevant version and other details into the relevant table (i.e. CA_ADMIN.VERSION_FOR_SPECIFIC_GT) of IWAS.
RootCause: Codebase where IWAS is still trying to validate these centres for question paper zone code in centre details with the zone ids of the fixed dates that are coming through Base Data itself
Resolution: Raised as IELTS-5115, included in IWAS R6.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BMU Reporting Job Failing
ProblemDescription:
The BMU Reporting job is failing intermittently. An emergency RFC increased the memory on SPJNTAP026 last week, but the job is still experiencing problems. Investigations suggest this is because the operating system is 32 bit. This means there's a limit to the amount of virtual memory available to complete the process. 

As per incident 507467, there are two possible solutions to this. 

The first is to split the package to make it utilize the memory more efficiently. This has been considered and will be considerable work that will need to go through the normal release process.

The second is to migrate the job to a new server that's identical to SPJNTAP026, but is running a 64 bit version of Windows Server 2003.
Workaround: NA
RootCause: BMU job used daily millions of data only for look up purpose. It consume huge amount of resource, but due to legacy system(32 bit OS) job was unable to get the required resource. This is the reason job was failing continuously in PRD.
Resolution: We have changed the Look up properties from full mode to partial mode in two packages. In partial mode: it consume very less resource as compared to previous mode. but It's performance time is increased 4-5 minute. RFC number is : 17860

Subject: Incorrect Number of Valid Combinations are being Generated Owing to the Complex Optionality Feature
ProblemDescription:
Incorrect Number of Valid Combinations are being Generated Owing to the Complex Optionality Feature in OCR LIBS.

For the Syllabus/Component Code H472/02, aggregation was failing as in BizTalk end, 175 valid combinations were being generated due to the Complex Optionality Structure used in the QPRD in LIBS end whereas the real count should have been 15..

Business Impact: Aggregation was failing and incorrect Marking of candidates could have ensued.
Workaround: The test structure needs to be changed to remove the usage of complex optionality and opt for a flat structure instead. For further details of the workaround, please refer to the attachment named "Instructions_for_FlatStructure_SetUp”.

Resolution: Training and knowledge share between OCR and CI has been offered and for the incident from which this PR occured was close via modelling the test data in a flat structure
