Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Category: CEO Preparation Centre Portal - non SAP
Subject: Unable to suspend access for prepcentres having previously deleted prepcentre having same fullname
ProblemDescription:
RCA done - detailed as below.

When two prep centres share same full name and email address from the same main centre or its linked main centres (linked prep centres), they would encounter an error when they try to edit/grant/suspend access to the prep centre. System will throw up the standard error and prevent them from making the changes.

Below are the cases reported with regard to this issue.

1.When there are two or more prep centres having same ‘Prep centre name’(might not exist under same main centre) -  both  being active.

2. When there are two or more prep centres having same ‘Prep centre name’(might not exist under same main centre) -  one might have been marked for deletion and be inactive too.

3.When the prep centre name is maintained as short name for any other prep centre in CEO. CEO maintains a field called ‘Prep centre short name’ and it holds BP number, or some SUP ID or sometimes the name of the prep centre itself which might bring up an issue.

4.When the same prep centre name is maintained in lower case for one and upper case for one, anyway producing two PCP IDs and two prep centres under two different centres.

5.When a duplicate prep centre is created out of Biztalk failure or any user error and no PCP ID gets assigned to it since the prep centre name is already there.

6. When two prep centres in a same main centre shares same email address(even if one of the prep centre is deleted or inactive or even if one prep centre is deleted and again created with the same name and same email address).
Workaround: Amend records in CEO and SAP ECC backend manually to sort out the issues
RootCause:
SP named : [CentreAssessmentManager].[CentreData].[ModifyCECPPreparationCentreList] 

Need to be modified in order to accept changes/modification for prep centres having their previous reference/previous prep centre with same name being deleted already.

Causes : Below are the cases reported with regard to this issue.

1.When there are two or more prep centres having same ‘Prep centre name’(might not exist under same main centre) -  both  being active.

2. When there are two or more prep centres having same ‘Prep centre name’(might not exist under same main centre) -  one might have been marked for deletion and be inactive too.

3.When the prep centre name is maintained as short name for any other prep centre in CEO. CEO maintains a field called ‘Prep centre short name’ and it holds BP number, or some SUP ID or sometimes the name of the prep centre itself which might bring up an issue.

4.When the same prep centre name is maintained in lower case for one and upper case for one, anyway producing two PCP IDs and two prep centres under two different centres.

5.When a duplicate prep centre is created out of Biztalk failure or any user error and no PCP ID gets assigned to it since the prep centre name is already there.

6. When two prep centres in a same main centre shares same email address(even if one of the prep centre is deleted or inactive or even if one prep centre is deleted and again created with the same name and same email address).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ODSPRDAG01 - Failovers on a daily basis
ProblemDescription:
This availability group is consistently failing every morning between 05:00 and 06:00. I've listed dates and times below. I can't see any obvious spikes in Foglight and vSphere to show the server is struggling. There are small signs of memory pressure and maybe disk latency in Spotlight, but this quickly recovers. 

I've asked Servers and Storage to see if there's any scheduled maintenance that runs between 05:00 and 06:00 that might impact on SPODSSQ004/005, ie does Netbackup copy kick in at this time?

2017-08-02 05:45:45.3433180
2017-08-05 05:48:18.6915932
2017-08-06 05:26:49.9616177
2017-08-07 05:51:27.0900555
2017-08-08 05:24:33.6695024
2017-08-09 05:24:36.8675099

Fortunately, this is happening between the ODSMaster job schedules, so this isn't impacting on the masterload. However, we do need to fail back each day, because the dashboard doesn't work when the primary replica is SPODSSQ005.
RootCause: There was instability on the cluster. We believe this was caused by a network bottleneck on the network card, which meant the quorum vote couldn't be established.
Resolution:
We configured an additional network card that's dedicated to cluster traffic. This means that when there is a bottleneck on the main network card, the cluster will still be able to establish the quorum status via the dedicated NIC. RFC17814

However, unfortunately there's no way to force the cluster to solely use this NIC for quorum traffic. Windows Server will attempt to establish quorum over any NIC available, so we do still see the odd brief interruption in traffic during busy periods. However, the cluster quickly recovers when it tries the alternate network card, which prevents a failover.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: OCR aggregation generating audit for endorsement changes when it should not
ProblemDescription:
OCR aggregation generating audit for endorsement changes when it should not.  The derive_candidate.aggregate procedure for assessment H420 for June 2017 after results issue (incident 510858) (as run through script dcsrag52), generated a large amount of audit which had to be rejected.  The audit should not have been generated.
There is also a concern that if this had been run before results issue it might have generated incorrect grading of the assessment.
Workaround: audit rejected by script
RootCause: This problem was caused by the change for OEPS-85 – GQ Reform Endorsements follow-up work.  The endorsement_grade procedure already existed in this package so Rakesh just copied the existing functionality and adapted it to allow for the new GQ reform endorsement.  Unfortunately, the existing code contained two updates for candidate_component_measures.  The first one set end_sid and eng_seq_no_derived to NULL and the second update calculated the new values.  Due to the particular scenario in which this procedure was called the first update resulted in the audit records being created.  As Tarit points out in his RCA the existing code would have produced the same result but since this is the first time that endorsements have been used by OCR for over 10 years there is no evidence of this happening before.  PVCS shows that this procedure existed in the package with the two updates as far back as 2011.
Resolution:
This PR should be scheduled into an OCR release so that the functionality of the endorsement_grade procedure can be assessed and a suitable solution to this problem found. December '17 release  which is parting place in Jan 2018

Solution deployed under RFC 19883

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cisco Prime not resilient and possibly unstable
ProblemDescription:
Summary from Intrinsic:
During dry run testing it became apparent that SNMP traps were not working when sent to the shared virtual ip address which Prime uses when in an HA pair, 10.112.41.10. Investigation showed that the HA had actually broken between the primary (10.112.43.150) and secondary (10.112.43.151) servers possibly a good while ago. The primary server appeared to be in a bad state as none of the services were started and would not start after several attempts and restarts. Whilst the services were not started, it seemed as though the primary still considered itself active and both servers were contending for the shared virtual ip address, which is usually only bound to one node.

On Tuesday evening whilst attempting to restore functionality to the primary server, the HA configuration between the two servers got removed which left the secondary server which had been active and working inaccessible.

Yesterday a VM backup of both servers was restored and functionality of the secondary server came back however, this was only after increasing the memory of the server as initially it was reporting lack of memory which was killing crucial system processes. The secondary server remains accessible today, but there may still be issues with memory usage and database problems.

There is currently no resilience to Prime, as the primary server is still not able to start its services. The secondary server although working, may have memory leak issues which may potentially be bug related.

I will log a TAC case with Cisco and explain the situation and provide them with output from both servers. Hopefully they can help us with a plan to restore full functionality to both nodes with minimal disruption.
Workaround: Cisco is currently working
RootCause: Database corruption
Resolution: Rebuild of Prime to version 3.2. Restore of backup. Under basic change SR

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Jagged Profile Report issues - IELTS-3640
ProblemDescription:
There are two distinct issues related to the this report
 
1. The Jagged Profile Report now only includes candidates with confirmed scores that have been through the jagged marks process, i.e. those whose 2nd Examiner (jagged) scores have been entered and confirmed and are now appearing in the View Complete Results screen of the Results area in IWAS. It no longer includes candidates that are waiting for 2nd Examiner (jagged) scores to be entered or confirmed.

2. The Jagged Profile Report will now include all candidates that have been through the jagged marking process, regardless of the second examiner (jagged) scores that are entered and confirmed. Previously, candidates whose second examiner (jagged) scores didn’t meet the jagged criteria (i.e. were not jagged) would be omitted from the report completely after the jagged scores had been entered and confirmed. Now, those candidates are getting included in the report, but they are not being assigned a 'Jagged Status' (W/S) - this field is remaining blank, which should not be blank in the report. PFA the screenshot (blank_jagged_status_screenshot.png) for this.
Workaround:
The candidates with proper jagged status that come under this report can be extracted by using the following query, which required Session ID as input: 

SELECT DISTINCT ABC.CENTRE_ID,
  ABC.TEST_DATE,
  ABC.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
  ABC.GIVEN_NAME
  ||' '
  ||ABC.FAMILY_NAME AS Can_Name,
  ABC.L Listening_Score,
  ABC.R Reading_Score,
  ABC.W Writing_Score,
  ABC.S Speaking_Score,
  listagg(ABC.RESULT_STATE, ',') within GROUP (
ORDER BY ABC.RESULT_STATE DESC) AS Jagged_Status
FROM
  (SELECT c.CENTRE_ID,
    c.TEST_DATE,
    c.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
    c.GIVEN_NAME,
    c.FAMILY_NAME,
    c.ID ,
    r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE R,
    r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE L,
    r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE W,
    r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE S,
    r.R_STATUS,
    DECODE(rw.rw_state, 'JAGGED_ENTRY', 'W', 'None' ) result_state,
    (
    CASE
      WHEN (r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE>=(((r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE)/2)+2))
      OR (r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE  <=(((r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE)/2)-2))
      THEN 'Y_W'
      ELSE 'N_W'
    END) Jagged_On
  FROM CANDIDATE c,
    RESULT r,
    RESULT_WRITING_STATE rw
  WHERE r.R_ID     =rw.R_ID
  AND c.id         =r.R_CANDIDATE_ID
  AND rw.RW_STATE IN ('JAGGED_ENTRY' )
  AND c.SESSION_ID ='171569'
  UNION ALL
  SELECT c.CENTRE_ID,
    c.TEST_DATE,
    c.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
    c.GIVEN_NAME,
    c.FAMILY_NAME,
    c.ID ,
    r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE R,
    r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE L,
    r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE W,
    r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE S,
    r.R_STATUS,
    DECODE(rs.rs_state, 'JAGGED_ENTRY', 'S', 'None' ) result_state,
    (
    CASE
      WHEN (r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE>=(((r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE)/2)+2))
      OR (r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE  <=(((r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE)/2)-2))
      THEN 'Y_S'
      ELSE 'N_S'
    END) Jagged_On
  FROM CANDIDATE c,
    RESULT r,
    RESULT_SPEAKING_STATE rs
  WHERE r.R_ID     =rs.R_ID
  AND c.id         =r.R_CANDIDATE_ID
  AND rs.RS_STATE IN ('JAGGED_ENTRY' )
  AND c.SESSION_ID ='171569'
  UNION ALL
  SELECT c.CENTRE_ID,
    c.TEST_DATE,
    c.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
    c.GIVEN_NAME,
    c.FAMILY_NAME,
    c.ID ,
    r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE R,
    r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE L,
    r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE W,
    r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE S,
    r.R_STATUS,
    DECODE(rl.rl_state, 'JAGGED_ENTRY', 'JE_L', 'None' ) result_state,
    (
    CASE
      WHEN (r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE>=(((r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE)/2)+2))
      OR (r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE  <=(((r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE)/2)-2))
      THEN 'Y_L'
      ELSE 'N_L'
    END) Jagged_On
  FROM CANDIDATE c,
    RESULT r,
    RESULT_LISTENING_STATE rl
  WHERE r.R_ID     =rl.R_ID
  AND c.id         =r.R_CANDIDATE_ID
  AND rl.RL_STATE IN ('JAGGED_ENTRY' )
  AND c.SESSION_ID ='171569'
  UNION ALL
  SELECT c.CENTRE_ID,
    c.TEST_DATE,
    c.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
    c.GIVEN_NAME,
    c.FAMILY_NAME,
    c.ID ,
    r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE R,
    r.R_FINAL_LISTENING_SCORE L,
    r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE W,
    r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE S,
    r.R_STATUS,
    DECODE(rr.rr_state, 'JAGGED_ENTRY', 'JE_R', 'None' ) result_state,
    (
    CASE
      WHEN (r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE>=(((r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE)/2)+2))
      OR (r.R_FINAL_READING_SCORE  <=(((r.R_FINAL_WRITING_SCORE+r.R_FINAL_SPEAKING_SCORE)/2)-2))
      THEN 'Y_R'
      ELSE 'N_R'
    END) Jagged_On
  FROM CANDIDATE c,
    RESULT r,
    RESULT_READING_STATE rr
  WHERE r.R_ID     =rr.R_ID
  AND c.id         =r.R_CANDIDATE_ID
  AND rr.RR_STATE IN ('JAGGED_ENTRY' )
  AND c.SESSION_ID ='171569'
  ) ABC
GROUP BY ABC.CENTRE_ID,
  ABC.TEST_DATE,
  ABC.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO,
  ABC.GIVEN_NAME
  ||' '
  ||ABC.FAMILY_NAME,
  ABC.L,
  ABC.R,
  ABC.W,
  ABC.S
ORDER BY ABC.CENTRE_ID,
  ABC.TEST_DATE,
  ABC.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO;
RootCause: The problem was introduced due to implementation of IELTS-1028. (deployed June 17)
Resolution:
The code logic introduced in IELTS-1028 has been reverted back and IELTS-3640 was solved.

Deployed to PRD RFC18686

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Improper EOR information for the Candidate Results if the last EOR has not made any marks amendment
ProblemDescription:
IELTS-3641

In IWAS, the Candidate scores can be incremented by the usage of the EOR functionality. After performing EOR, the admin users can pull out the report of the EOR status for the Candidate. Presently, the Candidate EOR letters and the EOR Status reports are showing incorrect EOR information by comparing to the previous EOR marking.  This is prominent when there has been no increase to the candidate’s mark in the past EORs. Please find the attached EOR letter pdf which shows that writing and speaking band scores are remained unchanged while the score has been changed when comparing to the original score
Workaround:
Actual candidates that come under this report can be extracted by using the following query, which required Centre ID and Session ID as input: 

SELECT c.CENTRE_ID, c.TEST_DATE, c.ATTENDANCE_REG_NO Candidate_No, c.TITLE||' '||c.GIVEN_NAME||' '||c.FAMILY_NAME Candidate_Name
FROM candidate c,
  result r,
  result_listening rl,
  result_reading rr,
  result_writing rw,
  result_speaking rs,
  (SELECT r_id, MIN(id) snmin_id FROM result_snapshot GROUP BY r_id
  ) snmin,
  result_snapshot sn
WHERE c.centre_id                = '<Centre ID>'
AND c.session_id                 = '<Session ID>'
AND (rl.rl_route                 = 1
OR rr.rr_route                   = 1
OR rw.rw_route                   = 1
OR rs.rs_route                   = 1)
AND c.id                         = r.r_candidate_id
AND r.r_id                       = rr.r_id
AND r.r_id                       = rw.r_id
AND r.r_id                       = rl.r_id
AND r.r_id                       = rs.r_id
AND r.r_status                   = 'Released'
AND r.r_id                       = sn.r_id
AND sn.id                        = snmin.snmin_id
AND ( r.r_final_listening_score <= sn.final_listening_score
AND r.r_final_reading_score     <= sn.final_reading_score
AND r.r_final_writing_score     <= sn.final_writing_score
AND r.r_final_speaking_score    <= sn.final_speaking_score );
RootCause: RCA doc attached (PR_5216_RCA.docx). Please go through this document for details.
Resolution:
The approach was taken to solve for the below mentioned scenarios in case previewing and Candidate EOR Letter Change/No Change Report generation works for individual and all candidates:

1. In case there are no Remarks and Candidate EORs have been generated multiple times after original score, then latest EOR should compare with original score to check whether there are any changes in scores.
2. In case multiple Remarks are done after Original Score, and followed by multiple EORs then latest EOR should compare with the latest Remark Score to ensure there are any changes in scores.
3. In case of Jagged, the most recent EORs should compare with Jagged(instead of Original Scores) to ensure whether there are any changes in scores.
4. In case of 3rd Examiner, the most recent EORs should compare with 3rd Examiner Scores(instead of Original Scores) to ensure whether there are any changes in scores.

Subject: CSP Report Generation Issue - NHibernate SQL Timeout Issue
ProblemDescription: Two centres have had reported failure in CSP report generation from Interchange. Having investigated, it was found to be NHibernate architecture where SQL timeout is by default is set as 30 seconds. Therefore whenever CSP generation takes more than 30 seconds to fetch records from backend; system exception is being shown/reported to centres users of Interchange application.
Workaround: We have managed to generate concerned centre's CSP report once database distribution of data has changed.
RootCause: NHiberate default SQL Timeout -> 30 seconds
Resolution: Unable to replicate. In production, problem only seen once or twice, so may have been due to increased volume at the time the report was run. No similar problems encountered over the Winter Series..

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CE Metrica deployments use a single location for all environments for SCALESET deploy files
ProblemDescription:
The SCALESET process in Windows Azure, the platform for Metrica, creates new VMs from parameter files.

IN the set up inherited from the original Metrica implementation, these parameter files are stored in a blob storage location that is common too all the environments.

In CAMLA metrica this doesn't cause an issue;  in CE Metrica it does.  THis is because CE Metrica has a different SSL certificate in PRD from the non-PRD environments.

Hence, if a deployment happens to a non-PRD environment, then there is a SCALESET UP event (a new VM is created to react to a load increase) that new VM will attempt to use the non-PRD parameter files, meaning the password for the SSL certificate will fail (or the wrong SSL certificate is being used, depending on your point of view) and the VM will fail to build.
Workaround: We've currently paused all dpeloys to non-prd environments whilst working on a fix.
RootCause: Bug in the deployment process.
Resolution: Re-write deployment scripts to be different between environments.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Discrimination,Facility and Difficulty attributes business requirement analysis and implementation
ProblemDescription:
The main problem lies is the expected business requirement analysis and implementation of the below mentioned attributes for which this PR has been raised. The issue that user has experienced is described below.

Issue description:
---------------------------------
There is a problem each content production user is facing while they add the Discrimination or Facility or Difficulty attributes in the test level inside the test details page. Please see the error screen shot attached 511647_error.png. 

The error occurs only when the above mentioned fields are having more than one numeric value added to it. Please see the attached image 511647.png red highlighted part as an example.

Issue can be replicated in two ways as mentioned below:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Item already on test
1. Log in. Choose a role that has access to Tests.
2. Go to Tests.
3. Open any test that contains an item with multiple numeric values for a single attribute. In our current setup, these are "Discrimination" or "Facility" values on multiple-interaction items.
4. Open the column picker on the left-hand (test construction) side of the window.
5. Turn on the "Discrimination" or "Facility" column. Click OK.
6. This triggers a server runtime error.
 
Place item onto test
1. Log in. Choose a role that has access to Tests.
2. Go to Tests.
3. Create a new test.
4. Open the column picker on the left-hand (test construction) side of the window.
5. Turn on the "Discrimination" or "Facility" column. Click OK.
6. Add an item with multiple numeric values for a single attribute to the test.
7. This triggers a server runtime error.
 
Once in the state that generates the error, any further attempts to open a test page (with an offending item) will trigger the same error.

For now we have added an error handling code as described in the workaround part.
RootCause:
We have investigated the above and found that because of the the presence of the below code, it is throwing an error. The below code is not able to handle the multiple numeric values assigned against the item. An screen shot of the item is attached here as an example.

double value = Convert.ToDouble(row[column].ToString());

File name: tests-details.aspx.cs
File Location: MetricaAdmin\modules\content
Method name: ShowTestGrid()

As per current code the line number is 999 but it may change depending on further release.
Resolution:
Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-7336
Code fix in UAT for 17,5 (PRD deploy planned 14/02/2018)

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Error while printing NQF Nationals Report (CAMS ADMIN)
ProblemDescription:
Details: 
Customer is encountered one error message while printing the NQF Reports. This printing of report executed one stored procedure (CreateNatCRF) in CAMS Database. Whenever, the stored procedure fetches records containing units greater than some specified (18 unit number) limit would throw an error.
Workaround: NA
RootCause: The stored procedure creates a temporary table (TempNATCRF) at runtime which fetches records from several tables (GNUB, Achievables, AchievableTypes, Registration). Whenever the records fetched contains unit number greater than 18 the report printing would throw an error (error details attached). The temporarily table which is created have attributes that is limited to unit number: 18 only. So whenever the procedure fetches records containing units greater than unit no. : 18 would show an error.
Resolution: This qualification is no longer offered by OCR and the documents are not printed so the PR can be closed.

Subject: Database backups failing for WHUATES01 on SDCJNTOR07
ProblemDescription:
We are having some problems getting the backups through for the WHUATES01 database on SDCJNTOR07.

RootCause: It was a memory-related issue with regards to the server towards the WHUATES01 database. Upon a database reboot after increasing the RAM of the server and also increasing the SGA_TARGET of the database, the issue didn't occur anymore. Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-3763 - Wrong activity is getting reflected in user’s score entry.
ProblemDescription:
Both the application UI and various other reports (e.g. Results History reports) indicate that a particular user confirmed scores for a specific test session on a date when he was actually absent. The User Login Report also shows that the user did not log into the website on that date.

Causal analysis:

While looking into this, we found that the application audits the results in such a way that it looks like the user has confirmed scores in SECOND_ENTRY for candidates belonging to the reported test session.

Please find the attached mail communication where the issue is further explained with the example of one such reported user and the timestamp on which he has given the scores for one of the candidates for that test session.

Business Impact: 

Administration and the user are unable to understand how the scoring was being done when the user was physically not present at the centre.
RootCause: When second entry scores are submitted, the component's state is changed from SECOND_ENTRY to SECOND_ENTRY_PENDING (in the back end). The component will remain in a "pending" state until IWAS can transition it to either "RESULTS_COMPLETE" or "JAGGED_ENTRY". At this point, IWAS does not record the time of this change in the component state tables (eg. result_listening_state) where part of the result history export data comes from. Once IWAS is allowed to transition the component to another state, that's when the component state for second entry is created. However, by the time this happens, IWAS has already lost the modification date information for the second entry.
Resolution:
This could be solved by reworking some parts of results engine and would require some more regression testing on the results entry page.

IWAS also records all modification dates in the component audit tables (eg. result_listening_audit) but these tables aren't built for generating reports and will cause performance issues if this is used to generate reports.

Bering progressed under IELTS-3763, targetted IWAS R7.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-3843 - Candidate EOR letter are sometimes failing to get sent over emails.
ProblemDescription:
It is seen that Candidate EOR letter are sometimes not getting generated as part of one of IWAS scheduled jobs (i.e. externalResultProcessingJob) which considers candidate marks from the Mark Manager external system to process candidate results and tries to send emails (Subject: EOR score for externally marked result (Mark Manager)) with attachments of the above letter to L1 centre uses for candidates who have received scores against their EOR requests.

However, it could be confirmed from backend that successful instances are found along with the problematic ones as mentioned above since 25-JUL-17 till date.

Causal Analysis: 
While investigating it further, we have noticed a specific type of technical exception (i.e. NullPointerException) while trying to either generate the URL or authorizing recipients for the report to whom the mail would be sent.

Replication Steps:
The issue cannot be replicated as we do not have email sent functionality at local and also it needs integration to other dependent systems like BizTalk and SSRS reporting server.

Please find the attached document which contains both technical and non-technical details of our investigation.

Business Impact: 
Sometimes the recipients (Centre User L1) of these emails do not find any attachment of Candidate EOR letter.
RootCause:
comment from Jon Phillips:
"ReportRegistry.java has a member variable:
private Map<ReportController, ReportDescriptor> reports;
But ReportRegistry is a Spring stateless bean and should not keep state with member variables.
I believe that when Spring re-creates ReportRegistry the reports map is not re-initialised and this causes null-pointer we see thrown in the error logs.
A simple refactor exercise to remove reports as a member variable will fix this issue. Alternatively a check could be done to verify that reports has contents but this a poorer solution.

My proposed diagnosis above also explains why we see this issue in PRD but we don't see it in UAT.
Spring only removes and replaces beans (ReportRegistry) when the application is under load and this does not happen in UAT."
Resolution: Removed reports as a member variable

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ATS Results Online - Administration Manage Dates Modify option not available
ProblemDescription: For some scenarios, when the ATS Results Online Admin logs in to the application and navigates to the Manage Dates Tab, the current session's qualifications are displayed along with their respective release dates for Candidates, Centres and  Universities. For some cases, the Modify option is not available and thus the admin is unable to make changes to the deadline dates, even if they want to.
Workaround: The available dates should be modified to future dates for all the components (Candidate, Centre, University) so that the modify option is visible to the user. Post the same, they would be able to modify the same to a desired value.
RootCause:
The business logic of Result Online - Admin module uses the below query to pull out the details of the Qualifications and the dates to display:

select *  from ENTRIESEXTRANET.result_session rs where to_date(rs.available_Until_Date,'dd-MM-yyyy') >= to_date(SYSDATE,'dd-MM-yyyy') order by rs.qualification.shortName,rs.userType;

As a result of this, it may happen that for a particular qualification having different dates of availability, the University dates are not fetched in the result set or any of the three are not fetched. 

The front end logic of the ATS Result online - admin module is designed in such a way that the headers (Candidate, Centre, University along with the underlying Release and Removal dates banner) is displayed separately irrespective of the outcome of the above query. As a result, if there are no dates fetched for the University User, the section below the University is kept blank and the 'Modify' option is not present.
Resolution: Non managed app, added to EE backlog with reference EE-41 - to be prioritised into a release if required.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP Grade set - Uppercase Gradeset
ProblemDescription:
Currently 1 PoS is being pushed to EPS from SAP per BODS job which is scheduled every 5 mins.
. 
- All that SAP BODS does is to transport the products from SAP to EPS and cannot handle re-push of failed products (this has to be re-pushed from SAP by the MDM team).

- There are limitations with respect to parallel processing of this job. One PoS is pushed in every BODS job. As part of the job, BODS triggers an EPS stored procedure and awaits for an acknowledgement from EPS to set the job status (complete/failure). 

- As the functionality is on the EPS side, the EPS team has to confirm if the same stored procedure can be triggered by if multiple BODS job are configured/scheduled in parallel.
RootCause: This was a service improvement PR to see if we could improve the performance or functionality of the BODS SAP to EPS interface.
Resolution:
Investigations were undertaken and the general conclusion is as follows; Luca has given approval to close this PR as there is no desire to re-design the interface at this present time.  

• EPS Team have confirmed that EPS would be capable of taking batches of product updates with minimal development work
• FUTURE CAPACITY CONCERNS - Tiago has advised that there shouldn’t be any capacity issues – see attached email 
• TURNING OFF THE TRANSFER ACKNOLEDGMENT FROM EPS TO SAP – Tiago advised against doing this – see attached email 
• PARALLELISM – CTS have confirmed it is not possible to use Parallelism to speed up performance – see attached email 
• CHANGING THE DESIGN OF THE BODS JOB – CTS have advised that it would take approx 2 months effort to re-design the BODS job – see attached email

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CAMS Transaction Log BAckup Issue
ProblemDescription:
The Transaction Log Backup on CAMS is creating several alerts that it failed.
This issue need to be investigated to prevent further failure in the future.
RootCause:
This incident is only triggered when the RESTORE HEADERONLY & VERIFYONLY  SQL statement is executed.
Unfortunately this takes additional processing time to complete the job (though it’s a good practice to always check & verify backups).
When this process failed to check & verify the log backup the entire CAMS Transaction Log Backup will send an error alert thus triggering a backup incident.

BACKUP LOG [cams] TO DISK = 'H:\SQLBackup\default\cams\log\cams_tlog_20180323051500.trn' WITH STATS, NOFORMAT, CHECKSUM [SQLSTATE 01000]
100 percent processed. [SQLSTATE 01000]
Processed 0 pages for database 'cams', file 'CAMS_Log' on file 1. [SQLSTATE 01000]
BACKUP LOG successfully processed 0 pages in 1.856 seconds (0.000 MB/sec). [SQLSTATE 01000]
RESTORE HEADERONLY FROM DISK = N'H:\SQLBackup\default\cams\log\cams_tlog_20180323051500.trn' [SQLSTATE 01000]
RESTORE VERIFYONLY FROM DISK ='H:\SQLBackup\default\cams\log\cams_tlog_20180323051500.trn' WITH STATS, FILE = 1, CHECKSUM [SQLSTATE 01000]
The backup set on file 1 is valid. [SQLSTATE 01000]


I can confirm that the CAMS Transaction Log Backup is running good and we do have a daily physical log backup files. 
I think it is now safe to close this Problem.
Resolution:
No issues found with the Transaction Log Backup in CAMS database.
In most of its execution, the CAMS log backup is executed successfully.
Backup files are pristine and safely stored in  H:\SQLBackup\default\cams\log\.
And as of this date,  we only have one alert related to this incident since January.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EAR request not feeding through from Interchange to EPS
ProblemDescription:
Similar issue to Incident:516289. Centre has raised requests for EARs on Interchange - received confirmation email with RSQ number. This has not fed through to EPS. Nor does the request show on Interchange when the centre is impersonated. Please amend this so that the EARs populate in EPS. Centre: 15233 Cand: 2078 Units: A162/A172/A182
RSQ:0000514021
Workaround:
A comparison was made between Interchange and EPS for EAR’s raised. The missing EAR’s were first confirmed by OCR and then re-pushed from Interchange to EPS. This worked for most of the EARs.

For some EARs there were data issues and hence it failed to load in the temporary tables with in EPS. For these the respective data was first corrected in Interchange ( omit unnecessary spaces etc) and then re-pushed into EPS to resolve it.
RootCause:
EAR created in Interchange feeds through in following process:
1. EAR is created in Interchange and be ready to pushed.
2. SSIS job picks those EARs and update a flag in Interchange and writes the file in EPS ftp
3. Then, those file was validated and loaded in temp-table - tt_req_interchange_requests_in, via SQL-LOADER.
4. During loading through SQL loader, it validates the data and creates a log. In case any bad-data found, a file with bad data is created. Also, records in original file after that bad record is not loaded in EPS temp-table y SQL loader in that run. This is designed as per SQL-loader’s control file.
5. Once the EAR is loaded in tem-table, after that, the EAR is processed from the temp-table to main table resut_enquiries by a shell script – o-usreq006.sh
6. Then EPS EAR information is again pushed back to Interchange through OWB job.
                This problem of EAR not feeding can be categorized in three type problem/reason as follows :
1. In EAR file there is a bad data with long name with unnecessary space values. Due to this this, data is not loaded through SQL-loader, as mentioned at Step-4. Also, as mentioned in the same step, the rest EAR which is following to that bad record are not processed. As a resolution of this, unnecessary space was removed and pushed again from Interchange.
Suggestion: In these cases, can we not put data validations and data cleansing at source/Interchange end. Any invalid data should be prevented from creation at Interchange, in the first place. If however, there is still some invalid data, they should not be pushed to EPS end.
2. The EAR which was not processed was on file processed on some certain dates and loaded in temp-table but still not loaded in EPS main table as follows:
2.1. EAR failed to process due to some data validation. Ex – EAR raised for a component for which no entry exists for regarding records. As a resolution, correct detail should be submitted by centre/OCR.
Suggestion: Again, these should be taken care at source/Interchange end so that invalid data is not sent to EPS.

2.2. The responsible shell fails or was down for some reason and unable to process valid EAR. Therefore, they got stuck in temp-table. As a resolution, either EAR can be re-pushed or that responsible pl/sql packaged procedure - result_enquiries_maint.Capture_Interchange_Requests can be run for that stucked EAR file.
  Notes: In Appendix, please find a sample EAR file, log and bad file, just for a reference.
Resolution:
Resolved in the OEPS May 18 release subject to the corresponding work being delivered in the InterChange Spring 18 release

Deployed under RFC 30552

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Mutiple VDIs failing (Manila & Cognizant) - Issue on NIC card failing on the OS
ProblemDescription:
VDIs been failing to connect from Manila and Cognizant. When the VM is opened via VSphere console the NIC Card can not obtain an IP (only APIPA Address). 

There are multiple incidents to be linked but several are Incident#516000 (VDI's of Brian & Ondie), Incident#521457 (VDI of Jamaela), Incident#521474 and 520879 (happened to Jhorelle twice this week).
Workaround: Assign a new NIC card the the VDI so the VDI gets a new IP. The new NIC has a new MAC Address, therefore the DHCP reservation for the particular VDI doesnt take effect. This causes the FW rules set for the VDI not to work as the FW rules are dependent IPs previously assigned.
RootCause: These outages were as a result of a problem with the vShield firewall appliance on the VDI host running these desktops. Whilst this appliance is powered off, all VDIs on the affected host will fail to get a normal IP addresses. We found that, as this appliance had failed on one of the hosts, a number of VDIs had their network cards disconnected or were failing to gain IP addresses in the correct VLAN.
Resolution: Powered vShield firewall appliance back on and will implement monitoring of all vShield firewall appliances in the VDI estate

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: To review BODS current configuration too see if BODS is fit for purpose post recent performance issu
ProblemDescription:
BODS root cause analysis:  
8th Sept 2017: # 517786 raised,  server in the BODS cluster was having issues in connecting to databases to which jobs were failing. 
Workaround: The BODS team moved scheduled jobs to run on dedicated server instead of continuing on the failing cluster.
Issue with failed cluster ODBC connection was resolved, server was restored to the BODS cluster along with returning BODS server schedules to use all 4 clusters the next day.
In between moving this server, the support team had deactivated the scheduled job between next run without impacting the job’s schedule. 
When server was restored back into the BODS cluster, the Job schedules reactivated picking up the activation(system/server time) instead of the original scheduled time.  
This resulted in #520406 being raised: Data not pushing through from SAP via BODS to EPS
BODS team changed the BODS schedule back to original start time for this schedule, removing the incorrect older schedule entries from BODS server to restore normal processing activity. 
BTS support teams processed the backlog of EAR PoS data to be pushed from BODS to EPS to resolve the incident.
Root Cause is attributed to the reactivation of the BODS scheduled jobs moved from dedicated server to Cluster server, the job scheduler picked up the activation time (system/server time) as start time rather than the earlier original scheduled start time.
Resolution:
1) The incorrect ODBC configuration on the app server was resolved by the basis team.

2) The functional BODS team reset the schedule and re-started it, then re-processed the back log.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Category: CEO Preparation Centre Portal - non SAP
Subject: CECP/Prep Centre Portal: Expired activation link
ProblemDescription:
When Operation Grant access is performed preparation centre access status will be changed to 'Pending Confirmation' and an activation link will be sent to the user on registered email address.
User has to click on the link to set up account password.
In this stage user is getting the error that 'Activation Link is expired'.

#WaterLine YES
#Super Networks
Workaround: Providing the password to the user by activating the account from CEO end.
RootCause:
• This process involves two systems one is CECP (SAP) and CEO (CAM DB) 
• For any changes in CECP a proxy call will be triggered to update the data in to CEO and data will be passed through PI and BizTalk to maintain data between these two systems synchronous.
• Because of multiple systems involvement in data processing there is a risk of intermittent communication failures, which causes the data discrepancies between CEO and CECP.
• In this case when user amends email id in CECP if there is a communication failure will result in different email ids between CECP and CEO for the same Preparation center
Resolution:
• Get the preparation Centre details from CECP including PCP ID, Email ID, and Name of Preparation Centre.
• Send the information to CEO (Legacy) team (IS SD Cognizant DotNet) and request for the details for the preparation Centre.
• Compare the Preparation Centre email id in CEO and CECP.
• If there is a difference observed, mail the user for correct email address among two
• On getting the information from user if CECP email is correct then assign a task to Cognizant APO team to update email id as per CECP records by mention the detail like Preparation Centre name, PCP ID, email that needs to be amended.
• In other case if the CEO email is mentioned as the correct email then update CECP records accordingly
• After updating the email perform  resend login from CECP
• User will get a new link to activate account.
• User will not face issues as email is in sync between CECP and CEO

CR 502 - This is in Backlog. However, there are no fixes we can do with the PR. So no point keeping it open and this is more of changes required.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: The CaMLA SSRS reporting server is unavailable
ProblemDescription:
Description of fault: 
The CaMLA SSRS reporting server appears to be unavailable.  I get a 503 - service unavailable error when I attempt to connect to it.

 Application / URL affected: Metrica CaMLA

 Error message: 503 - service unavailable error 

 Are colleagues affected - how many: 
 When was this last working? 

 What is the impact of this incident to business operations: 
Clients cannot generate Results
RootCause:
Memory capacity issue. CaMLA only configured with 7GB, CE with 28GB.
Microsoft site guidance on 503 error - If the report server is under high memory pressure, the report server will refuse new requests until the current application domain is unloaded and a new one instantiated. While requests are refused, you will receive HTTP 503 errors. If this situation persists, you should do one of the following: add more memory, move the report server installation to a computer that has more memory, or change the memory configuration settings
Resolution: CaMLA memory configuration has been changed. Next step is to increase memory capacity at a cost of $350 to CaMLA

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS - ARS print issue
ProblemDescription:
When running November 2017 Admin jobs through the session print request screen the attendance registers (Stationary ARS) are printing out of line. We have found two centres that are affected but are concerned that there may be more. The centres currently affected are MY212 and MU617. We have tried re printed the job for just these centres through the stationary re-print screen but the same problem occurs. We believe there is an issue in the way the centre name displays that is throwing the rest of the document out of line. We have checked the obvious that maybe the name is too long or the apostrophe is throwing it off but other centres with this in the name appear correctly.
Please can BTS investigate this as a matter of priority as this will now cause delays to the N17 admin despatches. The SPR for the centres affected are: 2812454 and 2813522.
Workaround: Remove apostophes and file is printed perfectly.
RootCause: an apostrophe in the Centre name is being identified by the ARS as a control character.
Resolution:
Amend the ARS extract package to identify an apostrophe and add another to it (this is used by Oracle to print a valid single apostrophe).
Further investigation reveals that the issue is caused by a grave diacritical character not an apostrophe. List of affected centres attached.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-4160 - Speaking test session field resets when previewing Candidate Letter report
ProblemDescription:
It could be seen that the selected value in ‘Speaking test session ID’ of ‘Candidate Letter’ (under ‘Candidate Reports’) is automatically getting reset if ‘ALL’ is selected from the list while previewing the report. However, the selected value in this particular field is not getting changed if any but ‘ALL’ option is selected.

Please find the attached SWF file to get an idea on how the application is behaving in this particular section.

Business Impact: 

Users have to select the ‘ALL’ option again from that speaking test session dropdown list if they wish to print the report.
Workaround: The user can set the Session date initially and if they need to get the report for all the dates, they can select ‘ALL’ in the Speaking session ID drop-down and then directly click on ‘Print as PDF’ instead of clicking on ‘Preview Report’. Or else they might preview first and then return to the Candidate Letter functionality and re-run the same as instructed above.

There is an issue in IWAS where the ‘Speaking test session ID’ select is reset if ‘All’ is selected and the user clicks ‘Preview report’. The select should stay populated with ‘All’ so that the report can be printed straight after previewing.

If an actual session is selected then select is not reset after ‘Preview report’ is clicked.
Resolution: Raised as IELTS-4160, added to backlog.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-4161 - RO contact details with special characters are not getting saved
ProblemDescription:
It is observed that ‘Name of person/department’ field in ‘Add/Update Recognising Organisations’ section is not accepting special characters (e.g. “/”, “?” or “*” etc.) whenever user tries to update any existing candidate. With this process of giving special character in this particular field, the association of RO with the candidate is getting affected. The issue could be noticed for any type of RO (i.e. STED – Subscribed/Unsubscribed, POSTAL or locally added RO by the centre). However, other fields in this section do accept special characters happily.

The replication steps are highlighted here at the below URL:
https://www.screencast.com/t/7b5IIoJxfcaK 

Business Impact: 

Users are not able to make changes to the RO where it needs special character in RO contact details. Also, they are unaware of the fact that any attempt to save the RO details with special characters in contact details could lead to de-association of that RO with the candidate.
Workaround: A script can be prepared if the change in RO contact details with special characters is needed to be done from backend. Also, we can tag again the affected candidate with the same RO through backend script execution.
RootCause: If an existing RO entry is amended to include a special character in the 'Name of person/department' field then the RO will become disassociated with the candidate record.
Resolution: Raised as IELTS-4161, addded to backlog.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Performance problem on CWE Tridion
ProblemDescription:
Foglight and Spotlight are consistently reporting that the AG Groups CWEPRDAG01, CWEPRDAG02 and CWEPRDAG03 have issue of excessive memory pressure.  Memory Pressure may cause performance degradation. This needs further investigation to determine whether all servers received out of memory errors, and verify whether an increase in workload, or changes in instance configuration caused memory consumption to increase unexpectedly.

There is also SQL Recompile issue being reported by Foglight on CWEPRDAG01. This not only slows down the process that is executing the procedure, but adds extra CPU load on the server. The June 2017 Health Check report also mentioned of consistent high CPU utilization on CWEPRDAG01. Additional CPU resource may be required for the 2 servers in the Availability Group.

Index Fragmentation in some large indexes in Tridion_cm is also a potential issue. This may indicate that some process or activity is causing excessive fragmentation on large indexes. This needs further investigation and possibly changing the schedule of the index maintenance job.

On CWEPRDAG02 and CWEPRDAG03, Object lock contention was observed during the monitoring period, taking 72.08% for CWEPRDAG02 and 85% for CWEPRDAG03 of response time. There is also an occasional blocking event on Tridion_Broker.
RootCause:
The server resource upgrade resolves the issue of High CPU Utilization on CWEPRDAG01.
We no longer receives alerts on CWEPRDAG1 about high cpu utilization.
Problem Record can be closed now.
Resolution:
The server resource upgrade resolves the issue of High CPU Utilization on CWEPRDAG01.
We no longer receives alerts on CWEPRDAG1 about high cpu utilization.
Problem Record can be closed now.  RFC# 18419

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EAR Priority Service Grade Change
ProblemDescription:
The attached EAR appears as open although all stages have been completed for all components up to conclusion (see attached).

THERE IS A GRADE CHANGE FOR THIS CANDIDATE WAITING TO BE CONFIRMED. As we can see in EPS Candidate Grades (see attached).

This candidate has a grade change on a priority enquiry and the UCAS deadline is today.
Workaround:
--REQ_PRD
UPDATE enquiry_request_parts erp
SET    erp.mark_released_datetime = to_date('08/30/2017 12:20:00 PM'
                                           ,'mm/dd/yyyy HH:MI:SS PM')
WHERE  erp.cer_sid = 995054
AND    to_char(erp.mark_released_datetime
              ,'mm/dd/yyyy HH:MI:SS PM') = '08/30/2017 12:26:00 PM';
--1 row to be updated
RootCause: Commits are not handled correctly in a specific scenario and because of that whenever a user clicks on released button MARK_RELEASED_BY_SID and MARK_RELEASED_DATETIME are always updated and committed. It does not depend on whether OK/Save or Cancel button is clicked after that.
Resolution:
The solution would be to modify the code logic so that change will not get committed once we click on ‘Release’ button.

One way to do this is by calling the procedure  Raw_Data_Maint.Val_Err_Mk with passing two parameters p_mcf_sid  and p_nocommit instead of only p_mcf_sid.

CI has accepted the workaround as the solution so this PR can be closed.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP- Personalised print output files contain no candidates
ProblemDescription:
In the personalised print output to printing team for SAP delivery group, candidate details are not sent.

Idoc created from PO output is sent with blank candidate details. Blank details of the candidate is due to ZPRE_CAND_DETAIL table update failure.

Incidents: 523847,524811

#WaterLine YES
Workaround: Maintain the ZPRE_CAND_DETAIL manually with candidate details and retrigger the output in PO.
RootCause: Fix will be deployed in FEBMTR for the table lock issue
Resolution:
1. In the program “ZPRER_MATERIALORDER_CREATE”, code changes are required in the form ‘f_populate_custom_tables’.
2. Custom table ‘ZPRE_CAND_DETAIL’ is inserted first time during material order creation process. As per the current logic, standard lock function modules (ENQUEUE_E_TABLE/DEQUEUE_E_TABLE) with modify ABAP statements are used. Moreover above mentioned function modules are in ‘NOT RELEASED ‘status.
3. Proposed logic will be ‘INSERT’ Abap statement and it used to put an entry in to the custom table without lock mechanism.

Changes are deployed in Feb MTR through RFC 19376

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Candidate is not being withdrawn from the OCR EPS screen
ProblemDescription: we have identified an issue in OCR EPS where user is trying to withdraw the candidate from EPS entries screen.In the Incident 526163, user tried to withdraw the candidate from the EPS entries screen by using the 'Withdraw' button. After this user tried to save these changes by pressing 'Save' button but EPS didn't show any error message so it was assumed that EPS successfully withdrew the candidate. however, when this centre order was re-opened again,candidate was still appearing on the Entry screen. This is an unexpected behavior and EPS should show a valid error message on the screen in this case.
RootCause:
The issue arises because there are manual grades on EPS and EPS rightly prohibits the deletion. However, when user tries to withdraw a candidate, having manual grades, using form FNORD013, EPS doesn’t throw any error message on screen and it gives an impression that the candidate withdrawal was successful.
This is because on form FNORD013 --> COC_CAN_BLK --> ON-DELETE trigger, there is a pl/sql block with EXCEPTION section. However, the RAISE command is missing from this section. Thus, even though server throws error while execution Candidate_Entry.Withdraw_Candidate, the exception gets handled on client.
Resolution: Resolved under RFC 35742

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IBM have identified a possible misconfiguration on our EPS platform zoning configuration
ProblemDescription:
During the recent EPS upgrade IBM made the following statement 
All of the hdisks on prd-vios1 are configured with 4x paths, all routed via fscsi2 / fcs2. Disks attached to prd-vios2 are configured with 8x paths - 4x via each of fscsi0 and fscsi2.

Although 4x paths is considered quite adequate for most scenarios, best practice dictates single points of failure should be avoided.
It seems likely there should have been paths provided via another interface to prd-vios1.

SAN mapping and zoning needs to be checked and/or updated.
Review the MPIO best practice document at www.ibm.com/developerworks/aix/library/au-aix-mpio/index.html. You may want to reduce the total number of paths for every disk to 4x (via 2x different interfaces).
Workaround: No workaround is needed as the system is functioning correctly we just need to determine if the configuration is correct.
RootCause: IBM have identified potential a misconfiguration of EPS which needs to be investigated when possible.
Resolution: If and when we perform our next OS upgrade ion Liszt we will ask IBM to give us the correct configuration. However, as everything is working fine right now we do not plan to make any changes to the config and are happy to accept that  this Problem Record does not need to be fixed

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Candidates are not appearing on the Missing Marks Reports for which Tolerance failure was resolved
ProblemDescription:
Found this to be an inherent bug in the system due to which the data is not getting populated in the BOBJ report for some candidates for which following 2 conditions are true:

1.       Candidate not having the measure availability status as MISSING (but AVAILABLE)
2.       It’s masks were not present, they were expected by HANA.
Workaround: DB update using script.
RootCause:
After testing various scenarios given below, we may conclude that the issue is related to how marks from different input channels gets updated in staging tables in HANA. When business is updating any Tolerance check error from RD for which incoming measures has come from any channel except OMR, is working properly but with OMR, the new measure value given by the user while resolving the error from RD is not getting updated in HANA. Please find key points related to this issue-

1. New batch is getting created in staging cand entry measure batch table and got reconciled at a later time as well
2. The respective notification log errors got resolved
3. The old measures(bad data) got updated as rejected
4. The new batch though was not getting processed(IS_PROCESSED = 0) as corresponding staging measure data failed to generate in the marks injest phase and hence nothing moved from staging to main tables(RD) in HANA.
Resolution: In NW, when we are filling staging data in the measure table, we would need to make a call to database and fetch Measuredef reference ids corresponding to LIBS marks scheme ids. Once that is done, measure update from OMR will become no different than other input channels.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Data transfer issue from TRF to Partner Sites(IDP/BC) via CRT; IELTS-5356 relates
ProblemDescription: Candidate results data is transferred from IBASE to TRF via the IELTS TRF PUSH JOB. Once this data has reached the TRF backend, scheduled calls from the Partner sites(such as IDP or BCUK) requests the CRT webservice to pull the candidate data falling within the START DATE and END DATE. This is then picked up by the CRT job and transferred in batches. For some instances we are being reported of missing candidate records for some centres and test centres by the partners.
Workaround:
1. If the currently running batch is being affected by the error, then the present batch data (from ieltsresultstransferbatch table) is to be edited to limit each transfer processing to 9,000 records. This is the safety threshold but ideally given the present implementation, the job can process upto 10,000 records in 30 mins.

2. If the reported candidates belong to a historical session whose data is no longer present in the ieltsresultstransferbatch table, then the historical candidates whose LAST_MODIFIED is falling in the same range of  START DATE  and END DATE is to be taken into account and then they are to be processed in controlled batches of 9000 records each.
RootCause:
After analysing the CRT logs(attached), it is evident that after the request arrives from the Partners, the list of candidates are calculated based on the following query:

SELECT  P_TransferID,
TEST_DATE,
C.CENTRE_NUMBER,
CANDIDATE_NUMBER,
-1
FROM    LIFESKILLS_CANDIDATE C
JOIN CENTRE C1
ON C.CENTRE_NUMBER = C1.CENTRE_NUMBER
JOIN IELTSRESULTSTRANSFERDATAACCESS I
ON I.CENTRE_TYPE = TRIM(C1.TYPE_OF_CENTRE)
AND I.USER_ID = P_UserName
WHERE   LAST_MODIFIED >= P_StartDate AND LAST_MODIFIED <= P_EndDate;

Here P_StartDate is the START DATE and P_EndDate is the END DATE.

Thus, all the candidates falling in the above criteria is considered for the present transfer. Lets say this transfer picks up 14,000 records. This transfer is then split into batches of 1000 each, thus 14 batches. These batches are processed one at a time. Normally 10 batches are processed in 30 mins after which the job to delete the expired batches is called:

RdbmsOperation with SQL [IELTS_RESULTS_TRANSFER_WS.DeleteExpiredBatches]

Since the records are deleted from the batch table, they are not found by the below query:

"
Batch Retrieval SQL: SELECT C.CENTRE_NUMBER, C.CANDIDATE_NUMBER, C.TEST_DATE, C.AG_MODUAL, C.TITLE, C.FAMILY_NAME, C.GIVEN_NAME, C.ID_NUMBER, C.DATE_OF_BIRTH, C.OVERALL_RESULT, C.R_ABSENCE, C.L_ABSENCE, C.W_ABSENCE, C.S_ABSENCE, C.R_BAND_SCORE, C.L_BAND_SCORE, C.W_BAND_SCORE, C.S_BAND_SCORE, C.CERTID AS TRF_NUMBER, '' AS TRF_COMMENT, LAST_MODIFIED AS EFFECTIVE_DATE from CANDIDAT C , IELTSRESULTSTRANSFERBATCH I WHERE C.TEST_DATE = I.TEST_DATE AND C.CENTRE_NUMBER = I.CENTRE_NUMBER AND C.CANDIDATE_NUMBER = I.CANDIDATE_NUMBER  AND I.TRANSFER_ID =  <TRANSFER_ID> AND I.BATCH_ID = <BATCH_NUMBER>
"

This produces the error : 

BatchTransferDAOImpl:106 - Nothing found, therefore not valid.
Resolution: Raised as IELTS-5356, targetted IELTS 2017 R1c Drop 1.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Filter/Pager not working according in Metrica Content end

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS try to push packet and script records for not “ACTIVATED” sessions of STS.
ProblemDescription: As EPS try to push packet and script records for not “ACTIVATED” sessions of STS, all the half-hourly jobs are failing for this issue. EPS should have transfer data through half-hourly refresh jobs for only STS end activated sessions but this primary assumption of STS application violated for this type of issue.
Workaround:
Need to activate the affected session at STS end OR run below on EPS as MARK_PRD

DECLARE

   CURSOR c1 IS
    SELECT distinct cwk.spk_sid, cwk.ses_sid
    FROM   script_tracking_updates stu, candidate_work cwk
    WHERE  stu.source_table = 'CWK'
    AND    stu.transfer_datetime IS NULL
    and cwk.sid = stu.source_sid
    AND    NOT EXISTS (SELECT NULL
            FROM   script_tracking_updates stu1
            WHERE  stu1.source_table = 'SPK'
            AND    cwk.spk_sid = stu1.source_sid
            UNION
            SELECT NULL
            FROM   script_tracking_updates_audit stu1
            WHERE  stu1.source_table = 'SPK'
            AND    cwk.spk_sid = stu1.source_sid);


BEGIN
  FOR r1 IN c1 LOOP
    script_packet_maint.add_script_tracking_update(r1.spk_sid
                                                  ,'SPK'
                                                  ,r1.ses_sid);
  END LOOP;
END;
RootCause: Refer attached document for RCA.
Resolution: 4 resolution options described in RCA all requiring code changes.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-4603 - IWAS - Result Release date incorrect for sessions processed at end of DST
ProblemDescription: As Session dates are set with a 12:00 AM timestamp, if the Session date is before the change of clocks from DST to GMT and the Result Release is after the change of clocks, the calculation will remove the hour, allocating the Result Date the day before the intended one.
Workaround: Process for Assessment to change the release date for the affected sessions
RootCause: APO analysis confirms this is a logic design issue (see "RE Incident# 534508..." - the test date is recorded as 00:00, so "Once daylight saving goes off, it reduced to 1 hr. less than the test date; eventually the date becomes the previous date. E.g. for Test Date 21-10-17, the date is considered as 20-10-17. ".
Resolution: Assigned IELTS-4603, added to backlog

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Failure in CAMS PLR-ULN validation
ProblemDescription: The CAMS PLR-ULN Validation was failing when GetUlnValidationBatchSize was set as 5000, it is working properly with lower batch size say 1000, whereas 5000 is standard configuration setting for this batch size which is followed for CIE business stream as well. Please find the attached error log to get further details.
Workaround: The batch size was decreased to 1000 to process the backlog CAMS items temporarily.
RootCause:
We have checked the code and found that the request is sent in batches (and not one request per uln) , i.e. Suppose we have a batch size of 1000 records , PLR will extract the learners ULNS from the database in one call and send them across to LRS ‘SubmitVerifyBatch’ method. So i believe if there is a file size constraint of 1KB on LRS side I believe increasing the batch size in PLR can cause this violation on LRS side. 
I believe this was the reason why the batch size was reduced to 1000 from 5000. Our recommendation would be to increase the batch size only after LRS has increased their file size limitation.
Resolution:
as per workaround of reducing the batch size.

This will remain in place until the LRS service (external vendor) is changed to enable larger file sizes.

Please see email attached 10/7/2019 09:45

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP mini-checks showing KPIs outside of recommended thresholds
ProblemDescription:
SAP provides utilities to perform pro-active checks against the environment. These checks have recommended thresholds for different KPIs.
There are 3 that have been highlighted :
1) Global consistency checks are to be run at regular intervals. This has not been done against the production database.
2) For System Replication, the max sync log shipping time is recommended to be <= 5 ms. This is breached from time to time (can reach as high as 15 ms).
3) The total SQL cache share of the statistics server should be <= 20%. This is currently at the 80% mark.
Workaround: This is a pro-active problem record, there is currently no noticeable impact on performance.
RootCause: This is a pro-active problem record, there is currently no noticeable impact on performance.
Resolution:
1) DB consistency checks are now run weekly against the all production databases.

2) Even though, at seldom times, the replication times are outside of recommended norms, they are very seldom and is having no impact on performance. If there are performance issues in the future, we have the tools to diagnose if there is a correlation between the replication response times and the poor performance.

3) The high percentage usage of the SQL Plan cache is a symptom of the large SQL cache allocated to the database. There is no reason to age out the statistics server information. The SQL plan cache only needs to be increased if :
a. the PLAN_CACHE_HIT_RATIO is lower than 90% 
 or 
b. the CACHED_PLAN_SIZE is bigger than PLAN_CACHE_CAPACITY
And neither of these criteria have been met.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Issue in Mass update for ZA cases
ProblemDescription: When ZA cases are changed via mass update with new Class Id and Subclass ID it is not updating the 'When Occurred' field in case item with correct value when changed to blank. Due to this system throws an error.
Workaround: Manually change the When Occurred field value via F4 option
RootCause:
User is unable to update tariffs for Special Considerations cases in transaction ZIW58 in using mass update functionality.
User can enter all the required fields but the below error message appears when he tries to save the changes:
Error message issues: Class ID, Subclass ID, When occurred, Percentage are inconsistent.

Technical Analysis:
As per the analysis, from transaction IW52, while updating the case status as ‘APPLY TARRIF’ for ZA case, for new classification ID and sub classification ID, the value of WHEN OCCURRED field is not getting refreshed with the new value. It is holding the old value and correspondingly while saving the case, it is going into error.
The validation for the Classification ID, Sub classification ID, When Occurred, Impact Table Name and Percentage combination is done against the entries in view: ZPOS_V_TTSC. For the new Classification ID , Sub classification ID, the value of When occurred is not getting refreshed internally and hence the validation is failing while the case is being saved.
Resolution:
In order to resolve the above issue, following changes need to be done at code level:

Include: SAPLXQQM, for screen: 110, in Process After Input block, system is checking if WHEN OCCURRED field value (from pop up) is blank, it will not update the same in the table control at IW52 screen level. To address this issue it is required to have a logic in the include: ZXQQMI17, that will get the value of WHEN OCCURRED for view: ZPOS_V_TTSC based on new CLASS ID and SUB CLASS ID (entered by the user in the pop up). If the current fetched value of WHEN OCCURRED is blank then also it will update the same and refresh the old value in the table control for the screen 103 at IW52 level. This will prevent the system to throw error even if Class ID, Sub class ID, When Occurred and Percentage value combination is consistent.

The logic needs to be invoked  at line number 114 ZXQQMI17

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-6167 - IWAS Intranet Password validation
ProblemDescription: It has been observed that the error message "Password must be no more than 16 characters in length" is throwing sometimes even if the actual password length that is provided by the user is lesser than or equal to 16 when a special character '>' or '<' is present in the given password
Workaround: Avoid incorporating '<' and '>' characters while providing password or else keep the password length lesser than or equal to 13 according to the number of times the mentioned character is used if inclusion of the character is essential
RootCause:
It happens this way because the application takes that particular character as “>” or "<" correspondingly while processing the request which is a string consisting of four characters. In this way, this particular one character is transformed into four characters increasing the actual password length by count of three. 

When user tries to keep the password suppose that include 15 characters in fact, the same password converted into 18 characters while  processing the request when passwords contain the special character '<' or '>' once in the password which exceeds the max length criteria (max length = 16 characters).
Resolution: Assigned IELTS-6167, added to backlog.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Repeat of PR# 2834: STS-EPS Half-Hourly refresh job facing timeout issues.
ProblemDescription: Half hourly refresh job between STS and EPS to sync data in both systems are failing due to the following logged reason: “Distributed transaction waiting for lock (ORA-02049, ORA-06512)” in a transaction reference table done by a EPS procedure (STS_REFRESH_CONTROL.STAMP_STU_BATCH_ID@MEPS_STS_LINK(P_VIEW_CODE,L_BATCH_ID)), which is calling from STS procedure (STS.SESSION.SETUP_ALL_REFRESHES_RECORDS) through Database Link (@MEPS_STS_LINK).    Mail chain attached regarding initial investigation.
Workaround: No work around available for this type of incidents. But next half hourly refresh job running fine and sync records between STS and EPS systems.
RootCause: SCRIPT_TRACKING_UPDATES table of EPS is maintaining audits of push/pull job (Half-Hourly Refresh Job) between EPS and STS. Both systems (i.e. EPS and STS) commit transaction to this table in different scenarios to perform push/pull operation for each records, which need to push at STS end or STS acknowledged regarding record receiving at STS end. This type of multiple asynchronous transactions of EPS and STS are locking this table/row of this table in production (Very rare incident). It’s an expected behavior as per current implementation of mentioned affected Oracle push/pull job.
Resolution: The job has been monitored and the issue has not occurred in the last 12 months so CIE has asked for the PR to be closed. (Repeat of 2834)

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ATS Results Online Centres Issue in Results CSV for TSA-S1 and TMUA
ProblemDescription:
When the centre user tried to print the CSV for the TMUA and TSA-S1 qualification, then the error message is displayed to the user stating that there are no candidates present for the particular centre and qualification.

When the PDF is printed for these two qualifications, the alignment of the report is not proper and there is a slight displacement from the proper tabular representation as expected.

Please refer to the attachments for further clarification.
Workaround:
The CSV issue can be compensated by raising the issue with the APO - Cognizant team and they can pull out the concerned details for the candidates from the backend and provide the same in a CSV or excel format.

The PDF formatting cannot be accommodated by the APO break fix and needs proper developmental effort with testing to fix.
RootCause:
The Query to pull out the list of candidates for the TMUA and TSA-S1 qualification uses the below clause in the query present at setJdbcTemplate.GenericResultExporterImpl.java class:
/*
and s1.SECTION_NAME = 'Section 1' and 
s2.SECTION_NAME = 'Section 2' and 
s3.SECTION_NAME = 'Section 3' and 
*/

The TMUA and TSA-S1 are not having sections in the same structure as of BMAT qualification. Thus, none of the records are pulled out by the query leading to the message stating that there are no candidates although there are.
Resolution: CE to request under a separate project, if required. Added to backlog with reference EE-44.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Error in Results Determination Centres CDM Conversion Job IN# 506968
ProblemDescription:
The Results Determination Netweaver job/process that converts Centre data received from ECC into CDM format data for the RD HANA database contains a bug which may result in the data being out of sync with ECC. Details of the modules involved are:-




Netweaver Job: Z_M5_E_ECC_TO_CDM_DATA_CONV9

Program: ZPOS_ECC_TO_CDM_CONV_SCHEDULER

AMDP Class:

ZCL_POS_ECC_TO_CDM_CONVERT

AMDP Method:

  RUN_CEN_CAND_MD_CONVERSION

Bug:

The parameter passed to HANA procedure should be 'v_when_acq_completed' and not 'current_timestamp' (see attached code).
Workaround: Manual update in HANA DB
RootCause:
In this design, there is a ABAP program ZPOS_ECC_TO_CDM_CONV_SCHEDULER which is used for converting ECC data into CDM format.
1. In this program the sequential execution of the HANA procedure for converting the required field into CDM format from ECC and also the procedure to run the calculation process is carried out.
2. The conversion of the CDM format for the individual field has caused no error.
3. In this method RUN_CEN_CAND_MD_CONVERSION we are getting the last successfully completed time and for that we are querying table ‘BATCH_JOB_RUN’, fetching the details of centre_candidate_cdm_conversion. Before making this call, have to take last job run timestamp which is successfully executed.
4. The method calls HANA procedure "PROC_CDM_CEN_CAND_MD_CONVERSION" and we are passing the parameter ‘current_timestamp’. 
5. The ‘v_when_acq_completed’ parameter holds the last job run timestamp, this parameter must be used instead of the ‘Current_timestamp’ to the HANA procedure, so that the mismatch of TIMESTAMP can be rectified.
Resolution:
After changing the input parameter from CURRENT_TIMESTAMP to V_WHEN_ACQ_COMPLETED while calling the HANA database procedure, ECC and CDM table data (TIMESTAMP) will be in sync which will  prevent any data(TIMESTAMP) inconsistencies between HANA and CDM in future.

RFC# 31672.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ZD#590286 IWAS: Showing results have been completed for all 20 test takers - IELTS-4960
ProblemDescription:
'Today we received 3 Jagged Re-mark Requests for the CD test on 12-DEC-2017. All 3 were specifically for Task 2, and we never received any for Task 1.
Our PSN team are not aware of any new way of generating a jagged that would result in only one of the writing tasks being flagged and are still waiting on the Task 1 re-mark requests to arrive from Cambridge.
IWAS is showing that all results have been completed for all 20 test takers.
Our PSN are unaware of any new method of jagged calculation , and they cannot see any methodology that would target only one task as until tasks are remarked they don't know which examiner, if either, is in error.'

Acceptance Criteria:
1. IWAS determines the Mark type of writing component as per the logic mentioned in attachment Marky_type_determination_logic.xlsx 
2. In case of remark request, IWAS receives the marks for the writing task requested for remarking (not for the whole writing component). 
3. IWAS merges the marks for writing task1 and writing task2. The marks are then copied to main result tables. 
4. IWAS keeps audit of the Marks coming from MarkManager.
RootCause: IWAS was not developed to cope with writing tasks having mark type ‘RefW1’ or ‘RefW2’ and do the merge. IWAS was developed to handle mark type ‘Normal’ only and do the merge. The requirement was not made clear by partners when the initial implementation was done.
Resolution:
Code changes were done in IWAS to enhance the merging logic to handle marks with mark type ‘RefW1’ , RefW2’ or ‘Normal’.  Partners came up with the merging logic and changes were made in IWAS accordingly. 
Fix deployed  under RFC18976
