Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: FW: F5 BIG-IP SSL vulnerability CVE-2017-6168 – Severity: Critical
ProblemDescription:
BIG-IP SSL vulnerability CVE-2017-6168 – Severity: Critical

A BIG-IP virtual server configured with a Client SSL profile may be vulnerable to an Adaptive Chosen Ciphertext attack (AKA Bleichenbacher attack) against RSA, which when exploited, may result in plaintext recovery of encrypted messages and/or a Man-in-the-middle (MiTM) attack, despite the attacker not having gained access to the server’s private key itself.

Details on this issue can be found at: https://support.f5.com/csp/article/K21905460
Workaround: None
RootCause:
When encrypting something with RSA, using PKCS#1 v1.5, the data that is to be encrypted is first padded, then the padded value is converted into an integer, and the RSA modular exponentiation (with the public exponent) is applied. Upon decryption, the modular exponentiation (with the private exponent) is applied, and then the padding is removed. The core of Bleichenbacher's attack relies on an oracle: the attack works if there is some system, somewhere, which can tell, given a sequence of bytes of the length of an encrypted message, whether decryption would yield something which has the proper padding format or not.

An example would be a SSL/TLS server. In the initial handshake, at some point, the client is supposed to generate a random key (the "pre-master secret"), encrypt it with the server's public key, and send it. The server decrypts the value, obtains the pre-master secret, and then compute from that pre-master secret the keys used for symmetric encryption of the rest of the connection. Using the standard for guidance, the client sends a ClientKeyExchange (which contains the encrypted pre-master secret), then a ChangeCipherSpec, then Finished; this last message is encrypted with the derived symmetric key and its contents are verified by the server.

If the client sends a random sequence of bytes of the right length to the server instead of a properly encrypted pre-master secret, then the server will, most of the time, respond with an error message telling "I tried to decrypt your ClientKeyExchange contents, but this failed, there was not a proper padding in it". However, by pure chance, it may happen that the random string, after applying the modular exponentiation, yields something which really looks like a pre-master secret with correct padding. In that case, the server will not complain about the ClientKeyExchange, but about the Finished message, which will be incorrectly encrypted.

This is the information the attacker wants: whether the sequence of bytes he sent would, upon decryption, look properly padded or not.
Resolution:
Upgrade to unaffected firmware version

Deployed under RFC 18775

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Centres are unable to create GT test sessions for specific GT dates. - IELTS-5270
ProblemDescription:
It is observed that centres are not able to create any test session which includes GT module even though they are all facilitated to have extra GT dates.

While investigating, we found a flaw into the application codebase where a particular string “testSittingId” was wrongly used which doesn’t have any reference to the respective ORM object for class - SpecificGTVersionBO.java. This is why technical exception has been occurring every time when user tries to create any test session for a test date that does not have GT module included but the centre to which the user belongs has special privilege to have GT module for that test date. The issue is also happening here when user tries to delete existing test session under the above conditions.

The details of the technical exception that we found here are explained further into the attached document (Technical_Explanation_of_Incident_542421.docx).

Business Impact: 
Centres are not able to add new test sessions for specific GT dates or delete test sessions created under specific GT dates.
RootCause: The code segment dealing with this specific area has wrongly used a particular string – “testSittingId”, which doesn’t have any reference to the respective ORM object (SpecificGTVersionBO.java).
Resolution: Code change - Deployed to PRD under RFC18976

Subject: BIP backup
ProblemDescription: BIP database hot archive backup jobs failed, although we can manually run it successfully sometimes.   But most of time the scheduled BIP DB hot archive backup jobs will fail.   I have logged a support case 180115-000872 with Veritas.
RootCause: In the DNS reverse lookup zones, there is an entry pointing 10.112.107.147 to bw-bwp-node2hb.    The correct one should be 10.112.105.147, which already exists in the reverse lookup zones. Therefore there were two entries in DNS reverse lookup zones pointing to bw-bwp-node2hb before.     bw-bwp-node2hb is one of the HA nodes in upsapap055. This explained why our BIP backup jobs completed successfully intermittently since last PRD refresh.
Resolution: I have removed the wrong entry from reverse lookup zones. I have tested BIP backup jobs for 4 days. All the BIP backup jobs completed successfully.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: NHP (HANA Results Determination) unexpected IndexServer restarts.
ProblemDescription:
The Native HANA Results Determination database (NHP) unexpectedly restarts itself.
After further investigation and logging a call with SAP, it was discovered that this is a known problem with this version of HANA (1.00.74.04.393829) where if a new version of HANA studio is used access this old version of the database, it can cause the server to restart.
The root cause is a bug in this version and the solution is to upgrade the database version.

NOTE : This is a reoccurrence of PR5299.
Workaround: The workaround is to use the compatible STUDIO version (1.00.74) with the database version. The correct studio versions vs database versions are listed in SAP note 2375176.
RootCause: After investigation and logging a call with SAP, it was discovered that this is a known problem with this version of HANA (1.00.74.04.393829) where if a new version of HANA studio is used access this old version of the database, it can cause the index server to restart.
Resolution: The resolution for this problem would be to upgrade the database to the latest version. There is a project planned to perform this work. Please see attached document,"HANA Native Upgrade Statement of Work".

Subject: Candidate Results Online: Duplicate Candidates from SAP for two different Sessions

Candidates of centre UY020 are unable to generate SoR for the SAP session CAE - 02/12/2017 - AM – PB because SAP sent the candidates of UY020 for two sessions – 09 December 2017 and 02 December 2017 with the same CanSid ID, i.e. the candidate got duplicated between these two sessions and each record had the same CanSid ID.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-5365 - Duplicate STED RO is getting created in IWAS after BASEDATA release
ProblemDescription:
Problem: It is observed that new entries for already existing STED ROs are getting created in IWAS soon after releasing new BASEDATA containing updated information in their country details. As a result, IWAS contains multiple records for STED ROs having same name and ORGANIZATION_ID but different country information.

Analysis: In the reported incident, there was a requirement to change the country information for few STED ROs from TRF Verification Site. Once it was done, the country values were correctly updated for respective ROs in IBASE. To reflect the same in IWAS, a new BASEDATA was released which was having updated country information for those ROs. However, it leads to duplicate entries in IWAS for those ROs with same name and ORGANIZATION_ID but different country information.

Similar issue was previously addressed under ITSM Problem Record# 3956 (currently closed) wherein we had shared an extract detailing all those discrepant ROs. An analysis was also done on the technical complexities existed in that process to bring these three databases (TRF, IBAE & IWAS) in sync. In that analysis, we found few areas where it lacks proper communication.

Here, I am attaching another extract (PFA: RO_discrepancies_18.01.2018.xlsx.xlsx) which contains the details of existing ROs which are currently not in sync between these systems. In each worksheet of this extract, the existence of data highlights areas that are affected in this flow.

Business Impact: ‘STED Recognising Organisations’ report of IWAS is giving multiple records for same organization.
Workaround: Data Fix is needed to mitigate discrepant RO details between these databases.
RootCause: Incorrect process undertaken whilst amending RO countries. Process now clarified.
Resolution: Process clarified to business ops team, see IELTS-5365 for full details.

Subject: Database issue preventing Tridion multimedia components from saving
ProblemDescription:

We need to look into if it possible to set up something to automatically do this without doing it too frequently as it is a resource intensive activity.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: PDQ entry file errors
ProblemDescription:
User is unable to load entry for CCA session.
The problem can be summarized as below,
1. Business tried to load PDQ entry file.
2. The entry file contains candidate/assessment which is aggregated previously in the earlier series.
3. EPS checks for any earlier aggregation records and if so, it tries to delete the same - entry, grade information for parent assessment in earlier series.
4. In this candidate entry/grade removal process, EPS sets manual grade for parent assessment in one step followed by grade information removal for the same parent assessment. 
5. As per EPS code logic, if manual grade is set for any assessment, it restricts the deletion/removal of that grade information and abort the process.
6. Thus, in this entry file load, EPS aborted the entry validation process due to the manual grade is set for the parent assessment on the fly(though the parent assessment did not have any manual grade prior to the entry validation).

The issue was not there earlier. It is found that CAOM_BEF_DEL_TRIG1 was changed during MREL0021.10 – PR2558 which caused the problem. Earlier the problem was not there.
Workaround:
Removed the candidate details in the earlier series respect to the parent assessment in which the contributing child assessment (present in the current entry file) is aggregated.
This confirmed that, the EPS logic from where the parent assessment was stamped with a manual grade, was bypassed. Subsequently, there was no other  problem to remove the parent assessment from the previous aggregating series due to the manual grade constraint.

Then file would be loaded successfully.
RootCause: It is found that CAOM_BEF_DEL_TRIG1 was changed during MREL0021.10 – PR2558 caused the problem. Earlier the problem was not there. But as communicated with business Step-4 needs to be removed after an inpact analysis. This exist in Maintain_CCA_Agg_Info in package - candidate_entry_2
Resolution:
Removed the candidate details in the earlier series respect to the parent assessment in which the contributing child assessment (present in the current entry file) is aggregated.
This confirmed that, the EPS logic from where the parent assessment was stamped with a manual grade, was bypassed. Subsequently, there was no other  problem to remove the parent assessment from the previous aggregating series due to the manual grade constraint.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-5425 - Technical exception occurs while updating candidate details
ProblemDescription:
It is found that the application is encountering technical exception while updating candidate details with few of its fields (e.g. county state, post code, reason other etc.) containing ‘/’ or ':' characters. The reason why the issue occurs is the implemented validation which considers the aforementioned characters as invalid.

While trying to create candidate entry singly from application by giving the above invalid character to any of its fields, it could be seen that standard warning messages are shown to the user restricting him to save the details.

However, we found another way of making candidate entry with the same invalid character through candidate XML import functionality. This is the reason why application still has candidates with this invalid character in their details. If any alteration is done to these candidates at later point of time, the application searches for invalid characters and once it gets the same, it nullifies the test session details for the user session and as a result, ‘NullPointerException’ is encountered while fetching the details of the test session.

Please find the attached video (2018-01-24_1649.swf) highlighting key areas which need to be looked into while replicating the issue.

Business Impact: Users are not able to modify the candidate details.
Workaround: Script can be prepared and executed to modify the user details as needed.
RootCause: The "/" character was identified as the cause of the TE. APO were able to submit the candidate updates via the candidate bulk import functionality, which suggests that the string validation between the Candidate Management->Candidate Search/Update form are different.
Resolution: Raised as IELTS-5425, added to backlog.

Subject: Mark Manager rejects CB Test Versions that were previously primed as PB versions - IDP issue
ProblemDescription:
Theory of what has happened:
a. We think that when MM refers to a ‘super test version’, this is equivalent to CA’s bank data. I believe the MM super test version / banks are W1AC, W2 AC, W1 GT, W2 GT, R AC, R GT and L (which is shared between GT and AC)
b. When we send the xml version of the answer keys, MM checks the whole database to see if it has seen the same SQID (response Id) at any time in the past (PB or CB across all banks not just the relevant bank for the type of test being referenced). If it does, then it rejects the new attempt to load the data.
c. The task that was referenced by the error had been previously used in a test before the xml answer key feed was active (i.e. it was supplied in csv (human readable) format).
Observations:
2) We can receive error messages from MM 
a. when we prime TDM feeds to it and
b. when MM starts to do automarking and finds errors.
3) The session sat at AU240 at 9am (local time, 10pm UK time) for listening test was attempted to be marked around 41 minutes later. This resulted in an error message email being generated at 10:43pm stating “AU24017010687,CD-L,Must enrol in a Super Test Version”.
4) Investigations have shown that:
a. The test version used was 18A33L
b. The test material was published to MM on Monday 22/01/2018 between 10am and 11am (sent as CHG records)
c. An error message was returned around 10:45am on Monday stating “Test is not a super test version”
d. The error on Monday and from the instigation of marking on 24th only referenced the third task out of the 4 tasks in the test.
e. On 20/10/2017 a CB listening test was sat (16D09) which used the same task 3 as the 18A33L test. The 16D09 test was primed using csv format data (i.e. human readable) and is still active (within 90 days to cover EORs and other queries).
f. The priming of the answer keys on Monday was using the new xml format feed.

Can the partners help to resolve this conundrum that we can’t prime the task to allow marking to continue for 18A33L without deleting the answer keys for 16D09L which still needs to be available for queries. Can they relax the cross DB checks of the SQIDs to allow us to get the answer keys in for 18A33L and allow marking to continue.
Surely the checking for uniqueness should only occur on the relevant banks (super test versions) that are relevant for the component being sat and not across all possible super test versions since a listening task is never used in reading or writing tests and vice versa?
RootCause: Issue with Mark Manager, owned by NESA and licensed by IDP and BC

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cambridge Technicals the marks are not feeding through to CAAP, this is leaving the records in suspe
ProblemDescription:
Previous PR 3583.

Cambridge Technicals the marks are not feeding through to CAAP, this is leaving the records in suspense with no marks.  As per current code logic if entry date is over for Cambridge Technicals scheme. And we make an entry for a candidate after the entry closing date. Then no attendance list will be generated for this newly entered candidate.    But if we will add the candidate in the attendance list then marks cannot be entered for this candidate if the attendance list is already in submitted state (Submitted to the examiner).  Hence for this candidate marks will not feed through to CAMS CAAP.  If we will add the candidate before submitting to the examiner then we can enter marks for this candidate and the data will go through to CAMS CAAP.    Please find the root cause document attached.
Workaround: From CAMS CAAP application CAMS Admin users are entering the marks manually for these newly added candidates.
RootCause:
Root Cause:    1st – Business has requested us to open the session for making an entry for a new candidate by extending the entry closing date from back-end.   2nd – As per business logic this late entry candidate will be missed in the attendance list which has been generated before the entry has been created.   3rd – Business has requested us to add the new candidate in the attendance list from back-end.  But if we will add the candidate in the attendance list then marks cannot be entered for this candidate if the attendance list is already in submitted state (Submitted to the examiner).   Hence for this candidate marks will not feed through to CAMS CAAP.  If we will add the candidate before submitting to the examiner then we can enter marks for this candidate and the data will go through to CAMS CAAP.

Session closed too soon, so late entries came in as pirates meaning pirate entry processing was done meaning data not added to the marksheet.
Resolution: Duplicate of PR #3583 - OCR have confirmed can be closed.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Category: CEO Online Centre Portal - non SAP
Subject: CEO Preparation Centres having "&" in their name are getting created/updated with "&"
ProblemDescription:
Preparation Centres modified from CECP end whose name contains the symbol "&" is not getting updated in CAM DB.

For example, if the prep centre name is "Kids&Us Manresa" in CECP, then it is getting created in CAM DB with the name "Kids&Us Manresa". Due to this the reconciliation job which compares the CECP and CAM DB data, finds this as mismatch and updates CECP with CAM DB data, i.e. in CECP the name gets changed to "Kids&Us Manresa".

Further analysis have been provided in the attached document.

Deployed under RFC 31340
Resolution: Code change to mange '&' when sent from SAP

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM - CLEB (missing mark) used for Aggregation rather than IMRB (mark)
ProblemDescription:
For years ESM has used the CLEB (missing mark) for aggregation rather than the IMRB (mark).  This is due to ESM logic looking at two different dates to determine which record is to be used for aggregation.

For example, we receive a CLEB from RM on 17th January 2018 which is the Production Date.  We then receive an IMRB from RM on 19th January 2018, which is a Production Date, however it also has a Marking Date which is 8th December 2017.  ESM will look for the latest record for aggregation by looking for a marking date for an IMRB and a production date for a CLEB, therefore in this example it will use the CLEB as the 17th January 2018 is later than the marking date of 8th December 2017 for the IMRB (see attached CLEB_v_IMRB.png).

This will process and load a Missing Mark to EPS.

If this is fixed, it may also fix PR#3234 because the 'previous marker ID' required in a remark request can only be found if a previous mark has been processed rather than the CLEB (missing mark).
Workaround: In the past the business has had to manually key the marks into EPS, however now we can delete the CLEB and replay the IMRB so that the mark will be passed to EPS (see attached sample script).
RootCause: ESM ignores latest IMRB marks in aggregation process when there is a CLEB (missing mark). This is because ESM logic looks at production date for CLEB and compares that to older marking date of IMRB. This comparison produces an incorrect result.
Resolution: Fix Planned for ESM April 2019 Release.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Enabling and testing the QPV improvements - Waterline workarounds 4 and 34
ProblemDescription:
The business currently undertake two workarounds associated with QPV - these are covered by Waterline workarounds 4 and 34. The functionality that is required to remove these workarounds is already in the system but has never been utilised. We are using this PR as a delivery mechanism for this new functionality. The PR team will need to make data/parameter changes and configure the functionality in the test systems for the business to undertake full testing. The PR team will also provide guidance to the business on how to utilise this functionality. 

1) SA Keying Required for non SA Components due to version discrepancies. (Work Around 4 of PR Master list)

2)Special Arrangements, processed manually with mark adjustments carried out ahead of marks entry (Work around 34 of PR Master list) 

 Need to investigate whether this requires change in the current design to allow the system to select multiple version of QPV for SA modified material ?
Workaround: Manually applying QPV versions.
RootCause:
Programme randomly allocates QPV for Non YLE (standard and modified) material in an entry order --> NO QPV! 

Technical fix is required to include sorting mechanism in the internal table contains QPV set details, before reading the actual QPV using binary search despite multiple QP versions are maintained. This is required for Non YLE products- both Standard and Modified (SA).
Maintenance of BRM tables
Resolution:
A new logic to be added  in SAP to handle sorting of internal table contents based on QPV set number, before reading the QPV details using binary search. This helps us to prevent refreshing QPV set before actual allocation.

the changes are moved through RFC  20195  on 24/04/18

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: where in Secret ID + Pin is a Unique combination in SAP whereas Secret ID alone is unique in PRDB
ProblemDescription:
It change in design issue…where in Secret ID + Pin is a Unique combination in SAP whereas Secret ID alone is unique in PRDB. Hence the issue arises when 2 candidates having the same Secret ID (but different pins) in SAP are pushed to PRDB.

Secret ID and Secret Pins is generated based Standard FMs QF05_RANDOM_INTEGER and GENERAL_GET_RANDOM_STRING
For Secret ID – Both Integer and String will be generated and concatenated as unique ID
For Secret Pin – Only 4 Integer will be generated  and updated as unique ID.

We have instances where the Secret ID is getting generated with old value which occurs on random basis as these FMs will generate random values. Whereas in PRDB, Secret ID will occur only once and hence the candidate fails in PRDB.

We would require to validate the  retrieved data with old history of Secret IDs and Pins before updating in the Equipment of the Entry order. Validation should be handled as a design change.

Details are attached in mail
Workaround: manually changing Secret id along with id as unique combination same as PRDB  and push the candidates to PRDB.
RootCause: It change in design issue…where in Secret ID + Pin is a Unique combination in SAP whereas Secret ID alone is unique in PRDB. Hence the issue arises when 2 candidates having the same Secret ID (but different pins) in SAP are pushed to PRDB.
Resolution: Updated the function module which generates the secret ID so that it checks for existence of a value before it completes. If secret ID value exists then a new value is generated until a unique one is done.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-5810 - IWAS unable to merge writing test responses causing components to get overwritten.
ProblemDescription:
A flaw was found at Mark Manager end which sends improper/incomplete records for ‘Writing’ part marks which IWAS is not able to merge with the other existing part and thus, the component gets overridden to hold the lastly arrived part only. As the result is not considered to be in the normal flow, it could not get processed. The issue has been identified at both IWAS and Mark Manager end and development work is still in the process.

The merging job that combines scores and sets them as confirmed (simulating the second entry) needs to be investigated as the scores sent for some writing tasks appear in IWAS as not been confirmed.
Workaround: Script deployment to compile tasks together.
RootCause:
as per IELTS-4810
The writing marks are arriving from MarkManager as two sets of marks, one for task 1 and another for task 2. This is not an issue for reading and listening marks.
IWAS needs to aggregate the information from the two writing marks records into a single record within IWAS.
Resolution:
The merging checks if it is partial writing marks that have arrived or a full set. If a full set then no further processing is required.
Merging takes into account the merging of the marks, Marker IDs and ensure the totals are correctly updated for the full set of writing marks. It also ensures AB and NR codes are included in the merge process. Deployed under RFC 18686.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Server Patching Issue: RHEL overwrites resolv.conf
ProblemDescription: The NetworkManager on RHEL 7 servers overwrites the resolv.conf file upon reboot. The domain (DNS) and nameserver(s) are defined in the resolv.conf file. Without the contents, the web server will not display/load the web page correctly.
RootCause: NetworkManager by default causes the resolv.conf file to be overwritten.
Resolution:
Before the server patch activity (RHEL 6 and above).
1. Back-up the /etc/resolv.conf file.
Note: Make sure that there are no files under the /etc/ with the name resolv.conf (sample resolv.conf.save). 
2. Edit all the Ethernet interface files: /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-*
Add the following line:
NM_CONTROLLED=no
3. Edit the NetworkManager conf file: /etc/NetworkManager/NetworkManager.conf
Add the following line under [main]:
peerdns=no

The above work was carried out under RFC 19594

After performing the above, you can now proceed with the Server Patching.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP Entries: Audit trail report
ProblemDescription:
There was a development from the 2.2 project (BFS 1371) which is meant to provide an audit trail of the operations carried out on entries. This development was deployed but never worked in the production enviroment and as a result PR2640 was raised. This PR was closed but the issue was never resolved. The Network services team (James loose and Zane Sheldrake) have now approached me asking for system access to do exactly what this development is meant to achieve. this is why this new PR is being raised.

below is the solution over from the original BFS.

"2.3 Overview of Solution

In current design Oracle database is used as staging database. BPM processes captures all events and record them in Oracle DB however booking changes are not recorded in oracle DB.

As part of this development we are enhancing the existing development to capture the Audit trail information in Oracle database for all updates on booking and entries including the approval and rejection scenarios. 

A report will be created on the Oracle database to show updated on Booking and Entries-Entry order level changes and Candidate Entry level changes. This report will list out all fields at a particular time. It will not highlight changes, business need to compare 2 rows.  The report will be accessed from the portal by admin users."

the old ITSM incident was 321886

This report would give the business the ability to see full details of all amendments, creations and withdrawals for all entries. it would also provide visibility on bookings.

BPQ link: http://bpm-bpq.ucles.internal:51100/webdynpro/resources/ucles.org.uk/app~exp_audittrail_wd/AuditTrailReportApp?SAPtestId=1#
Workaround: non available.
RootCause:
The query used to fetch booking level details fetch data from Candidate_Entry table instead of Sync_Back_Log table.
Scenarios not working
Scenario 2: Report display/navigation/filtering – Bookings 
Scenario 3: Booking Creation
Scenario 4: Booking Amendment
Scenario 5: Creation of additional booking
Scenario 6: Booking Cancellation
Scenario 19: Test User role
Observation: 
User 1 :Centre (CEM) user for Centre 
User2: Cambridge English Admin user
Created entries using the above users.
Fields in the result audit display are as expected, except for the ‘SubmittedByRoleType’ field, which shows both users as having CEM roles, which is not correct. – The value for the field SubmittedByRoleType is updated in oracle DB as ‘CEM’.
Resolution: Booking level changes need to fetched from Sync_Back_log table instead of Candidate_Entry table. Date formatting need to be done for the booking level query.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: UTLSUP01A - AggregationEngine Refresh Failing
ProblemDescription:
When troubleshooting incident 557508, I've noticed that the refresh job for AggregationEngine is failing. The backup job in PRD has changed to use a dynamically assigned file name, so the refresh job needs to be reviewed. The job is currently disabled to prevent setting the database to restricted_user mode.

The problem is:

1. The database is in an availability group, therefore you can't always be sure where the backup file will be stored.
2. The name is dynamically generated and so the refresh process can't use a hardcoded name.
3. The only way to get the name of the latest backup is to directly query the PRD server, either at a SQL Server level, or via Powershell and retrieving the flat file path.
4. UTLSUP01A is on the ucles.data domain. File sharing access isn't possible from UTLSUP01A to the PRD servers.
Workaround: In the meantime, the SUP database will need to be manually refreshed as and when required.
RootCause: n/a
Resolution: Please close PR5768.  This should not have been raised as a Problem and has been replace with SR169748

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Duplication of Result Enquiry Stage 2 in SAP
ProblemDescription:
When Results enquiry case is created for a candidate, there are few instances where its creating duplicate cases in SAP

Example in ERP:

We have received two Stage 2 enquiries from Centre CH008 for Candidate 6501 (702343482) numbered 300005258  at 10.39 am and 300005259 at 10.43 am.

It should not be possible for the Centre to raise two queries for the same candidate.
Workaround: Closing the duplicate Notification case manually
RootCause:
Duplicate Result Enquiry- Clinical check (ZI) cases are getting created from portal for a single candidate. 
Expectation is that a single ZI case should get created per candidate and for relevant composite module. The duplication is occurring rarely and is not replicable.
Resolution:
To prevent the creation of duplicate Result Enquiry cases for the same candidate, a check has to be invoked at RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION  level, to identify whether there is already ZI case created for the same candidate. If one such ZI case is already being created before, for the same candidate, then creation of one more ZI case for the same candidate shall not be allowed.

System will try to retrieve already created ZI case for the current candidate BP, from Quality notification header table and Quality Notification Items table. If valid ZI case exists for the current candidate BP then a flag shall be set. Before calling the RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION, the value of the flag needs to be checked, If it set as ‘X’, then system will bypass the call to the RFC. Thus creation of duplicate Result Enquiry cases can be prevented.

The changes needs to be done at line number: 205 within RFC: Z_POS_CASE_CREATION

Moreover, system will prompt the user with a pop up ‘Results Enquiry - Clerical Check (Stage 1) case is already being created for the candidate’, if the user is trying to create duplicate case ‘ZI’ for the same candidate BP from different sessions or multiple users are working on the same candidate.

Deployed via Feb Mini MTR,  RFC 33537

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica non ascii character bug
ProblemDescription:
CaMLA has encountered a significant data integrity bug in Metrica.When adding a comment to an item, all non-ASCII characters in the item content are replaced with double-escaped HTML entities when the comment is saved. This greatly increases the risk of improperly formatted content appearing on CaMLA tests, and requires significant additional proofing work to make sure that does not happen. Fixing the issue is an urgent priority, as our ordinary workflow includes adding comments on hundreds of items per week.

Steps to reproduce:

1. Create a new item or open an existing item.
2. Enter any non-ASCII character (e.g. é ’ —) in the item stimulus, prompt, or choices. Save the item.
3. Enter commenting mode. Create a new comment anywhere in the item content. Save the comment.

Result:
HTML entities now appear in the item content. This is due to double-escaping. The XML view reveals that non-ASCII characters that were previously directly represented in the XML are replaced with HTML entities, but with '&' rather than a literal ampersand. For example this original text…
<simpleChoice identifier="B">at the café</simpleChoice>
…becomes…
<simpleChoice identifier="B">at the caf&eacute;</simpleChoice>

Expected behavior:
Adding a comment should NEVER change other item content in any way.
Workaround: non ascii characters should be added or edited once all comments have been added
RootCause: Code changes identified and provided to Metrica team further action under MET-7824
Resolution: Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-7824

ProblemDescription:
PERC/ROMB Batteries will fail every 2-3 years, they need replacing in order to restore the write-back-cache functionality. The only impact to service is a very slight, mostly unnoticeable performance degradation.

Servers we're currently aware of with PERC battery failures:
SPCSDSQ006
SPCSDAP029 - virtualised
SPCSDAP068
SPJNTEX102
SPJNTEX109 - virtualised
SPJNTSQ055
SPJNTSQ102
SPOCRSQ005
SPOCRSQ007
Workaround: Ignore, suffer the slight performance degradation and silence the alert.
RootCause: Use of the battery causes it to constantly discharge, recharge and it eventually fails due to the nature of batteries.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CF Indicator Not Pushing to EPS.
ProblemDescription:
The table which is getting inserted is OPTION_COMPONENTS
The source data from SAP is compared again the data from EPS OPTION_COMPONENTS table and the comparison is based on COM_ID, ASS_CODE, ASV_VER_NO and OPT_CODE.
If any of these values is not available in EPS, then the Operation code is set as Insert (code=’I’). If all of these values are matching with EPS table, then the Opertaion code is set as Update (Code=’U’)
And for OPTION_COMPONENTS table, we filter out all update records and pass only the Insert records as per the design.
Workaround: Script execution in EPS can update Carry forward Indicator.
RootCause: See attachment.
Resolution: This PR requires a change on SAP to correct the data transfer to EPS.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-6305 - IWAS - "java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded"
ProblemDescription:
Nodes become unresponsive as GC runs and exhausts heapdump. From the Java doc:

"Excessive GC Time and OutOfMemoryError
The parallel collector will throw an OutOfMemoryError if too much time is being spent in garbage collection: if more than 98% of the total time is spent in garbage collection and less than 2% of the heap is recovered, an OutOfMemoryError will be thrown. This feature is designed to prevent applications from running for an extended period of time while making little or no progress because the heap is too small. If necessary, this feature can be disabled by adding the option -XX:-UseGCOverheadLimit to the command line."

The GC overhead limit exceeding generally happens when java virtual machine is not able to allocate memory in the heap space.
RootCause: A need to update virtual machine RAM and tomcat/java memory setting in IWAS applications
Resolution: RFC was completed to update the java memory settings.  Under Rfc 32545

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interfaces O2C_I_232 and O2C_I_233 issue
ProblemDescription:
Check out the data in the attached file and find why we have so many blank POD dates?
Please check the incident 557563
Have the interfaces been working via PI?

Interface numbers:

O2C_I_232
O2C_I_233

Can we check the interface files to see if updates have been sent for any of the deliveries where there is a blank POD date. We may need to write some sort of file scraping script, or search using Notepad++
RootCause: The DHL and UPS interfaces places input files in FTP path to update the details of POD and External Tracking ID’s to the Outbound deliveries created in ECC. For DHL, there is no error in POD status updates whereas for UPS , multiple error occurs in ECC for the inbound IDOCs received for POD updates from UPS interface. Upon receiving the updates, found that few inbound IDOC’s goes into failure status ‘51’ due to the reasons “Delivery not GI posted, not POD-relevant, or already POD confirmed”. Duplicate feeds were also sent to ECC system, wherein the POD status is not updated properly. In order to restrict the duplicate feeds / incorrect updates in ECC, the following solution had been identified.
Resolution:
Before triggering an inbound IDOC in ECC for the Master Tracking consignment number issued by UPS courier service, a validation to be provided to exclude the delivery documents in ECC , having the Goods issue status updated as ‘C’ [VBUK-WBSTK = ‘C’] .If Goods Issue is not completed ‘C’, then check for the POD Confirmation status . If POD status is set to ‘C’ [VBUK-PDSTK =’C’], exclude the deliveries for further updates and do not trigger any inbound IDOC for the delivery documents. This will restrict the deliveries goes into Failure status and helps to reduce the duplicate data load to ECC. In order to keep track of the total number of deliveries for which inbound idoc is not created, an application log would be created in FTP location. The log will contain the details of delivery documents received for External Tracking ID update on daily basis. The Program “ZPREI_DELIVERY_PROOF” will be used to create application log for the deliveries which has been excluded from idoc creation. The new main object: Z* and sub-object: Z* will be created using SLG0. The application log can be seen using SLG1 and can be deleted using SLG2. The log file would be saved in the following path, so that people can have a track on the list of delivery documents sent from interface for updates.  Email Distribution List contain the details of Business User to whom an email communication should be send ,with the details of Application log, where the user can have the track of list of deliveries that have not gone for inbound IDOC generation. This is similar to the approach that the daily monitoring team is doing currently when there is any IDOC failure happens for UPS interface on POD update.

Business users will be notified with an automatic email trigger on daily basis. Details available in Application Log are furnished as below,

Please refer Incident # 623209 for resolution

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Discrepant count of Banned Candidates for ESOLASSESMENTSTAFF and PARTNER Users  IELTS-6671
ProblemDescription:
There is some sort of application caching issues which is causing this data discrepancy count for banned candidates. PFA the screenshots (i.e. CE_Assessment_user.png, IDP_Partner.png) provided by customer, which are showing the discrepant count.

Please find the below steps used for replicating this issue:

1. Take total count of banned candidates which are currently present at BANNED_CANDIDATE table.
2. Click on INTRANET module to login as ESOLASSESSMENTSTAFF user and visit the following section to check the count of Banned Candidates (Banned Candidates  Manage Banned Candidates):

6. Restart the application tomcat server.
7. After restarting the server, repeat Step 1 to Step 3.
Observation: The count is now showing the correct one (i.e. one less from the initial one).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CBT processing issue in high load scenario
ProblemDescription: It is observed that in high load scenario with the present processing rate, some messages are failing to process. Further with the requirement to double the processing rate, the present solution both at Connect+ and BizTalk needs to be analyzed if it can support the extended load or some code changes will be needed.
Workaround: Polling frequency is adjusted so that not more than 20 messages hit the Connect+ url at once.
RootCause:
Analyze the existing solution in BizTalk and Connect+ to identify any issue in high load scenario.
The issue was let’s assume we polled a batch of 25 candidates from connect plus using C+ list queue service and sent ack back to C+ of the successful receipt. 

Now our BizTalk process is processing those 25 candidates further. Here processing means polling CI, FA and AH from connect plus for individual candidate.

Let’s assume while polling CI, FA and AH from connect plus for the 23rd candidate failed for some reason. (let’s assume C+ service did not responded timely), the loophole in our current 
processing was we will no longer process/ Ignore the 24th and 25th candidate. (Here processing also means polling CI, FA and AH from connect plus for individual candidate) 
- Ideally we should keep on processing  the 24th and 25th candidate and only 23rd candidate is marked as error. If we don’t fix the loophole, 23rd, 24th and 25th will be marked as error.
Resolution:
Code fix needs from Biz-talk end. Need to planned for deployment 
PRD deployment on 29/04/2018
RFC#20218

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Standardisation Visitors Cannot be found in xPlan
ProblemDescription:
As reported by Katy today you are unable to find standardisation visitors in XPlan this is a problem with the logic we are using to set up the visitor in Xplan. For example this is a standardisation record we have received from EPS:

9719/8685/01SpanishLanguage(Speaking)(c/w)|21-APR-18|The Triangle Building Shaftesbury Road Cambridge|Mr Philip Noel Scully|386715|PHIL_SCULLY@HOTMAIL.COM|OCR

As highlighted we receive just the full name as one string not split between the component parts. When calling XPlan we set the first word in the string as the first name and second word as the surname. So in this instance it would be: 

First Name: Mr
Surname: Philip

We propose to change this so that the last word is the surname and the rest of the string is the first name, so it would be:

First Name: Mr Philip Noel
Surname: Scully

Is this acceptable? If it is we can look to make the change sometime next week into production. In the meantime you probably need to search for people first name in xplan surname value.
Workaround: Search by First name in the surname section in Xplan
RootCause:
As reported by Katy today you are unable to find standardisation visitors in XPlan this is a problem with the logic we are using to set up the visitor in Xplan. For example this is a standardisation record we have received from EPS:

9719/8685/01SpanishLanguage(Speaking)(c/w)|21-APR-18|The Triangle Building Shaftesbury Road Cambridge|Mr Philip Noel Scully|386715|PHIL_SCULLY@HOTMAIL.COM|OCR

As highlighted we receive just the full name as one string not split between the component parts. When calling XPlan we set the first word in the string as the first name and second word as the surname. So in this instance it would be: 

First Name: Mr
Surname: Philip
Resolution:
We propose to change this so that the last word is the surname and the rest of the string is the first name, so it would be:

First Name: Mr Philip Noel
Surname: Scully

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CECP: discrepancy between timetable overview and report
ProblemDescription: The timetable overview screen allocated entries count for speaking component shows all entries as allocated due to the discrepancy in the candidate number in backend table.
Workaround: As a workaround, open the “Allocate Entries” for the Speaking component and click on the “Save and Close” button this will change the unallocated entries count to one so you can go ahead and allocate the speaking component for the “005” candidate to the required sitting and slot.
RootCause: While 2 concurrent users are allocating entries for timetabling for the same centre at the same time, the candidates existing for the booking (allocated by one user) are getting deleted from the custom table: ZPOR_TIME_ALLOC  as the other user has already allocated some new/removal of candidates for the same booking . For this inconsistency is happening at the custom table: ZPOR_TIME_ALLOC level, causing the count discrepancy.
Resolution:
In order to address this, the deletion has to be done based on the candidate details/numbers present in the allocate entries screen. So change has to be done at line number 326 for View: V_TT_DASHBOARD, Event Handler Method: ONACTIONSAVE_CLOSE_ENTRIES, where the mismatch between the number of candidates allocated by the first user and second user in 2 separate concurrent sesions for the same centre has to be captured. 

For any such mismatch, a new popup window should be triggered if there is a discrepancy between the allocated entries from current user login. A message should be available on the popup window as “Another user is currently timetabling these entries. Do you want to proceed?”. 

Based on user acknowledgement, entries will be processed. 

RFC# 31672.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: PRD Internal Load Balancer failed after config sync
ProblemDescription:
• One of our engineers logged in to the active load balancer via the cluster ip
• They made a change to virtual server skypeForBusinessInternal_https
• When they went to sync they noticed the standby device ndc-lbi02-prd also had changes. So he sent an email to confirm it was ok to run an overwrite sync from the active.
• The email was sent 12 April 2018 13:59
• He received confirmation at 14:15
• He then then synced nhr-lbi02-prd to the group
• It said it had synced ok, but then showed ndc-lbi02-prd as disconnected
• 30 seconds later or so, his session to nhr-lbi02-prd was disconnected.  When he connected again it was now standby
• Ndc-lbi02-prd was not reachable
Workaround: Fail over to standby node
RootCause: Root cause is due to the load balancer being under high CPU load when the config sync was applied which caused the MCP process to fail a heart beat and subsequently result in the TMM process restarting as a fail safe
Resolution:
RFC 20179
Increased CPU reservation for the virtual appliance from 2ghz to 4ghz
Increased CPU count from 2 - 4

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Performance issue of store procedure- [ETLStaging].[MigrateExaminerSapEms]
ProblemDescription: A SQL job ExaminerManagementSapEms in server "UTLPRD03A\SQL01" runs everyday which call this SP [ETLStaging].[MigrateExaminerSapEms]. This SP works well and takes few seconds to execute when there are small number of examiners(10-15) need to pushed from SAP to EMS. But it takes large time to process and consumes almost all the data resources when there are large number of examiners need to push from SAP to EMS. Due to which above SQL job fails and also EMS site goes down as there is no database resource available. We faced this issue from last couple of weeks. Related incidents are 573190, 570889
Workaround: As workaround, we need to stop the SQL job manually to make the site up and working.
RootCause: Small number of changes do not have an effect, but for this PR a bulk data change was done which increased the number of data changes, causing job to fail and EMS site being impacted.
Resolution:
Investigation in the SAP team has shown that :
1) EMS is used by Cambridge English and data goes from SAP every day (For Cambridge English examiners only), and issues have not been raised.
2) The maximum number of examiners sent to EMS from SAP (ever) is less than 1,500 and we are not aware of any peak coming;

If a bulk upload of data is planned by the SAP team, will need to arrange EMS downtime. No change to EMS is planned to handle what looks to be a rare event, and can be managed with downtime.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Multiple Delivery Groups for YLE - Change log not Captured
ProblemDescription:
After CR 557 implemented it has been identified that, delivery block was set for all items considering the rejected line items which had confirmed quantity  as 0. This was identified to be a bug and it was fixed. In the meantime, some lines for which delivery block should not be set but it has been set. due to this it was not appearing for Delivery creation in VL10a. On the later date, same appeared as the blocks were removed but the removed blocks were not captured in change logs. Investigation is required for this to check the root cause for delivery block not removed.

Incident linked  - 568141

There is no code change required as we could able to see the change log getting captured in material orders. 
This PR would kept open for next couple of months to see any such instances occur else we shall close this PR as confirmed with Gayathri and Maria.
Resolution:
“Z3” Delivery block was set to all line items considering the rejected items with confirmed quantity as “0”.  Few lines for which delivery block should not be set, also been set with delivery block which is incorrect. Due to which the line items does not appear for delivery creation on earlier date had appeared on later date.
The reason behind the appearance of items in delivery screen was due to the removal of Z3-Delivery block from material order. Investigation has been carried out for the aforesaid issue and the bug was already fixed in incident “559250”.  

Upon further analysis, found that there is no change required as we could see the change log getting captured with both update and removal of Z3 delivery block in Material Order line items. Please find attached the analysis document for your reference. The activity log is available for Audit trials as expected and there is no new incidents raised recently for this.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: QPV allocation failure message
ProblemDescription:
QPV allocation failure message (copied below) for Entry order 20067289 (CAE KAD 02.06.2018).

None of the lines in the entry order have a QPV Set allocated.
Workaround: Update the QPV set manually in the entry order-20067289.
RootCause:
1.BPM System allowed creating multiple Entry orders for the same booking ID which is incorrect. This was a random occurrence happens in BPM. BRM table is maintained with the limitation of 500 entries for every minute result in multiple entry order creation for the same booking. Since the processes are running in parallel, when initial entries are submitted for creation, remaining entries were also picked for creation instead update. There is no track in system to save the interim response for the total entries submitted against the same booking until first process is getting completed.

2.QPV allocation failure message had triggered in ECC, since there is already one Named Entry Order- 20067288 available for Booking ID -11068094. System did not find any valid line items for QPV allocation for the new Entry Order- 20067289 created against the same booking.

1.Analysis for Multiple Entry Order creation: 

Issue occurs when more than 500 entries are submitted for a Booking at the same time. The entry controller picks entries to be processed in the batch of 500 entries for every 1 minute. The maximum entries to be picked i.e. 500 are maintained in the BRM table. 

Entry Order Creation Process :

 The booking details are fetched by the RFC - Z_EXP_RFC_GET_BOOKING_DETAILS and stored in rfcOutput. The entry order availability is checked for the booking from the output of Z_EXP_RFC_GET_BOOKING_DETAILS. If entry order is not available for the booking, then Z_EXP_RFC_CREATE_ENTRY_ORDER is called to create a new entry order and if entry order is already available for the booking, then Z_EXP_RFC_UPD_ENTRYORDER is called to update entry order that is available for the booking.
Resolution:
In order to avoid the above situation, entries breakup from BPM to be avoided (parameter value maintenance to be changed) since BPM Considers only first 500 initial entries for Order creation in parallel run. However the issue is occasional, changing the parameter value in future would result in performance issue. 

The aforesaid issue can be sorted, if the processes are scheduled in multiple runs instead of parallel run one after another by keeping an interim status for the total entries submitted against each Booking for Entry Order processing. A complete Impact Analysis to be carried out to accomplish the proposed change.


No Fix required, since its a design change. Confirmed by Ottley and Owen for closure of this PR.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM connections to LIBS not handled properly, connections are persisting and not relasing
ProblemDescription: ESM connections to LIBS not handled properly, connections are persisting.  ESM oracle database connections are not handled properly and it is impacting the communication between ESM and LIBS.  Recently, we had an incident (#573589) where some the ESM's connection to LIBS had been made and and remained open and not released.
Workaround: Kill old inactive connections.
RootCause:
ESM connects with LIBS to retrieve QP related data for various operations like session setup, CB processing, aggregation etc. But in some of the cases, once the data retrieval is done successfully, ESM does not terminate the connections with LIBS. This leads to multiple open & inactive connections of ESM with LIBS. 

These open connections may cause trouble later while trying to re-connect with LIBS.
Resolution:
Fixes to resolve this successfully tested and released as part of the RM/ESM 5.3 release

Deploy under RFC 34734

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Missing Entries in Marks/Candidate reports w.r.t INC#577361
ProblemDescription:
Issue: There are few entries missing for reports. Which means Candidates are not appearing in any of the reports for CA results/Test/Center based reports.

There are incidents raised frequently in recent months for the same issue. For instance we had RCA for Incident#577361 and notice the below anomalies between student data and Sales Oder Item data.

Steps for Workaround:

Ask User for exact report and selections of the report data. Selection are Key Assessment Date, Centre No. Program of Study, Sales Order & Students

Check the Info provider ZSLMHO9, ZSDTO02 of the report if the any relevant data is missing and the Identify the missing entries of the Student and Sale Order, Item

On confirming that we have data for SO & Student in both the DSOs. Trigger Full selective load between ZSD4D01 -->ZSDTO02 & ZSDTO02 -->ZSLMHO9 with filter Student = Missing Student's data.
RootCause: We clearly understood that Student data is not in sync with SO & Item data. Which means the deltas of SO & Item is being delayed in most cases. Refer the attachment
Resolution: Change in design by capturing missing entries of daily loads and reloading them again on next day.

Subject: Transaction ZEXP_DKME is locking table ZEXPNR_BCH for unsually long time

Incident 583153  : T-code  ZEXP_DKME, is taking  long processing time during submission. (for a single entry it took more than 5 mins) .

Another incident - 581073

RFC# 30134

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-7546 - Inconsistencies involved while confirming the result
ProblemDescription: It has been noticed the system to be auditing as the same user performs the first and second entry for result writing component. It has also been reported and consequently speculated as the system bypassed the confirmation of the result. Result progresses without allowing the user to provide the marks in confirmation stage (Second entry).
Workaround: Result progresses automatically
RootCause:
This defect is encountered when remarking the results of a candidate whose previous results were received from Mark Manager. During remark, after the First Entry scores are submitted, IWAS transitions the Writing component to Second Entry, but does not clear the First Entry data. In the back end, the RESULT_WRITING table still holds the First Entry data (eg. scores, task 1 user id, task 2 user id) and RW_STATE is set to SECOND_ENTRY. IWAS also inserts a new row to the RESULT_WRITING_STATE table to audit FIRST_ENTRY scores. At this stage, since scores are entered manually, IWAS should have cleared the data (eg. scores, task 1 user id, task 2 user id) in the RESULT_WRITING table.

In effect, when another user goes to the Confirm Results page, it would appear that the Writing Scores have already been confirmed. The second user confirms the remaining components (Listening, Reading, and Speaking) and IWAS transitions all components appropriately. However, IWAS inserts an incorrect RESULT_WRITING_STATE record for the confirmed Writing Scores (this explains the problem reported in both INC-594980 and INC-583544).

This defect applies only to the Writing component because of a special case for retaining the task1/task2 scores when they are received from Mark Manager. If the scores are received from Mark Manager, scores are retained, otherwise scores are cleared so that the scores could be confirmed by another user. To check if the scores came from Mark Manager, IWAS reads the data from RESULT_WRITING.RW_SOURCE. This is currently set to OSM whenever IWAS receives the scores from Mark Manager, but it is never cleared/reset when the results are remarked and entered manually.
Resolution: Fix developed under IELTS_7546 and deployed to PRD in RFC 34045

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange: All candidates are not appearing in Claims when uploaded through spreadsheet
ProblemDescription:
All candidates are not appearing in Claims when uploaded through spreadsheet.

When centre is uploading the spreadsheet it is getting submitted and after moderator samples it, centre is trying to view the claim but is seeing that there are no candidates displayed.

Further analysis have been provided in the attached document.
Workaround: Workaround is to take the Registration ID from the Registration table and then update the RegSeqNo in ClaimUnit table with the RegistrationId.
RootCause:
Interchange should not save claims in the database as long as candidate validation is not successful. But we are seeing that Interchange code is going ahead with the process and saving the claim in the Claim tables and then submitting the claim.
Because of this the RegSeqNo in the table dbo.ClaimUnit is having NULL value for the ClaimUnitIDs. This is the reason that candidates are not visible in the claim.
Resolution: Added to Jira Backlog with reference OCR-295. To be prioritised into a release.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Google Analytics and TagManager tracking included wrongly on Live Learning English
ProblemDescription:
It is possible to include 2 types of tagging on the Live Cambridge English website: Google Analytics (GA)and Google TagManager (GTM).
It is possible to choose which is included via fields in the publication properties in Tridion.
The 2 types of tagging should be independent, so the inclusion of one type should not affect whether the other type is included.
This is working correctly on the Live Cambridge English website except for the top-level Learning English page and the activities pages under that.
I have also verified that this problem is occurring in UAT. The testing in UAT is summarized as follows:
UAT testing: 3 test cases
  1) GA ID unset, GTM ID set in Tridion
      Main site: Correct - No GA tagging.GTM appears
      Learning English: Incorrect: No tagging at all, not GA or GTM
  2) Both GA ID and GTM ID set in Tridion
      Main site: Correct - Both types of tagging appear
      Learning English: Correct - Both types of tagging appear
  3) GA ID set, GTM ID not set in Tridion
      Main site: Correct - GA tagging appears but not GTM tagging.
      Learning English: Incorrect - both types of tagging appear.

So it appears that the logic that decides which type of tagging appears on Learning English is incorrect. Can you please investigate and fix this please as it is preventing us from deploying an important security fix on the Live website.
RootCause: The code for google tag manager was only getting pushed from tridion to the website for learning english when the google analytics field was populated. There was no code for it to pull through the GTM code when the GTM field was populated
Resolution: Code written to separate the GA and GTM code being pulled through when their respective fields are populated. Deployed via RFC 30830

ProblemDescription:
We are currently experiencing slow/intermittent net work issue that is affecting Manila AST, HD and CIE.?

Network Updates:

8x8 issue comes up with a solution to use BRIA as workaround, an application installed by the Service deskteam. It is clear that Manila MPLS and Internet connection are not the contributor for this issue.

BRIA was undergone for testing by the service desk and looks good as Interim.

This Message belows came from Lucian Nimigean (8x8 Support)

This message is in regards to your 8x8 Support case C1267070 - Customer Requested Hold.

Thank you again for running all of the tests for us. As agreed yesterday, I have reviewed all of the available data and also involved our Ops technical team to double-check my assumptions and results.

I can confirm that the test results look good. The fact that there was higher latency to our UK datacenter compared to HK or US, as it is in your case, won't represent a problem when you are going to use 8x8 with our proprietary application called Virtual Office Desktop (VOD). VOD uses a proprietary technology called geo-routing, which basically ensures all calls using the app will be routed to the closest datacenter, latency-wise. The tests you did using VOD confirmed there were no call quality problems reported. 

With all this in mind, my technical suggestion would be to have everyone move to using VOD in order to solve any latency issues you are experiencing at this point in time after your move from UK to Manila. If you consider going forward with this plan, I would have to defer any questions you might have in regards to the contract, financial side and legals, to my colleague Andy Needham who is handling your account from these perspectives.


Thanks again for all your help and looking forward to hearing back from you!
=============================End=================================================

Note: Two test account that was used from Service desk are from 8x8 support.

There was a pending discussion regarding 21 users that needs the VOD service (License)

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-7739 - Online pending volume data for particular sessions are showing negative values
ProblemDescription:
It has been noticed that for some sessions, the online pending volume counts are shown in negative values. 

It has been noticed that it generally happens when candidate is transferred to another session. Since the new session in which the candidate has been transferred already occupies the total provisional volume with confirmed candidates (online confirmed volume), the online confirmed volume increases compared to the provisional volume to account for the inclusion of the new candidate in this session and pending count decreases to the negative values to counter the increment in confirmed volume so that these both can ultimately be in sync with the provisional volume count.
Workaround: We have updated the column “onl_conf_volume” and “onl_pending_volume” of  “Session_Usage” table and fixed this issue from back end.
RootCause: According to the existing code logic, the issue occurs when centre user transfers a candidate with confirmed status from source session (session 2) to destination session (session 1) where candidate session slot at destination session is pending (although at source session, candidate session slot was confirmed for the candidate in question). Once candidate transfer is finished across sessions and centre user confirms 1 pending candidate, the existing code confirms all the remaining pending candidates erroneously and online pending volume decreases to a negative number.
Resolution: Business has confirmed this is expected behaviour. (see IELTS-7739 for further details).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Category: CEO Online Centre Portal - non SAP
Subject: ESOLCP Push failed on 4th July at 9:24 due to a failed delete call
ProblemDescription:
The ESOLCP Push (Entry Confirmation to the Portal Push) failed on the 4th July at 9:24am. A P2 was created (592176) and a war room setup to investigate the issue. The members of the incident management team were - Mark Lloyd, Ian Manning, Anjan Saha, Chris Simmons, Ian Waterson, Lalit Mandal, Bikramaditya Samanta. The team identified that the issue was being caused by a delete request within the backlog which was trying to delete centre JO302. The job was trying to authenticate to another SQL server via double hop which was causing the problem. This is the first time a centre delete request has been received since the databases have been migrated to the new infrastructure. 

A workaround was implemented to clear the back log and manually delete the centre which means the job will resume. However, a permanent fix is required to fix the double hop logon authentication issue identified by Chris Simmons.
Workaround:
The team disabled the delete line from the backlog and then re-processed. This successfully cleared the back log. The team then ran the deletion manually using an SQL script created by the APO. 
This will now enable the job to run but will failed the next time a deletion request is received.
RootCause: The authentication method used (double hop) by the job is failing. An alternative method of authentication needs to be designed and implemented.
Resolution: See attached email from Chris Simmon's regarding potential solutions.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Rank Order Violation not present and should be present
ProblemDescription:
If scaling is keyed on EPS that causes a change in the order of merit for candidates entered for the relevant syllabus/component, EPS does not allow the scaling to be verified and shows an error message.  This will stay un-verified until resolved.

In this scenario EPS has allowed us to verify a centres scaling (DE178 0486/05) even though it causes a change in the order of merit.  The system should not allow this to happen.
Workaround:
A check script has been scheduled for CIE to identify errors. The permanent solution can be implemented taking idea from the change done on the attached pkrank_bdy.txt(package body but file has been renamed as IVANTI won't allow me to attach package body)
Do a comparison between this one and the one from PVCS and you should be able to locate the change. Only one change has been done to block_range_cur cursor of violated function. This change is marked with I592890 comment. Also, note that the current change that this file contains only addresses one issue i.e. RO violation when there are SF blocks with missing candidates. However, if there are mark changes to candidates which results in SF RO Violation, this change will not capture it. Thus, refer to the comment on the package body. We can use SF threshold values instead of relying on MIN/MAX candidate mark achieved between these thresholds
RootCause:
When scaling factor sets are verified, the verification program on EPS does a comparison between (minimum mark + scaling factor) achieved by a candidate within a block with the (maximum mark + scaling factor) achieved by a candidate in the following block i.e. the block below the first one
The program fails to identify violation, if there are blocks created where there are no candidates falling in those blocks. This is because it results in a Numeric to Null comparison and technically this fails

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: MTU settings currently transient on production HANA appliances.
ProblemDescription:
During the network change on Saturday 07/07/2018, the replication for the ECC and BW HANA databases stopped working. This was resolved by changing the MTU setting on the server.
This change, however, has not been made permanent (it is only set in memory), so if the appliance were to restart (either due to fault or for a scheduled outage) it is most likely replication for ECC and BBW will stop working.
Workaround:
What is required is to persist the change and perform an appliance restart thereafter to see that the changes have taken effect and are working properly.
If the servers were to restart (either scheduled or unscheduled) and replication stopped working, the MTU settings for the bond2 interfaces on all the servers involved (upsapha001, 002, 003, 051 and 053) need to be set to 1500 rather than 9000.
We are working with Centiq to determine the exact steps and the exact servers affected  so that we can formulate a plan to roll out the changes.
RootCause: Network change caused replication to fail. Parameter changes were made but downtime was required to check if the changes made were persistent.
Resolution: This was implemented in production under RFC31886

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-7818 - IWAS: No PRRC email generated for some sessions
ProblemDescription: Some centres are not getting PRRC emails
Workaround: Release the candidate in two batches instead of releasing all the candidates for a release date in bulk each centre. After the release of first batch of candidates, IWAS will still find some candidates in UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING status and would trigger the PRRC email.
RootCause:
After validation completes PRC and uploads the spreadsheet, IWAS executes the following steps in the current world:

1.       Determines and saves result release date based on test date selected as input. 
2.       Withhold candidates. If there are candidates to be withheld, IWAS changes the status of the candidates to WITHHELD
3.       Release the remaining candidates. IWAS changes the status of the remaining candidates to released.
4.       Determines which centres are eligible to receive PRRC mails. If a centre has got any candidates either in UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING status, that centre is eligible to receive PRRC emails.
5.       Send emails to the centres.

We got this issue because, after step 3, the candidates uploaded in the spreadsheet will either move to RELEASED or WITHHELD status. That mean when IWAS will execute step4, if it doesn’t find any candidate with UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING status, it will not consider the centre for those candidates to receive PRRC mails. 

Before R5, the logic was slightly different. IWAS use to check UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING candidates before and after changing the result status. Pre R5 logic was:

1.       Determines and saves result release date based on test date selected as input. 
2.       Determines which centres are eligible to receive PRRC mails. If a centre has got any candidates either in UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING status, that centre is eligible to receive PRRC emails.
3.       Save the list of centres into a SET (java term).
4.       Withhold candidates. If there are candidates to be withheld, IWAS changes the status of the candidates to WITHHELD
5.       Release the remaining candidates. IWAS changes the status of the remaining candidates to released.
6.       Determines which centres are eligible to receive PRRC mails. If a centre has got any candidates either in UNCONFIRMD, UNVALIDATED or VALIDATING status, that centre is eligible to receive PRRC emails.
7.       Save the list of centres determined in step 6 in the SET created in step 3. 
8.       Send emails to the unique centres in the SET from step 7. 

Notes for development team: The change was done in ValidationManagerImpl.java in SVN version 15627.
Resolution: Addressed under IELTS-7818 and RFC30772

The view S_PACKET_DETAILS  contains the above tables:
CREATE OR REPLACE FORCE VIEW S_PACKET_DETAILS
(
   BARCODE,
   PACKETID,
   DB_SOURCE,
   QPV,
   FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG,
   ROUTING_INFO,
   MODIFIED_MATERIALS
)
AS
   SELECT "SP"."DENORMBARCODE" "BARCODE",
          "PK_ADDTL"."SPK_SID" "PACKETID",
          "DB_SOURCE",
          "QPV",
          "FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG",
          "ROUTING_INFO",
          "MODIFIED_MATERIALS"                                  -- Added 22/05
     FROM (  SELECT DISTINCT
                    "SPK_SID",
                    "QPV",
                    LISTAGG (RTRIM ("ROUTING_INFO"), '; ')
                       WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY "ROUTING_INFO")
                       OVER (PARTITION BY "SPK_SID")
                       "ROUTING_INFO",
                    CASE
                       WHEN COUNT (
                               CASE
                                  WHEN     "FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG" IS NOT NULL
                                       AND UPPER ("FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG") LIKE
                                              '%HIGH PRIORITY%'
                                  THEN
                                     1
                               END) > 0
                       THEN
                          'Y'
                       ELSE
                          'N'
                    END
                       "FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG"         --Added on 22/05: start
                                              ,
                    CASE
                       WHEN COUNT (
                               CASE
                                  WHEN     "FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG" IS NOT NULL
                                       AND UPPER ("FAST_TURN_AROUND_FLAG") LIKE
                                              '%MODIFIED MATERIALS%'
                                  THEN
                                     1
                               END) > 0
                       THEN
                          'Y'
                       ELSE
                          'N'
                    END
                       "MODIFIED_MATERIALS"
               -- Added on 22/05: end
               FROM "S_PRIMING_DATA_ADDITIONAL"
           GROUP BY "ROUTING_INFO", "SPK_SID", "QPV") "PK_ADDTL"
          JOIN "S_SCRIPT_PACKET_ALTS" "SSPA"
             ON "PK_ADDTL"."SPK_SID" = "SSPA"."SPK_SID"
          JOIN "STSPACKET" "SP" ON "PK_ADDTL"."SPK_SID" = "SP"."PACKETID"
   WITH READ ONLY;

Subject: Dropped permissions on the CAMS application server (production)

Please provide a Root Cause Analysis for the loss of permissions on the CAMS application server, SPCAMAP001, which resulted in CAMS users being unable to access CAMS Admin and Awarding. Sev 2 incident 595143 and incident 595490 resulted from the permissions being dropped.
The permissions were corrected on 13th July but then dropped out so that none of the CAMS users were able to access CAMS Admin on 16th July.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS asks for judgemental thresholds to be entered despite proper judgemental thresholds are set
ProblemDescription:
As per EPS code logic, there should be two qualifications - L3 Prncpl Lrnng Unit (sid: 1151) & Level 3 Ext Project (sid: 1161) for which, assessments must have first and sixth grades to be judgemental. So these values must be not null prior to proceed with the calculation.
With a code change with Incident 382637, a third qualification - Level 3 Certificate (sid: 1227) is added to this contributing qualification list for a different purpose ['L3_QUA_SIDs' in eps_reference_values table].

This is the probable reason to this problem. As for the 'Level 3 Certificate', user is not expected to enter a first and sixth grade as judgemental (so not null), but user provides a separate judgemental grades to second and fifth grades. Thus EPS does not receive not null value in first and sixth grades which brings the failure.

All the assessments under this qualification 'Level 3 Certificate' might have the same problem.
RootCause: Code change required.
Resolution: Solution deployed to production under RFC 32628 on 18th December 2018.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SPUKBSQ010 - System Database Integrity Check Performance
ProblemDescription: The last two successful system database integrity check jobs took 36 and 42 hours to complete. The last run failed with an unspecified error. The instance appears to be functioning OK, but this needs investigating.
Workaround: Disable DBCC CHECKDB as this is impacting the UKVI SSIS jobs for UKBA and PRDB Extract jobs
RootCause: DBCC CHECKDB operations are incurring RESOURCE_SEMAPHORE waits indicating that the SQL instance is short of RAM
Resolution:
As this server is only used to run SSIS jobs there is no need to run integrity checks against user databases as these are not in use, therefore disabled the user database checks.
The problem with system database checks was due to insufficient RAM being available while SSIS packages were running. So I have rescheduled the system database checks to run at a time when there are no scheduled jobs running. This means that the checks complete in less than 10 seconds.
