Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Excessive deadlocking/blocking on NHP (Results Determination) database
ProblemDescription:
There appears to be excessive blocking on the NHP database as well as confirmed high levels of deadlocks occurring. Addressing this issue should allow for a more performant application so that it is actually doing work rather than waiting for blocks and deadlocks to be released/unwound.

I can try and provide more information if required, eg database trace files with more details around the deadlock transactions.
RootCause: The old version of the database appeared to handle certain locks inefficiently.
Resolution: Upgrading the database to the latest version (on 23/3) has now resolved this. We used to get reports of anywhere from 200 to 500 "blockers" per day previously. Since the upgrade on the 23rd, our daily report shows a value of 0 every days since. Looking at the locks in the database confirms this. that there is now very little locking and blocking occurring.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Duplicate marks upload in EPS.
ProblemDescription: While ESM's eps upload processor processing BizTalk request to upload the marks in EPS, if another request comes from the BizTalk then ESM process both the request simultaniously. This results the same candidates/marks get upload in two files causing duplicate marks at EPS end. BizTalk sends request to ESM with 30 seconds of intervel. If ESM does not able to process the first request in 30 seconds due to huge data, BizTalk sends another request to ESM and it starts processig both the BizTalk's request.This causes both the files have some duplicate marks.
Workaround: Remove duplicate records from EPS Audit table to avoid any Business impact.
RootCause: The RCA Potentially similar root cause as PR 6350 which was BizTalk multi threading.
Resolution:
A change needs to be implemented in ESM end to process concurrent requests, received from BizTalk, sequentially within ESM so that duplicate data won’t get sent back to BizTalk. A row level lock needs to be acquired within database transaction to avoid multiple selects for same data. 


No further issues have been reported - closing PR as per last update

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Certain views within Hana RD have more than 2 billion entries
ProblemDescription:
Due to a Hana database limitation, joints created within the Hana RD database need to be reviewed, as the views contain two many entries:

• AT_CONVERSION_CANDIDATE   
• CA_CONVERSION_THRESHOLD_CAND        
• CA_REP_OPEN_REMARKS_STATUS_GV
RootCause:
The reports causing issues are those that derive their data content from Results Determination HANA calculation view models that in turn use the CANDIDATE_MEASURES table from the database. This table is the largest in the database (circa Dec 2018 there were approx. 900M rows in NHP). 

Although the database tables themselves do not contain more than 2B rows, the poorly designed calculation models join the tables in such a way as to create large intermediate data sets and in the case of the ‘Marks Drilldown’ report a set of more than 2B rows, hence the error. In the case of the other reports, the large intermediate data sets cause a significant reduction in performance and will in the future cause the reports to fail in the same way as the drilldown report.
Resolution: HANA model view for GCL report was re-designed so that input parameters were pushed down to the lowest level of the model, resulting in a much reduced data volume being queried from the database. Other report models will be modified in a similar as part of a future CR.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: User accounts as owners of availability group endpoints
ProblemDescription:
I have uncovered a potential risk whilst performing the initial healthchecks on VODS.

I ran SP_Blitz and it highlighted the fact that the owner of the availability group endpoint was a windows account and that the availability group could stop working if the account is ever deleted or disabled.

Upon further investigation it turns out that all of our production availability groups are set up like this I attach a list of HADR endpoints and their owner from production. It seems that by default the owner is the account that set up the availability group.

There is a way to change the owner but it should apparently be done during down-time.
RootCause: By default the owner is the account that set up the availability group.
Resolution: A test was carried out in a POC environment. It was shown that an availability group continues to function normally after the owner account is disabled or deleted. There will be no urgent requirement therefore for remedial action. We will instead change our processes to set the owner to the SQL Server service account, when creating the AG.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-8346 - Version change operations within IWAS generating incorrect Enrolment messages
ProblemDescription:
Using version change operation in IWAS invokes code which was previously seen in the bulk version change. When used, the version change messages are generated incorrectly. The normal Flow of Add, Delete, Add is present but the delete message is sent for the newly added test versions which leads enrolments being present for all test versions.

Issue present in 
Results management tab -> change candidate version
Results management tab -> Enter result
Test session tab -> Manage test session
Workaround: Versions are changed in the IWAS message table and message re-triggered.
RootCause:
It is possible to change the test versions in 4 places within IWAS:
 Candidate level: 
 Results management tab -> change candidate version - BROKEN - original BVC error present.
Incorrect version is being deleted

Results management tab -> Enter result - BROKEN - no message generated.
Discuss with Lydia to remove the version selection from this screen

Session level:
 Bulk Version change - WORKING
 Test session tab -> Manage test session - BROKEN - original BVC error present.

Using version change operation in "Change candidate version" IWAS invokes code which was previously seen in the bulk version change. When used, the version change messages are generated incorrectly. The normal Flow of Add, Delete, Add is present but the delete message is sent for the newly added test versions which leads enrolments being present for all test versions. This functionality is required as business sometimes need to make candidate level changes. 
 The broken functionality also appears in the "Manage test session" functionality but business have agreed they can make the session level changes using the bulk version change. 

Business have confirmed they do not use the "Enter Result" functionality to change version. However when trying to change the following behaviour was observed. It allowed the reading and listening version to change but not that writing task. When pressing submit the writing version reverts. No outbound messages were generated using this functionality but the reading and listening versions changed in the candidate table.
Resolution: Assigned to IELTS-8169, added to backlog.

eStore_productcatalog

eStore_transactionconfig
eStore_transactions
FinalTest_marketing

FinalTest_productcatalog

FinalTest_transactions
FronterProcessing
MSCS_Admin

SharePoint_AdminContent_4a7884e7-372a-456c-be34-ba00be523797
SharePoint_Config
WSS_Content_7c52e16f8ace4191b447c5b7ee4b6f1a
WSS_Content_d546e8aa5d3747d49ac1eca6008ae447
Workaround: Remove spjntsq039 from the domain and delete computer account in Active Directory. Restart and then re-add spjntsq039 back to the domain, and a final restart. Ensure spjntsq040 can see and synchronise with spjntsq039.
RootCause:
It appears that spjntsq040 was the active node, and spjntsq039 the passive.

Logs indicate that spjntsq039 had been having issues with the domain for quite some time.

When spjntsq040 attempted to fail over to spjntsq039 it could not due to spjntsq039 not having trust with the domain, causing the cluster & associated services to fail.

We have been unable to identify why spjntsq040 restarted, triggering the failover, hence the root cause being unidentified.
Resolution:
spjntsq039's trust with the domain has been restored and is now a functional member of the cluster and will be able to support services in the case of another fail over.

To note, this failure was a one time event and the cluster has been stable for quite some time before, and has been since. The resolution has been to ensure that there is redundancy and ensuring both servers are fully functional.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Weekly non-prod backups going into "hang" status.
ProblemDescription:

Workaround: Kill the unix processes and rerun the backup

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-8217 - IWAS BVC generating duplicate and incorrect messages when doing not all components
ProblemDescription:
IWAS is updating the candidate record twice because the versions for two components were changed together. The number of updates to candidate record will be equal to the number of components whose versions will be changed for the candidate.
That means, if the version gets changed for R,L,W together for a candidate, IWAS will update the candidate record three times and will send out 3 pairs of ADD and DLT messages.
In ideal scenario, IWAS should have done a single update in database for updating versions for all the components and should have sent only one pair of ADD/DLT messages.
Workaround: Manually correcting messages.
RootCause: When sending the messages, the version change tool was iterating through the whole set of versions assigned to the candidate causing duplicate messages.
Resolution: code change to ensure only the affected versions were primed

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: PDQ Results not pulling to certificate code in EPS - June (CCA2) 2018 series
ProblemDescription:
when amendment files are loaded on EPS for CCA certs, the certification entry is removed. This is an issue only with the amendment file and not with the initial entry file

Analysis has been done under Incident 603656. Please refer to email
RootCause:
Because the PDQ certs are auto created by EPS, the entry files only contains the unit code and not the cert code
 
2.       The entry process believes that EPS will auto create when the files are loaded on EPS
 
3.       When the initial entry file arrives on EPS, the cert codes are created without any issue
 
4.       When an amendment is submitted, because the file only contains units and not certs, there is a program on EPS that removes these certs entries. I  believe this program has been built thinking that a syllabus entry will always be in the entry file i.e. even PDQ cert codes will appear on the entry file along with unit codes
 
5.       However, EPS then proceeds to check if the candidate is eligible for CCA certs. When EPS does this check, it does the check based on candidate’s  unique id. The amendment entries that are in process of loading uses a temporary unique identifier, which is updated by the candidate’s original unique id at the end of processing. It is this temp id that is used during the check to identify if cand is eligible  for CCA cert.
 
6.       Because the temp id is not on EPS and the PDQ unit entry is against a different unique id, the check fails
 
7.       Since the check fails, the cert entry is not re-created and is lost

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Bacway - Availability Group Requirement
ProblemDescription:
In January 2018, the Bacway database was added to the availability group, BACPRDAG01 (see attached). However, this caused problems, so the database was then removed, but the availability group was left in place. 

This PR is to identify if the AG is required, or even supported by the Bacway application.
Workaround: The database has been taken out of the AG to allow the service to start successfully
RootCause: Confirmation received from the vendor that the application will attempt to put the database into single user mode every time it is started, when it checks if updates are required and then subsequently apply these updates. As this is by design and the fact that it is not possible to do this if the database is in an AG, then it is not possible to keep this database in an AG.
Resolution: Confirmation has been received that the application will not support the the database being in an Availability Group. As a consequence the database will remain on a standalone server (SPBACSQ001) and the AG and secondary server will be decommissioned.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Webex Call Disconnects
ProblemDescription: Users are finding that sometimes when they join webex conferences they are continually disconnecting from the call every few minutes.
RootCause: .VoIP Silence Suppression is enabled. What this does is it drops any RTP packets sent from a peer within a conference call when there is no audio detected/they are muted. After 2 minutes Webex is detecting this user as disconnected as they arent receiving any packets from said user which then auto disconnects that particular user.
Resolution: .VoIP Silence Suppression has been disabled on the Session Border Controllers. This has resolved the issue.

Workaround: Increase SQL RAM allocation
RootCause: RESOURCE_SEMAPHORE and THREADPOOL waits have been frequently occurring on this instance, triggered by shortage of memory. These would impact the ability for successful connections to the database.
Resolution: Although there is 16GB RAM installed on the server SQL was only configured to use 6GB, meaning that the OS was over allocated RAM while SQL was under allocated. Increased SQL RAM to 12GB and this has cleared the poison wait events.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Re Closed PR 2401 – CIE Direct saving entries with disallowed options
ProblemDescription:
This is with reference to the previously closed PR# 2401 (Incorrect Centre ID – School ID mapping at the backend while candidate creation) where some mappings that are not possible from the application end are being saved at the database. 
In the present incident, a candidate entry has been observed to have been submitted from the CIE Direct application where the following Assessment – Option mapping is seen to have been submitted by the centre user using the CIE Direct Finalentries application. The below snapshot depicts the fact that the first entry was proper and not having any Option Code. Later the amendment is shown to have been submitted for Assessment 1113 and BX option code.
Workaround: The affected entry should first be filtered off if the parent centre checks the entry CSV before approving. If the centre is not a sub-centre or the parent centre approved the entry with the incorrect mapping, then the entry needs to be corrected from EPS end so that the corrected value flows back to CIE Direct via EPS – CIE push process.
RootCause:
• We have replicated the same scenario in DEV environment. The error is due to the NULL teaching group code for an entry and not due to the option code(as mentioned in the PR). Attached screens are from the PR itself which describes the issue.
• From final entries application, user cannot insert null or incorrect teaching group code as it is validated against mapped teaching group code (populated from EPS). Moreover, wrong option code cannot be inserted for an entry as users are given options to choose from a list of valid option code.
• So, we are assuming that the error scenario can occur only if EPS pushes an entry with null teaching group code for Primary Checkpoint/Checkpoint qualifications or the mapping itself is incorrect (null teaching group code mapped with PC/C qualifications).

Looking at the above facts, it is seen that this is a data issue. So, to prevent this scenario EPS should validate and prevent pushing null teaching group code (with an entry or in the mapping table)for Checkpoint qualifications to Direct database.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-8632 - IWAS - Candidates Scores Missing
ProblemDescription: The marks coming in from MM are stored in a staging table as soon as they are received by IWAS. There is a separate batch job in IWAS that runs after every 30 mins and processes the marks stored in the staging table. This job processes the marks in batches with a batch size of 2500. For example, when the job runs, and if there are 7500 marks to be processed, IWAS should process the marks in 3 batches in one run. The logic to select first 2500 record for processing depends on the order in which they are received from MM. Its looks like there is as issue an IWAS because of which IWAS is not processing more 2500 records in one run. As a result, the backlog of marks increased rapidly as compared to the overall processing time of the job.
Workaround: Running the "External Result Processing job" from the UI clears the backlog.
RootCause: IWAS is not processing more 2500 records in one run. As a result, the backlog of marks increased rapidly as compared to the overall processing time of the job.
Resolution: A tactical fix (IELTS-8508) has been implemented under RFC 31341 however a strategic, permanent fix will be tackled under IELTS-8632

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BizTalk Server stopped processing all messages - Service Account issue
ProblemDescription: As per incident 607992 (P2) and  608775 - All BizTalk PROD services  got stuck. Integration support team was unable to restart any BizTalk services to get the services back online.
Workaround: No workaround that is the reason it's P2. The only way to solve the issue is to call Service desk and unlock the service accounts and then restart BizTalk services. The root cause of the account lock out need to be identified.
RootCause:
All Service accounts used by BizTalk PROD system got locked out. Service Account list 
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_SendHost
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_ReceiveH
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_ProcessH
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_Isolated
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_BusRules
UCLES\ BTS_ESB_PRD_SingleSi
Resolution:
As part of BizTalk 2016 migration project we are setting up brand new servers for BizTalk. 
While configuring BizTalk in those  new servers we were using Microsoft standard automated scripts. We have found a bug with suppressing the password in the standard script which was causing the service accounts to be locked out. 

The resolution of this PR is not to use the standard automated script. Instead use manual step to configure the new servers. This will make sure the account not to get locked again.

Workaround:
Currently we have enabled TLS 1.2 by default by creating up the SchUseStrongCrypto DWORD value in the following two registry keys to 1.
 
"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\.NETFramework\v4.0.30319" and "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Wow6432Node\Microsoft\.NETFramework\v4.0.30319"
RootCause: SF disabled the TLS 1.0 encryption protocol
Resolution:
Will do code changes within the service to enable the TLS.

https://btsservice.atlassian.net/browse/ASD-2215

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CD IELTS: TEST DAY ISSUE: Pilot TC NZ150 Sitting 3: Unable to end test for candidate 001219
ProblemDescription:
IDP Head Office report: -

We were unable to end test for candidate 001219 for Test date 5 July 18 from the NZ150 TSA. Status showed as Ending for around 8-9 minutes.

We manually PAUSED the entire test after around 10 minutes after which the ‘Ending’ status became ‘Ended’ for that candidate.

Severity:High

Details: 

Test Centre: Pilot NZ150

Test Taker: 001219

Test Section: Listening

Sitting: 3

Issue Description:

-          Test was Paused approx. 3mins into the test commencing for all candidates (‘Overview’ tab by clicking Pause button in the Test Controls against the AC Listening section)
-          Test was Resumed after a few minutes
-          Completed answering all 40 test questions for 001219 - Listening
-          Ended test for this individual test taker at approx. 20 minutes left from the “Candidates” tab. After a few minutes, the test still had not ended so we waited and took some photos (attached) of the TSA and CW. The status displayed as ‘Ending’
-          The test showed ‘Ending’ status for about 8-9 minutes after which we did not wait any longer.
-          Paused test again for all candidates using Pause button in Overview tab with the hope that it would End test of candidate 001219 at approx 11mins (as test still had not ended for test taker)
-          After pausing the test, we could now see that the Test Taker’s Listening test had Ended
-          Resumed test after a few seconds, but test had ended for Test Taker, and it did not resume for them.
-          Collected the logs as per procedure for CW and TSA and uploaded them to the FTP server on 5 July.
-          Snapshots attached.

Note: We have been able to end tests for other candidates on the same CW normally without any issue before and after this incident.


RM have investigated this issue and advise: -

We could not see any Connection problems logged in the CW for this test date.

But we could see that the times set in the TSA and CW were different. For example, the candidate login is logged at 19:23 in the TSA but 17:22 in the CW. 

We believe the CW time is 2 hours behind the TSA time. Considering that, we could see that the test was ended at 19:45:21 and this reached the CW at 19:55 (After considering the time difference).

When we checked the corresponding time in the logs of the CW, what we could see that, at 19:43 (Logged at 17:43 in the logs, but we considered the time difference again) , a particular audio file,ILI20246EVO-1-0-1.OGG, was requested by the test player. This same scenario happened for another audio file,ILI30213EVO-0-0-1.OGG, at 19:50.

One possible scenario we can think of is that, due to these requests, the CW/test froze and did not receive the test end message from the TSA. After a while, that is just under 10 minutes, the CW recovered and responded to the test end message.

Could you please have a look into this from the test player end and let us know if there is anything odd in these requests ?
RootCause: code Issue
Resolution: Code revised and deployed into Production, under RFC 32698

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SoR Comparison Report not Updating
ProblemDescription:
In the scenario where the SoR already exists and if the candidate marks are revised in HANA (due to a tariff application for instance), the SoR comparison report's HANA section data should be updated instantly thereby showcasing a difference between the XML & HANA sections of the report. 
However, in this scenario, the HANA section data is not updating instantly and it happens only when the new XML is generated during result release.

As per the business this issue was identified during CR 9000428 UAT but the issue still exists.
Workaround: There is no workaround. However the report reconciles when the results are manually released after SoR XML is generated.
RootCause:
The SOR comparison report is a XML driven report. 
As per the current design, the XML & HANA sections of the report are updated only when the XML has been generated. 
This means that if in HANA the marks are revised, due to a tariff application, the SOR comparison report will not be updated at real time, but only when the XML is generated.
Resolution: To have the HANA section of the report updated real-time, additional functionality needs to be incorporated. This would need a business case to be raised.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Corrupt Marks Manager TDM zips files created in case of BizTalk internal failure.
ProblemDescription: Corrupt TDM zip files got created on 1st September 2018. There was no issue with the content of the TDM received from ATP.The corrupt TDM zip file caused issue in IDP and BC Marks Managers and prevented the processing of TDM files that were generated after that. This led to auto marking failure in Marks Manager due to Test materials unavailability.
Workaround: The corrupt files are removed by the partners in their system and TDM are republished to Marks manager.After TDM publish completion candidate response are replayed to Marks manager.
RootCause: During SSO unavailability or incorrect content of the TDM request, the Test Day Materials process in BizTalk is not generating a failure and aborting the process.Instead the process is creating an incorrect zip file and sending to Marks Manager.
Resolution:
The Test Day materials process need to be changed to abort processing in case of SSO failure or incorrect content and return negative ackowlegment to LIBS/ATP specifying that the publishing has failed. This will ensure that incorrect and corrupt files are not generated and sent to Marks Manager causing failure at Partner end.This requires a code change in BizTalk.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica CE - SSRS VM Admin Password
ProblemDescription:
The generic, local administrator account for SPAZMETSQ still has the same password from the time it was initially created. This password has been widely shared and is common knowledge to a number of teams. It's  still regularly used. By using a generic account, there is no traceability of changes made and having the old password so widely shared represents a security risk. The account has both local administrator and SQL administrator privileges on SPAZMETSQ.

This is already recorded in JIRA - MET-6970.
RootCause: Create and apply account with appropriate privileges
Resolution:
In order to change the password of the SSRS VM, we can take one of two approaches:

1. Create a generic account with restricted privileges. All those who currently use the local admin account would now use this and we can change the password the admin account.

2. Identify who should have access to the SSRS VM and ensure they each have an Active Directory account. Each individual would log onto the SSRS VM using their own AD account.

Once one of these options is chosen, we can implement and then lock down the admin account.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Data Services BODS job - regular index maintenance
ProblemDescription: BODS jobs slow down over time. This is because the index becomes more and more fragmented as inserts/updates and deletes are performed against the table.
RootCause: Very regular inserts/updates and deletes on a table will cause an index to get fragmented. This is normal databases behavior. What was identified here is that the index got so fragmented (and so big), that it consumed all the database cache and cause performance issues.
Resolution: The resolution is to rebuild the index at regular intervals. This will get rid of the fragmentation and keep the index nice and small. An online index rebuild has been scheduled to run once a week.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Mobile phone users can't authenticate with WiFi via certificate
ProblemDescription:
Mobile phone users have to use their Active Directory credentials to connect to the CA-Corporate WiFi network.  When a user's password is changed, often the mobile phone locks the users account out as it has to be updated manually, this often results in wasted time and unnecessary calls to the service desk.

Users with corporate mobile phones now have certificates generated for their phones by Airwatch and issued by our internal certificate authority (CAIssuer01,02,03 or 04).

Currently Cisco ISE that protects access to the WiFi network doesn't have suitable configuration to allow a user to connect using the certificate.
Workaround: Use a username and password to connect to the network and manually change these when the Active Directory password change is enforced.
RootCause: Configuration is not present in Cisco ISE to validate the mobile phone's certificate.  The process of adding this configuration is complex and there isn't sufficient in-house knowledge to progress.
Resolution: Airwatch is being replaced by another product called Intune. The project is already underway and is near completion.

Subject: ESM Remark Service is creating duplicate remark requests when BizTalk is mulithreaded.
ProblemDescription: When BizTalk is re-started after downtime parallel process are started up instantaneously.  If there are ESM Remarks outstanding, each BizTalk thread will pick these up and both threads are processed by ESM.  This results in duplicate data being created in ESM.
Workaround: When BizTalk is re-started after downtime BizTalk will introduce a delay when starting parallel threads.
RootCause:
Problem statement : 
On Saturday 22/09/18, all remark requests which were uploaded through ESM were duplicated.
At around 11.30am a CSV of 721 requests was uploaded. These did not appear on RM until about 4pm and the entire file was duplicated (1442).

Root cause:  

RCA for delay in syncing RM: Due to RFC 31187 BizTalk environment was completely shut down 2 times. Roughly BizTalk environment was brought down at 2018-09-22 10:01:35.410 and re-enabled at 2018-09-22 15:35:07.423
Hence even though CSV uploaded in ESM around 11.30am , but the Remark requests reached RM reached around 4 PM. 

RCA for duplicate in RM: 
Once the  BizTalk environment was brought online, within a few millisecond interval 2 parallel BizTalk processes polled ESM for pending Remark requests in order to sync RM. Both the parallel threads of ESM polling received identical response (721 remark requests) from ESM Remark service. As BizTalk process received 721 remark requests in 2 separate threads from ESM, it send RM the same 721 remarks twice. Ideally ESM Remark service should not return same data in the 2 parallel threads.
Resolution:
Change ESM to process BizTalk mulit-threading without creating duplicate Remark Requests in ESM.

On discussion with the business and the Integration team it has been agreed that this PR can be closed. Single threaded BizTalk has coped with 15,000 records in summer series 2017with no issues.  Any more than 6,000 records would be exceptional.  Summer 2016 processing volumes was exceptional and is unlikely to be repeated.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Problem in producing the statement of result for the candidate.
ProblemDescription:
This is a copy of previous PR 1784 which was closed incorrectly.

A candidate is entered for a assessment and obtained a grade for a older session . The same candidate is re-entered for the same assessment but  for a current session and obtained a grade. The candidate is also appeared for other IGCSEs and ICE award. But when the grade is calculating, the assessment  grade for the current session is not used to calculate their ICE award (older grade would have been used to calculate the ICE award).     For example: candidate IN511/2 entered for 0500 English in Nov 2013 and obtained C grade. For June 2014, the same candidate repeated 0500 English using candidate number 14 and obtained A* grade.They also appeared for other IGCSEs and also entered for the ICE award.For 0500 English, grade C (but not A*) would have been used to calculate ICE award.    The candidate should get a separate IGCSE statement of result (SOR) for the assessment (0500 English). However this is not producing any data and unable to print this SOR.
Workaround: DELETE FROM candidate_assessment_parts        WHERE ses_sid = <enter session>          AND can_unique_identifier in ('enter can_unique_identifier ) ;
RootCause: Wrong session - qualification used to create grade.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica/CLMS: Audio not resuming while launching from CLMS site
ProblemDescription:
For some Metrica tests which are launched from CLMS site.There are multiple issues with audio failures and test navigation. However when the same test are directly launched from Metrica site,no such issues could be replicated.

Example:-
Example:
Affected Course: Cambridge English Empower C1 Advanced ---> Unit 2 Progress Test
Assessment URL: https://www.cambridgelms.org/main/p/en/class/28950304/launch_assessment/419295/5662
Class code: Cr9ff8

Login: agonzalezortega1
Password: LELS54321

This is not an issue with the Flash settings.

We have managed to make the audio resume by following the below steps:

Step 1 - Open the URL for the assessment so it opens in a popup window
Step 2 - Confirm that the audio hasn't resumed
Step 3 - Press F12
Step 4 - In the DevTools popup window select Console
Step 5 - Click back to the original popup window with the test
Step 6 - Press F5 to refresh the page
Step 7 - The test should now say "Paused in debugger" in a yellow box
Step 8 - Go back to the DevTools popup, it should now be on the Sources tab
Step 9 - Check to see if line 2968 is highlighted for you as well
Step 10 - In the test window, press F8 and see if the audio resumes.
Workaround:
1) Open Google chrome.
2) Open chrome://flags/#autoplay-policy
3) Setting No user gesture is required
4) Relaunch Chrome
RootCause: We think this might be happening because of the default 'Autoplay' behavior of chrome which is why its not replicable for other browsers
Resolution:
This can be avoided using a ’muted’ property inside the video tag for jplayer. However this could further be investigated for better workarounds.

MET-6177 that will address the issue raised against PR6375/MET-8158 schedule for Metrica release v19.

MET-8158 now in UAT and is scheduled for v19.1 - RFC32887

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: RGT report / EPS data
ProblemDescription: Data on RGT is not matching data on EPS. The details can be found in the incident AH.
Workaround: None
RootCause:
Issue is because EPS uses below view to puch component level marks eres_cand_com_measures.
This view makes call to mark_scaling_factors_query.assessor_mark to get the assessor scaled mark. When it makes a call to the function, it passes hard coded ME id = 1. This is not correct and is causing issue. You can verify this by using below query. First call is using 1 and second one '01'. in WRM we have '01' and thus first call returns incorrect data.

The solution will be not to change the value to 01 but use the value that is on WRM.
Also, check if this is an issue in other areas on EPS


SELECT mark_scaling_factors_query.assessor_mark(e1.ses_sid
                                               ,e1.ass_code
                                               ,e1.asv_ver_no
                                               ,e1.com_id
                                               ,1
                                               ,e1.cnu_id
                                               ,e1.cand_no)
      ,mark_scaling_factors_query.assessor_mark(e1.ses_sid
                                               ,e1.ass_code
                                               ,e1.asv_ver_no
                                               ,e1.com_id
                                               ,'01'
                                               ,e1.cnu_id
                                               ,e1.cand_no)
FROM   eres_cand_com_measures e1
-- this view generates incorrect assessor level scaled mark because function called has issues as
-- the mark element passed is not matched with mark element on WRM
WHERE  e1.ses_sid = 3227
AND    e1.cnu_id = '40645'
AND    e1.cand_no = 5003
AND    e1.ass_code = 'J587'
AND    e1.com_id = '03';
Resolution: View updated under RFC 34403

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SSIS package in SSISDB Catalogue fail following Availability Group Failover
ProblemDescription:
On a SQL Server 2016 Availability Group (ODSPP2AG01), with SSIS installed and the SSIS Catalogue database added to the AG, packages hosted in the catalogue are failing following an AG failover, with the above error message.

Hosting SSISDB in an availability group with automatic failover is supposed to be supported from SQL Server 2016 onwards. At this time, it is not established whether this is a bug or a failure to install and configure properly or whether it is only affecting ODSPP2AG01 or other SSIS catalogues hosted in AGs.
Workaround:
The following script synchronises the Database Master Key with the Service Master Key of the new primary instance, following a failover.

USE SSISDB　　　　　　 
OPEN master Key decryption by password = '*****' -- Password used when creating SSISDB
ALTER Master Key ADD encryption by Service Master Key
RootCause: Sync needed between Database and Service Master Keys
Resolution: Script created

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: VODS & ODS_CDM - ECC PersonDetails not sent correctly
ProblemDescription:
BODS jobs should send updates to both ODS_CDM and VODS

VODS_WH.ECC.WH_PersonDetail.stgPersonDetailUid=0703094639 has GivenName="FIORELA ...". ODS_CDM.PersonDetail.PersonDetailECCUid=0703094639 has GivenName="FIORELLA ..."

1)
ODS_CDM has a meta_src_Updated value of '2018-09-26 00:00:37.0000000' - this is the apparent modified date of the current record in ECC
VODS has a whenReceivedFromECC value of '2018-09-16 00:00:00.0000000' - this is the apparent modified date of the current record in ECC, and WH_CreatedDate = '2018-09-16 03:00:13.0000000' - when the candidate record was FIRST created in VODS, suggesting VODS did not get updated on 26/09/2018 with ODS_CDM

2)
When SAP was queried directly 0703094639, was created and modified several days before '2018-09-16 00:00:00.0000000' suggesting BODS did not send to ODS_CDM or VODS when it should have done.


Refer to attached emails for more detail.
Workaround: N/A
RootCause:
The FM takes a single date input parameter which is considered used to query numerous ECC tables in order to return the Candidate Business Partner (BP) and the associated person details. 
The FM module input parameter is a date field, this date is considered as Key Assessment Date or Booking date, while querying (HRPAD506) and uses this information to retrieve the associated BP information from BUT000.
Resolution:
Please refere to RCA attached 
1. Remove the existing logic to retrieve person details based on input date = KAD /Booking date 
2. Introduce additional logic to return the person details information (from ECC table BUT000) based on creation date CRDAT or change date CHDAT (if change date exists).
a. There will always be a value for BUT000-CRDAT, however BUT000-CHDAT may or may not be populated. If BUT000-CHDAT is populated, CHDAT takes precedence over CRDAT
3. One off backfill activity required while deployment to production.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS invoicing - fees problem
ProblemDescription:
Please refer to incident for more details and screen shots.
In short, the issue is that for some centres, EPS is charging incorrect fees.
Example attached as email on the PR
As you can see, user is expecting £73 to be charged instead of £52.
Workaround: None. User needs to handle this themselves
RootCause:
To identify the amount EPS needs to charge, EPS follows below:
1.       Identifies the product range through which centre is taking the syllabus
2.       Identifies the payer contact of the product range 
3.       Then finds out the Accounting Region of the contact
4.       In this case (reported on incident), the Accounting Region is Jordan
5.       As per Financial Regions screen shot (refer to email), Jordan is part of “Int Sterling Fee Sheet C”
6. “Int Sterling Fee Sheet C” is set up to £52
6.       Hence, value of 52 is picked on the invoice

As per user, Fee should be charged for the country where the exam takes place. The test centre and not the accounting centre is the fee sheet that needs to be used. In the example on Incident, although Jordan are paying, the exam was taken in the UAE.  Therefore, the correct fee should have been £73.

So, the cause of the issue is that EPS is charging as per a logic that user's don't agree

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IBM Health Check - EPS System
ProblemDescription:
IBM carried out a health check against our EPS AIX systems and identified the following issue.

Although not represented clearly above, all of the hdisks on prd-vios1 are configured with 4x paths, all routed via fscsi2 / fcs2.
Disks attached to prd-vios2 are configured with 8x paths - 4x via each of fscsi0 and fscsi2.

Although 4x paths is considered quite adequate for most scenarios, best practice dictates single points of failure should be avoided.
It seems likely there should have been paths provided via another interface to prd-vios1.

Please have SAN mapping and zoning checked and/or updated.
Review the MPIO best practice document at www.ibm.com/developerworks/aix/library/au-aix-mpio/index.html. You may want to reduce the total number of paths for every disk to 4x (via 2x different interfaces).

This issue is not effecting current performance or functionality however following the EPS upgrade project wrap up meeting it was decided that this should be recorded via a problem record.
Workaround: N/A
RootCause: This is a duplicate of Problem 5435
Resolution: This is a duplicate of Problem 5435

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: McAfee Host Intrusion Prevention memory leak when patching SQL Servers
ProblemDescription:
It appears we have a conflict with the Host Intrusion Prevention service when we’re applying SQL Server service packs. I was patching a couple of servers in the QA1 environment on Monday night and both started off well enough, but eventually hung completely. When looking at task manager, I could see that the HIIS service was consuming all the memory on both servers. I had to cancel the installation eventually, but unfortunately one of the servers is now corrupted and will need to be rebuilt. 

Recently, we’ve come across a number of servers with corrupt installations in the QA1 environment, and all are exhibiting the same errors that I see on the recently broken installation. 

I’ve done a little research and can see that there does appear to be a known issue with a memory leak with HIIS and “unsupported” versions of SQL. Unsupported by McAfee, that is:

https://kc.mcafee.com/corporate/index?page=content&id=KB81968

I was installing SQL Server 2016 SP2, which apparently isn’t supported according to this somewhat dated link:

https://kc.mcafee.com/corporate/index?page=content&id=KB65845

The first link suggests a workaround of disabling HIIS on the SQL Server service while patching. Is this feasible? I assume it will require someone from Security to disable.

So far, we’ve only seen corrupted installation in the QA1 environment.
Workaround: Raise a service request for Security team to remove HIP on any server we need to update.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: intermittent IPC transfer errors on SAN31c
ProblemDescription:
A port on bottom controller of SAN31C is operating at the incorrect speed of 4Gbps, instead of the recommended 8Gbps that we use across the other ports.

The top controller of SAN31C then experienced an unexpected reboot and after raising with Dell (SR#974673656) they believe the speed mismatch was the cause of this.

The bottom controller of SAN31C is getting intermittent IPC errors 
So far we have (in no particular order): 
• re-seated various fibres
• replaced various fibres
• fibre inspection for all non-structured fibre utilised for bottom controller ports 1 and 3
• performed end-to-end attenuation tests on bottom controller ports 1 and 3 which proved the run of fabric, including the structured, is good
• both controllers have been swapped with warranty replacements 
• firmware updates (this caused the IPC errors to move from top controller to the bottom controller)
• BMC was misconfigured on one controller (one had a 169.254.x.x address and the other had 192.168.x.x) I rectified this which allowed the SAN to pass a remote health check performed by Dell, but didn’t resolve the IPC errors. GW is still set to 0.0.0.0 for BMC on both controllers as per Dells recommendation (and convention based on our equivalent SANs)

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Direct Access
ProblemDescription:
To provide a bit of extra context…..

• The Standard Change that triggered this incident has been implemented hundreds of times since DirectAccess was deployed in around 2014.  It has never gone wrong or had any undesirable impact.  It is very low risk.
• We have no reason to believe the engineer made an error during the change.  From experience, I believe he could have clicked all the wrong buttons but still not caused the result we have experienced.
• The cause is very likely to be a software bug.
• With Microsoft’s help we will establish root cause.  We will also identify architectural options to reduce the impact of issues in future, and explore options for monitoring to identify such an issue faster in future.

The technical detail of what happened…

• In implementing the Standard Change, a simple DNS entry was added to the DirectAccess configuration.  Copy/paste activity.  When the engineer clicks “apply”, DirectAccess automatically applies that setting directly in to two “Group Policies”  in AD.  That change then replicates around all of the Domain Controllers, and client computers (laptops in this case) check in for updates/changes every 4 hours.
• On this occasion, for some reason DirectAccess literally emptied one of the two key policies.  All content was removed from it - automatically.  This isn’t something the engineer will have been able to see.  Through the day this empty policy replicated around the Domain Controllers, and clients downloaded the empty policy.  At that moment, the laptops with the new policies lose any knowledge of DirectAccess.
• We fixed the issue by restoring the original policy from a backup

Current status
• Any laptops that received the “empty” policy who DO connect to a Cambridge Assessment network (Triangle, Coventry, internationals) will automatically receive the policy.  DirectAccess will automatically work when they restart and connect from home/away.
• Any laptops that received the “empty” policy who DO NOT connect to a CA network (home workers) sadly will not automatically get the policy and will not be able to connect to DirectAccess.  Fixing this will not be trivial - somehow we have to get a complex policy applied to a computer we have zero access to
Workaround:
Service Desk instructions

• Log incident with service desk
• Connect to remote computer via GoToAssist
• Check OS
• Windows 7
o Following existing instructions to install and connect via the Cisco AnyConnect SSL VPN
o Right click the “Command Prompt” result and click “Run as Administrator”
o Log in as .\master with the relevant password
o Type the following command and press Enter
 gpupdate /force
o Type the following command and press Enter
 wf.msc
o The Windows Firewall MMC will automatically open
o Browse to Connection Security Rules on the left panel
o DirectAccess policies are in place if you see 4 policies as per below screenshot:
 
o Restart the computer
o DirectAccess should automatically connect after the restart.  If it doesn’t, a simple test is to check if Direct Access is in the list of wireless networks, as per the screenshot below.  If it isn’t listed, you may need to re-do the process above, or escalate to EUS 2nd Line Team.
  

• Windows 10
o Get screenshot of computer name
o Send the computer name to John Dobson or Dan Petty or Kenson Tjinakiet - whoever is responding immediately via Skype.  Only send to one person!
o The EUS engineer will send the Service Desk Analyst a text file
o Email offline domain join file to any email account available on the remote computer
o Download the offline domain join file to c:\temp
o Click start, type “cmd” to search for the Command Prompt
o Right click the “Command Prompt” result and click “Run as Administrator”
o Log in as .\master with the relevant password
o Type the following command and press Enter
 cd \temp
o Type the following command and press Enter
 djoin /requestodj /loadfile C:\offlinedomainjoin.txt /windowspath %windir% /localos
o Once complete, restart the computer.  DirectAccess should automatically connect.
o Ask the customer to try and access Insite (http://insite.ucles.org.uk)


EUS 2nd Line / Infra Apps Instructions

• RDP to the DirectAccess server (spinfap053)
• Open a command prompt
• Prepare the following command in a text file FIRST so you can easily & safely copy/paste into the command prompt.
o Replace the computer name in yellow below with the user’s computer name.  Double check the computer name is typed properly!  It’s a one-way journey.
o djoin.exe /provision /domain ucles.internal /machine computername /savefile c:\temp\OfflineDomainJoincomputername.txt /policynames "DirectAccess Client Settings" /policypaths "\\ucles.internal\SYSVOL\ucles.internal\Policies\{CC4528F0-D528-4084-BF78-5D24E6398B0D}\Machine\Registry.pol" /certtemplate Machine /reuse
• Email the prepared file from c:\temp to the Service Desk Analyst
RootCause: GPO file removed by replication
Resolution:
New procedure to make sure the GPO file is not removed.
New system is also being designed to replace this.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Full database Backups on ESMPRDAG01 failing due to drivespace.
ProblemDescription:
The full database backup on ESMPRDAG01\SQL01 usually takes 5 - 6 hours. There is just enough room for 2 backups on the backup drive, so it is imperative that the previous days backup is deleted following the successful completion of the current backup. Currently the backup job deletes any files older than 22 hours.

Around once a week the job is, for some reason taking in excess of 12 hours. Then the next day it returns to 5-6 hours. meaning that when the job finishes the previous days backup files are less than 22 hours old. They will not be deleted and, on the third day the job will fail, as there is no space for the new backup files. This has been mitigated by incident management so fa, but could potentially pose a threat to recoverability.
Workaround: currently deleting files under incidents. Could also potentially reduce the threshold for deletion temporarily.
RootCause: The wide variation of times taken for the backups to complete.
Resolution: Reduced the cleanup time of old backup files from 24 hours to 12 hours. This has prevented any further occurrences of the issue and there is no point in looking into it further since all backups will eventually be taken directly by NetBackup, with no need for locally stored backup files.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Unable to save '&' symbol correctly in Database from XML
ProblemDescription:
There is an issue in CEO in which the Ampersand(&) symbol is getting saved properly in database. Here the user was getting error while setting up profile in preparation centre portal. The error was due to the Address_Line_1 which contains '&' in it. When the user set up their profile and saves it a back up of user details is saved CentreData.User_Setup_Audit_History table. The Address Line 1 is 'Agiou Konstantinou & Elenis  49, Kokkinos Mylos, A'. The data is pulled from CentreData.Contact table of CentreAssessmentManager database and is updated in the CentreData.User_Setup_Audit_History table. In the xml the the Address_Line_1 comes as 'Agiou Konstantinou & Elenis  49, Kokkinos Mylos, A'. This Adress_Line_1 gets updated as it is in database and no conversion of & to & happens.
Workaround: Manually updating the affected field from back end
RootCause: This is a PRDB issue, not SAP.
Resolution: Solution to the problem will be handled under PRDB problem record 5680

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Possible for results removed from ResultsService without enduser being notified by appropriate error
ProblemDescription:
If a candidate has a positive result and has their results released, then the RO downloads those results, only for Cambridge English to realise a mistake has been made and mark that candidate as Absent or Refunded for at least one component (Reading/Writing/Listening/Speaking), the RO is not alerted to this change.

What happens is that the existing downloaded file is not changed, as this is a file on the RO’s machine and we have no reach there. The Download history is modified to remove that candidate, but no new result is added for them (as we don’t report absent or refunded candidates). This means that the RO doesn’t know that their existing downloaded file is now out of date, as there are no new downloads.

As a result of this its possible that a download with a count of 0 candidates could appear on download dashboard. There is no specific error message to cater for this.
RootCause: This has been identified as functionality that was not envisgaed from the start so it has been added to the JIRA backlog
Resolution:
Converted to JIRA 
RES-1539

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cosmos moving data files before candidate information has been written
ProblemDescription:
EPS Portal writes data files to \\ucles.external\ResultsOnlineprd$\XmlDumpDirectory. 
Cosmos monitors this folder and after detecting a file in there picks it up and moves it to \\prtsysinputprd\jobs\jobID where Cosmos reads the data from the file and processes the job.

Cosmos hits a 'Processing Error' when it gets to the 'Start parsing XML' stage and then stops processing. Upon checking the file we found that there is no centre or candidate information.

The reason for this is that Cosmos is moving the files before EPSp has finished writing the data. This error happened previously which is when we discovered the root cause when consulting with Canon. 

It was decided that a wait time would be set in Cosmos so that there was a delay between Cosmos noticing a new file in \\ucles.external\ResultsOnlineprd$\XmlDumpDirectory and it moving the file to the new jobs folder. This was set to 2 seconds and carried out on CR# 31541. Until now we have not had a recurrence of this error since making those changes.
RootCause: Cosmos is moving data files from \\ucles.external\ResultsOnlineprd$\XmlDumpDirectory to \\prtsysinputprd\jobs\jobID too quickly - before EPSp has finished writing data to the file.
Resolution: Code change to stop blank xml being created - deployed to PRD on RFC #35432

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: FI error due to > 999 items, blocked billing
ProblemDescription: The error in billing is caused due to maximum number of items in Fi reached.This issue is known to occur when Creating/Releasing Billing Document via VF01 or VF02 or VFX3. Fi documents are limited to 999 line items only whereas when an SD billing document is released to accounting, the SD-FI interface creates one line for every condition of every item of the billing document. So the limit of 999 FI lines can be reached even if the SD billing document has less than 999 items and it occurs when the Document is a Cash Sales Document.
Workaround: To create new Invoice via VF01 with selection list after cancelling the existing invoice.
RootCause: The error in billing is caused due to maximum number of items in Fi reached.
Resolution: Per attached email - agreement from Finance to log this as a CR - the solution will require a design change - refer to CR9000796.

Subject: Consider removing orphaned group policy containers from Active Directory
ProblemDescription: The policy-setting information for a GPO is stored in the following locations: •Group Policy container •Group Policy template The Group Policy container (GPC) is an Active Directory container that contains GPO properties, such as version information, GPO status, and other component settings, under the CN=Policies,CN=System,DC=… container, which is replicated via AD replication. The Orphaned GPCs test queries each domain in the forest for orphaned group policy containers. When a GPO is deleted, both its Active Directory objects and GPT folder should be deleted. However, if user does not have a sufficient permissions in active directory, the deletion might fail for the entire GPC container. They should be removed as part of a cleanup task.
RootCause: Probable initial replication failures.
Resolution: Orphaned folders deleted. Now doing this task as part of BAU duties.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Disable SMB1 Protocol To Protect Your Network From Security Risks Such As Man-In-The-Middle-Attack
ProblemDescription:
SMB1 isn’t safe and should be disabled to provide key protections offered by later SMB versions.

When you use SMB1, you lose key protections offered by later SMB protocol versions:
  • Pre-authentication Integrity (SMB 3.1.1+). Protects against security downgrade attacks.
  • Secure Dialect Negotiation (SMB 3.0, 3.02). Protects against security downgrade attacks.
  • Encryption (SMB 3.0+). Prevents inspection of data on the wire, MiTM attacks. In SMB 3.1.1 encryption performance is even better than signing!
  • Insecure guest auth blocking (SMB 3.0+ on Windows 10+) . Protects against MiTM attacks.
  • Better message signing (SMB 2.02+). HMAC SHA-256 replaces MD5 as the hashing algorithm in SMB 2.02, SMB 2.1 and AES-CMAC replaces that in SMB 3.0+. Signing performance increases in SMB2 and 3.
No matter how you secure all these things, if your clients use SMB1, then a man-in-the-middle can tell your client to ignore all the above and share all its secrets unless you required encryption on that share to prevent SMB1 in the first place.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Review accounts that never had a password set
ProblemDescription:
User accounts that have never had a password set are a significant security risk. This status can be reported if an account has been created without a password or if the Change password at next logon flag has been set.

User accounts can be flagged as never had a password set under three conditions:
  • Where an account has been created but a password has not been assigned.
  • Where an account has been created and the administrator has assigned a password but selected the option to change password at next logon.
  • Where the administrator has selected the option to require a user to change their password at the next logon as part of managing that user’s account, such as after a password reset.
This condition is detected by querying the user accounts and finding out instances where the value for passwordLastSet is zero.
You should regularly scan for and identify accounts where passwords have not been set. Check your user account provisioning processes and ensure that there is no significant gap between provisioning a new user account and that account having its password changed.
RootCause:
User accounts that have never had a password set are a significant security risk. This status can be reported if an account has been created without a password or if the Change password at next logon flag has been set.

User accounts can be flagged as never had a password set under three conditions:
Where an account has been created but a password has not been assigned.
Where an account has been created and the administrator has assigned a password but selected the option to change password at next logon.
Where the administrator has selected the option to require a user to change their password at the next logon as part of managing that user’s account, such as after a password reset.
This condition is detected by querying the user accounts and finding out instances where the value for passwordLastSet is zero.
You should regularly scan for and identify accounts where passwords have not been set. Check your user account provisioning processes and ensure that there is no significant gap between provisioning a new user account and that account having its password changed.
Resolution:
Password not required flag cleared

used powershell code to identify problem accounts
get-aduser -filter "useraccountcontrol -band 32" -properties useraccountcontrol 

Manually edited the 6 accounts returned by script.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Update on Stuck candidate 19-11-2018
ProblemDescription:
After completing the process of first Candidate INSERT feed, if there is any component version change against the same candidate then again candidate INSERT feed processed along updated version. Now here as the first one is not deleted before sending the second INSERT, candidate feed become stuck on RM end.
 
Steps:
1.    1. Send candidate INSERT feed along candidate details and candidate enrollment or just candidate enrollment
2.       2. Change the component version for the same candidate.
3.       3. A new INSERT candidate feed will be processed with updated version.
Workaround: First we need to send DELETE candidate feed to clear the first INSERT feed and then again send DELETE feed to clear SECOND INSERT candidate feed. Once it complete then finally send INSERT candidate feed again.
RootCause: As per the current design, data feed is not processed in real time; there is some time lag in data transfer between source to the destination application. If anything changes between the previous changes have through to the destination application (C+/MM), this issue is happening. This is the reason the candidate is not present with the current version in Connect+.
Resolution: IELTS-11161 created and added t the backlog.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: QPPD Interface to RM Assessor:  change month numeral system
ProblemDescription: In RM, the Series (or Sessions) dropdown does not follow the month sequence.
Workaround: n/a
RootCause: The Session month originates in the QP Product Data (QPPD) Interface to RM Scoris.  The issue is because the interface uses different numeral system in each of the software (i.e. SAP uses decimal, LIBS uses binary, and ESM uses hexadecimal), and it is conveyed into RM with different values, which do not mean the same to RM.
Resolution:
To convey from BT to RM the month field in binary numeral system, i. e.:

January – 1
February- 2 
March – 3
April -4 
May -5
June- 6
July- 7
August – 8
September -9
October – A
November –B
December – C

This issue was originally raised on SAP CR 9000591.  After some analysis, it was determined that the fix should be done in BizTalk. The code change was deployed to Production as part of the SAP CB adoption project via RFC 35040.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Centre number check digit missing
ProblemDescription:
The CAMS centre invoice extract failed because the check digit was missing.

We believe :

Whenever, a new centre is added in CAMS the backend code logic calculates the checksum(checkdigit) of the centre and updates the same in the CAMS backend table. The User can not enter the values for the checkdigit when entering the new centre.

This calculation of the checkdigit might have been introduced in CAMS to check the validity/authenticity of the centerno.(entered by the user).

We think that the introduction of alphanumeric centres led to removal of this function. So, whenever a new centre is added  the checkdigit value remains blank.
RootCause: The check digit calculation has been disabled for new centres.
Resolution: Update code to reinstate the check digit.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Importing erroneous EDI Test entry file doesn't create entry in CAMS but fed entries to Interchange
ProblemDescription:
Details:  Whenever an EDI file related to a schema (TECA, TECE) is imported in CAMS the file is validated line by line in GTI. The file is divided in different groups like for TECA- A1, A3, A5, A7, and A9 and for TECE – E1, E3, E5, E7, and E9. While importing files validations are performed on different groups. Regarding this incident few EDI files where the series information was not in the proper format. While importing these files error appears (attached below) but after closing the error import was getting completed in CAMS but no records was getting created n CAMS main tables (forms_NQF1Form, forms_NQF1Detail, AssessHeaderValid, AssessDetailValid) as the file was erroneous but the record was getting created in Interchange Staging tables (forms_NQF1Form_Staging, forms_NQF1Detail_Staging) from there the records went into the Interchange Entry tables through EDI sync job.
Technical Details: Please see the below screenshot displaying the format of session details mentioned in the affected EDI files was 9I18 where 9I signifies series and 18 signifies year. But looking the validation query there is no series specified with 9I. This is where the validation was failing but records were being fed into Interchange tables.
Workaround: We modified the session details from 9I18 to 1C19 as this was related to January 2019 session. Later, importing the modified EDI file entries got successfully created in CAMS and Interchange too.
RootCause: While importing EDI files error appears and after closing the error import was getting completed in CAMS but no records was getting created n CAMS main tables (forms_NQF1Form, forms_NQF1Detail, AssessHeaderValid, AssessDetailValid) as the file was erroneous. This was because few EDI files where the series information was not in the proper format.
Resolution: Fix the Stored Proc logic/Delphi Code

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS tests failing to reach IWAS. Failing at ATC REST Layer.
ProblemDescription:
ATC requests fail to reach IWAS due to an issue with the REST layer of the application. This causes the tests to then not reach C+. See incident description below.
This is caused by the tomcat application reaching its maximum number of open files. This can be observed by the log output above.
Checking the java process you can see the number of files open for the process reaches 4096:
[root@uuielap011 logs]# ps -ef | grep java
tomcat    5710     1  0  2018 ?      

[root@uuielap011 logs]# cd /proc/5710/fd
[root@uuielap011 fd]# ls -l | wc -l
4096

For the user Tomcat, the limit for maximum files open is allowed is 4096:
[root@uuielap011 fd]# su - tomcat
Last login: Tue Apr 24 08:08:20 BST 2018 on pts/0
-bash-4.2$ ulimit -Hn
4096




Missing IELTS Tests for the 28th - Please raise as a Priority 2 ASAP
Hello,
We can see that tests that should have been created by ATC/ATP overnight have failed to reach Connect Plus. It would also appear that there were a series of ATC and ATP failures this morning - this needs to be raised as a priority 2 call ASAP, especially for the sitting 2 tests where the failure happened over 8 hours ago.

I have attached the notifications of missing test packages from Connect Plus - THIS DOES NOT YET INCLUDE SITTING 3, WHICH ALSO APPEARS TO HAVE MISSING TESTS.

Please compare the report with the ATP/ATC failure notifications and try to re-process the tests. I will be monitoring this intermittently until 7pm tonight, at which point I will need a report from the Major Incident Manager about what has gone wrong and whether or not a resolution has been possible. I need to know this so that I can deploy contingency tests.

Best wishes,

Ben Cooper

SSD Manager | Systems Support and Development (SSD)
The Triangle Building, Shaftesbury Road, Cambridge, CB2 8EA
T: +44 (0) 1223 552600
NC3-H

Cambridge Assessment English
Part of the University of Cambridge
www.cambridgeenglish.org

We help people learn English and prove their skills to the world
Workaround: Restart tomcat across the REST Layer of the application.
RootCause:
SR200138 raised for RCA
In ATC REST layer the HttpClient used to send ATP response to IWAS is not closed (RestClient.java).
As UNIX like operating systems treat network connections like files, and they use file descriptors [REF 1, REF 2].
So for the system - not closing a network connection is equivalent to, a file being left open. This increases the number of open files count for the system. Once the maximum number of open files permitted for the process is exceeded, the issue surfaces.
Resolution: Raised as backlog item IELTS-10746.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange - Moderator is able to withdraw a candidate from a “Processed” claim
ProblemDescription:
Moderator is able to withdraw a candidate from a “Processed” claim.

This should not be allowed because once a claim gets processed, no further modification should be made to it. However, there is bug in Interchange due to which moderator is able to do this by opening two different tabs.

Further analysis and resolution has been provided in the attached RCA document.
RootCause:
After investigation, we have found that it is possible to withdraw a unit of a candidate from Interchange even if it has been processed.

We think the moderator must have opened the same “Review claim” page of the claim 474011 in two different tabs of the same browser. Suppose if the moderator confirms all the claims in the page which is open in the first tab and then proceeds, the claim will get Finalized and then to Processed. The file will then move to CAMS. Now if the moderator goes to the second tab where the same page is still open, and there if he/she Withdraws the claim, then in Interchange back-end, the claim will get withdrawn but no file will be generated.
.
Resolution:
Added to Jira Backlog with reference OCR-464. To be prioritised into a release. 
Moved to the Interchange Jira backlog for code change prioritisation

Subject: DC Event Subscriptions have stopped working
ProblemDescription: DC Event Subscriptions have stopped working. This doesn't break anything, but reduces our ability to troubleshoot
RootCause:
The event subscription had stopped due to an expired certificate on the collector (spinfap999).

When I created the WINRM listener with this command (three years ago): winrm quickconfig -transport:https it created the listener, embedding the thumbprint of the servers certificate in place at the time, this cert has since expired and been deleted by the server (as it's an auto-enrolled one).

This morning I replaced the listener, first delete: winrm delete winrm/config/Listener?Address=*+Transport=HTTPS and then create as above, then (as we are using port 443): winrm set winrm/config/service @{EnableCompatibilityHttpsListener="true"}

ProblemDescription:
Hi BTS,

Sitting: 1
Components: Reading
Module: GT

Please see attached test bundle report and screenshot from C+ for reference.

Jumar Bagtas | Application Support Technician
Workaround: CAE published content to the erroneous ‘Default’ placeholder and were then able to remove the content and placeholder altogether. As a result, the test instance is now approved and available for download.
RootCause: C+ has a place holder for each test bundle  and is possible to send the entries with or without QPVIDs. In EPS as we do not send QPVIDs so C+ creates a default placeholder but in IELTS we always send the QPVIDs so each QPVIDs creates a default placeholder.

Subject: Jan PETfs VN D426/02 KAD 06.01.2019.QP feed issue - RCA
ProblemDescription:
11/01 – 
On initial analysis, BTS has found that the QP feed had reached RM successfully on 20/11 itself but later SAP received another response as F1 (QPPD Failure) on 21/11. BTS have changed the flag status to C to try and resend but it has failed to send again.
   
14/01.  
The script that was run to change the Scoris flag status to C was incorrect. On correcting the script and running it again, the flag status was changed to C and the business have confirmed that the IGMD feeds have been successfully sent to RM.
  The root cause is to be identified at Biztalk end as to why SAP received another response on 21/11 which set the flag status to F1.
Workaround: The issue is temporarily solved after manual re-triggering.
RootCause: RC could not be identified in SAP End as PI would not hold 30 days old messages either not present in achieved folder
Resolution: Issue is not reoccurred for more than one month.

Subject: Problems with Search on Live Cambridge English Malaysia website

Subject: [RES-1578] Duplicate results showing in App Support Results Search
ProblemDescription:
Prerequisite
The same student must have shared their result with more than one on-boarded RO

Shared; Candidate name; Number; TRF number

Shared with;

Application needs to be changed in line with the required business rules.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Standard decommissioning activity resulted in Priority 2 incident
ProblemDescription:
Unable to connect to SAS PRD. Please see below for error. This was accessible last Friday 18/01/2019.

Unable to telnet the server and port from my machine.

Port 8563 is open on SPSASAP001 side.
Workaround: Firewall rules reinstated under Standard Change# 33061.
RootCause:
Root cause for this PR is human error contributed to by Production server names and IP addresses being used in a Non-Production environment.

Service request #196105 requested firewall rules related to SAS in the Threshold PP1 (THR-PP1) environment be decommissioned.  The server names and IP addresses used in THR-PP1 match Production.  The Network Engineer who fulfilled the service request incorrectly removed rules/objects relating to Production SAS on the Staging and Production firewalls.  The firewall policies were then installed under scheduled Standard Change 33016 on the morning of Saturday 19th January.  Subsequently some services and clients were unable to communicate with Production SAS, resulting in P2 incident 643407, resolved by re-instating the firewall rules under Standard Change 33061.
Resolution:
1) Education - remind all of Network Team that removal of PRD-related firewall rules or objects on STG and PRD firewalls must be done under Normal RFC, in line with rules relating to PRD servers.
2) Education - conduct a dedicated Tech Session for the Networks Team to review the network architecture of the THR-PP1 environment - in particular the use of conflicting names & IP addresses, and potential risks associated.
3) Process Change - when implementing decommission request for any environment, the Network Engineer must check (via ping & other means) whether the servers/systems being impacted have already been decommissioned.  If in any doubt, the engineer should halt the work and check with the requestor or other relevant colleague.  Escalate to Team Lead or SLT if any uncertainty remains.
4) Process Change - Decommissioning activities should be implemented under one consolidated Change (RFC) to ensure that all technical teams involved are aware, and the tasks are orchestrated to provide simple and fast roll-back.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange: A different claim gets updated when Moderator samples a Submitted claim
ProblemDescription:
It has been observed that if there are two claims of a centre for same scheme code, candidate and Unit where the first claim is Processed and the second claim is in Submitted status, then when the moderator samples the Submitted claim, the Processed claim gets updated to Sampled and its Sampled Date gets changed to the current date. The Submitted claim remains unaffected.

Please refer RCA document attached for more information.
Workaround:
Manually run the below script in the back-end to fix the issue:
update ClaimPackage set ClaimPackageStateId=6, SampledDate=XXXX where ClaimPackageId=XXXX

Get the Sampled Date from the ClaimPackageAudit table of the affected claim.
RootCause: The issue is happening due to incorrect logic written in SP [dbo].[eClaims_UpdateUnitSampled]. The ClaimPackageId is not passed to the SP. Rather it is set in the SP based on the Centre, Scheme Code, Unit and Candidate Number. Now when there are two claims with same Centre, Scheme Code, Unit and Candidate Number, then both claims are returned and the top most ClaimPackage ID is selected, which happens to be the one which already has been processed.
Resolution:
RCA document attached.  Jira-550 created in Interchange backlog

Moved to the Interchange Jira backlog for code change prioritisation:

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM: ATS PDF requests raised in ESM shows “Pending” even after 10-15 minutes
ProblemDescription:
When business creates ATS PDF requests by uploading csv files, the record gets created and it is shown in the screen “ATS PDF Status”. Usually the script should be available after 10-15 minutes but it has been observed that for random candidates, the status gets stuck at “Pending” and the user is unable to download the script PDF.

Further analysis has been covered in the attached RCA document.
Workaround:
Following is the workaround:
1. We provide the request_argument_id which has NULL rm_request_id in the table ATS.PdfStatus of database ItemMarksV2.
2. BizTalk sends us the Acknowledgement XML for the given request_argument_id (for example refer 904.xml attached).
3. We call the service http://spjntis011.ucles.internal/UCLES.ESM.Facades/AtsService.svc from SoapUI and pass the XML message to the operation SaveAtsRequestAcknowledgment.
4. The rm_request_id gets updated in the database.
5. We then ask BizTalk to provide us the PDF Filepath XMLs for the given rm_request_id.
6. BizTalk team sends us the XML (For example refer 439503_20.xml attached).
7. We call the service http://spjntis011.ucles.internal/UCLES.ESM.Facades/AtsService.svc from SoapUI and pass the XML message to the operation SaveAtsReturnOfScript.
8. The PDF filepath then gets updated in the table ATS.Files table and the script is then ready to be downloaded from ESM Portal.
RootCause:
We are unable to determine the root cause due to lack of proper logging in the back-end.
A CR will be raised to implement logging in the back-end in order to understand root cause and once the CR is implemented - Dev team will work on identifying the root cause
