Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: JIRA 10300 - IELTS - IWAS allocates same QPVIDs for different sittings
ProblemDescription:
IWAS is allocating the same QPVID (version) to different test sittings, including those with the same module and component.  It has happened for a total of 32 times (32 pairs of sittings).  This potentially means that the wrong band score could be used to calculate the final score of the candidate (R/L)

Luckily, only 2 of these are for the same module and component, and are either Reading or Listening (for which band score conversions apply).  Again, by pure luck, no results have been miscalculated yet. 

This is a serious issue which may lead to non-conformance.  Please contact me or Didac Planas-Paz for more information if required.
Workaround: Work around is being developed under JIRA https://btsservice.atlassian.net/browse/IELTS-10300
RootCause: None Created as duplicate, see 6710
Resolution: ive updated 6710 with more information and my one - 6709 can be closed as a duplicate

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Sessions/packets missing from STS
ProblemDescription:
A number of packets do not appear on STS. Everything has labels and is present on SAP but this data does not appear to have been pushed through to STS.
IDOC is responsible for sending the packets to STS as it belongs to respective PO in ECC. However in this case, it has not sent the packet to STS and multiple packets were seen to be created for the same session.
Workaround: As a workaround, the packet details need to be pushed again to STS again under a new IDOC for the packets to appear in STS.
RootCause:
The main incident involved with this problem record was caused by the exit of planet edu from SAP. This solution was always designed not to sent script packet label feeds, yet when the changover happened at the end of 2018, it happened just after the material order had been created for the incident in question. Other incidents associated to this related to connectivity problems which were one-offs and should be handled via incidents in the future. 

The main problem record for STS normalisation failures is PR 5597 and that must remain open. Development effort from the STS team is underway with PR 5597.
Resolution:
Resbumitting failed packet feeds for the order related to a planet edu customer solved the issue. 

PR 5597 aims to resolve the issues with normalisation failure.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-9352DefaultTest Versions are not appearing while tring to add/update PB SELT/NON SELT session.
ProblemDescription:
Login to Centre admin as a center user, select test type as PB SELT IELTS / PB IELTS. When we try to add or update an OSM session, default test versions are showing as pending and disabled.
 
Steps:
1.       1. Login to Centre admin as a CENTREUSERL1 user.
2.       2. Select test type as PB SELT IELTS / PB IELTS.
3.       3. Go to ‘Test Session’ section.
4.       4. Select ‘Add Paper Based OSM Session’.
5.       5. Give Test Session Date, Module, Test Location, Volume (number of test papers).
6.       6.   You will see default versions (Listening, Reading, and Writing) are showing as Pending.
7.       7. Click on Save. A new session with session id will be generated.
8.       8. For update, if we select ‘Manage Test Sessions’.
9.       9. Give Test Session Year, Test Session Month, Test Session Date, Module, Test Location.
10.   10. Click on Search and give Volume (number of test papers).
11.   11. Now you will see default versions are showing as pending here as well.
12. Now clicking on save button, session successfully saved with success message
Workaround: If customer wants to know the default test versions of any session they can give us the session id and we can share the versions details with them and if they want to change any version of  a session they can give us the changed version with session id details, we can change the version from backend an informed accordingly.
RootCause: Found a bug has been already raised 'IELTS-9352' to addressing this issue or PR '6721' and development team is working on it.
Resolution: This has been addressed under IELTS-10535 and released as part of IWAS 9.6.1. This has been confirmed by Jared in IELTS ops to be resolved.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: LIBSDATA tablespace runs out of space on Production LIBS database every Saturday morning
ProblemDescription:
For the last 3 Saturdays, foglight raises 2 alerts about space thresholds being breached and then a further error to say it has run out space.

Upon investigation, there is plenty of space available.

this suggested an operation that is trying to create a new object in the tablespace, fails when running out space and then backs out the request, freeing up the space.

Upon further investigation, it looks like it is the schedule ORACLE SPACE advisor that is causing a problem. A call will be logged with Oracle.
Workaround: Just ensure space is available after crashing with error
RootCause: Insufficient space for non-essential housekeeping job to complete.
Resolution:
Job disabled, now space freed under PR6838 RFC will be raised to re-enable.

Job enabled under RFC37078 (5/9) and we have received no error alerts since.

This Problem can now be closed.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SDCJNTSQ85 Drive-space low
ProblemDescription:
The D: drive on SDCJNTSQ85 is 75% full. We have been advised that it will require a reboot to extend the drive. Server hosts 4 instances and mixture of environments: UAT, Sys and Dev.

I suspect many of these databases can be decommissioned, but need time to identify this.

There are also space issues on the H: Drive, which could also be fixed either by an extension or by decommissioning databases and therefore having less backups to store.
Workaround: Free disk space is now below thresholds to avoid alerts
RootCause: New drive-space thresholds mean that space is now considered too low on the D: drive.
Resolution:
A number of system database files have been shrunk to free up sufficient space on the D drive. There drive is now 50% free space.

Instance SQL04 has been disabled as all of the user databases have been taken offline.

The database backups have now been transferred to NetBackup, which has cleared the space on the H drive.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Active results performance issues. Candidate Search not working and throwing timeout error.
ProblemDescription:
Upon replication of AR, use of the system is clearly degraded.

On investigation it was found that there were missing indexes (around 14) on the online database, which were dropped during bulk insert but did not get recreated after the insertion as complete. The replication job needs to be investigated as to why it is failing to recreate the indexes.

Also we need a script/mechanism to compare the database objects between offline and online database which we can run after the replication job is completed to check whether any db object/index has been missed during replication.

Please find atatchment for more information non the investigation.
RootCause: Replication method is inefficient
Resolution: New replication method has been built

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Page refresh happening during marking session creation
ProblemDescription:
When creating marking sessions the page refreshes each time a user takes an action (selects from a dropdown/ticks a check box) this should not be happening.

A short video to show what is happening is given below with the screencast link:

https://www.screencast.com/t/N96nb02Q4Dh
https://metrica.atlassian.net/browse/MET-8339 

After our investigation on this, we found that the marking setup page is coded in such a way that it doesn’t support partial page updates. As per the functionality in this screen, ‘Session Group’ value is loaded depending on the ‘Product’ value selected by user and populated in drop downs. However, we found this functionality (where page does not gets refreshed after every selection) is present in Sessions set up page when the user tries to add a session after creating session group.

So this needs to be developed using update panels and script managers to enable partial page updates like loading child drop-downs based on parent drop-down's selected value. This partial page update functionality is already present in the Sessions add page, which can be referred.
Workaround: None
RootCause: Code changes identified and provided to Metrica team further action under MET-8561
Resolution: Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-8561

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Bulats production database Configuration value got changed.
ProblemDescription: Candidates were facing problems of questions not appearing in the screen while appearing for the speaking test. Many examiners’ account was also got de-activated. These all were being accounted to the discrepant data at the backend in multiple tables. Upon further investigation it turned out that production database configuration was stored in source control and a typo in build command resulted in unit test cases to execute in production environment affecting multiple records in production database.
Workaround: Data of Production database compared with the latest available backup taken of the production database before the issues were reported to identify disparities and then update the same with the correct data in the existing production database using backend script.
RootCause: The root cause analysis identified that a process to build and test new non-production environment had been initiated using production configuration information leading to unintentionally change to production configuration data..
Resolution: The root cause analysis identified that a process to build and test new non-production environment had been initiated using production configuration information, action has been taken to prevent this happening again by removing access to the production configuration data.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Multipart packets’ part numbering is wrong for yellow label packets
ProblemDescription:
1.      1. Many times when packet contain more than one consignment number, the part numbering in ITEMDESCRIPTION field of STSITEM table for the packets per consignment number are updating erroneously through Half Hourly refresh job between STS and EPS. Screenshot from STS attached (Multipart_No_Error.jpg).


2. Due to existing code logic in database package when session activation job is running (everyday 23:30 hours), an exception is occurring for a particular case (Inserting multi part yellow label packets) which is interrupting the entire process of session activation. While session activation job is getting run in STS end at 23:30 on daily basis, if the argument of the of the mentioned procedure is not set/assigned in STS.SESSION database package under the database function DO_LOAD_FUNCTION, the session activation job will fail and the corresponding session will not get activated. Accordingly the STSPACKET table gets populated with required data partially. When the exception occurs, no data is processed further in the queue
Workaround:
1. For first case: Update ITEMDESCRIPTION of STSITEM table for affected packets through backend script.
2. For Second case: No such work around decided yet
RootCause:
1. Updating yellow label Packets:
When STS_ITEM_UPDATE.UPDATE_PKT_ITEM_DESCRIPTIONS procedure is called from the function body of DO_LOAD_PACKET_TABLE, the argument passed in the mentioned procedure is the item_id of the particular multi-part packet which is creating the problem. Screen-shot attached (RCA_Update_action.png). It should be passing the partMaster_Itemid as argument.
Error Message: “Multipart_No_Error.jpg”

2. Inserting Yellow label packets:
When STS_ITEM_UPDATE.UPDATE_PKT_ITEM_DESCRIPTIONS procedure is called from the function body of DO_LOAD_PACKET_TABLE, the argument is never assigned/set that is being passed as a parameter to the above-mentioned procedure. Screen-shot attached (RCA_Insert_action.png). This causes ‘ORA-01403: no data found’ error in the backend and all the further processing comes to sudden end leaving many data unprocessed and session remains in ACTIVATING state (Not getting ACTIVATED).
Error Message: “load FUNCTION DO_LOAD_PACKET_TABLE others exception catch, line 574, oracle code: 100  ORA-01403: no data found   l_debuginfo: before insert into STSPacket on line 789”
Resolution: Functionality didn't exist to handle this specific requirement.  Code change done as per STS-138. Release to production successful under Change 38664

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS Results Service - Unable to add RO_MAINTAINANCE, ROLE_APPLICATION_SUPPORT

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Missing A Level syllabus code on Statement of Entry when preceeded by IGCSE and ICE
ProblemDescription:
The issue was observed where a candidate had been awarded IGCSE syllabus, resulting in a special ICE award (ICE has no syllabus code by intent). This candidate then is awarded A & AS Levels, where the first award is missing its syllabus code.


Initially reported under IN#652564 where 27/02Activity History contains analysis and examples.
Workaround:
An exception from Print Systems would be to update the data file received to restore the missing syllabus code. This would be with agreement and for low candidate volumes due to manual nature of workaround.

A long term fix would be at EPS code level.
RootCause:
Missing component data structure <SOECOM>
It is noted that the data structure for an ICE award does not include the component element denoted by <SOECOM> in the data. As a result of no component data, a Transform logic process does not trigger resulting in the next subject showing no syllabus code. The Transform version 4 template is MCORD001.
Resolution:
Manual Resolution
A workaround was provided to the business to resolve the immediate issue of syllabus codes not being displayed. This involved data file editing to manually insert <SOECOM> (syllabus component data), and to make each data element empty.
The addition of the <SOECOM> data structure was able to trigger the Transform and leaving the data elements empty resulted in no unnecessary or spurious printed text.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Individual user account required to run reports on Robo ID Service
ProblemDescription:
1. This is a security issue as an individual's account (sheend) is required to enable the running of an automation service (the Robo ID service).  The Security Team is aware of this.
2. My understanding is that the Robo ID was initially set up approximately 3 years ago as a temporary solution (possibly pilot/POC)
3. This service is not in the Service Catalogue and, as far as I am aware, there is no Service Support documentation on this Service.
4. Since 2017 the customer CE has renewed the contract with the 3rd party company (TCS) without the prior knowledge of BTS.
5. As a solution an attempt was made to set up a generic account for this purpose in December 2017, to remove the requirement of the sheend account.  A condition of the approval for this account was that the use of it would be audited.  We are unable to carry out AD auditing on one account so the generic account was not used, neither was the set up within TCS carried out due to this.  The third party has not been able to provide us with suggestions for an alternative solution.

Three possible options for resolution:

1. Security sign-off for the sheend account to be used and monitored until this service is no longer required.
2. A new generic account is set up and configured by the third party TCS, the use of which is monitored.
3. As this was a temporary solution which has been extended, this requirement be taken through PMO so it can be set up as a production Service and is, therefore, included into the Service Catalog with the relevant documentation and support agreements.
Workaround: Account can be re-enabled and again disabled by the Service Desk when needed
RootCause:
The Robo ID was initially set up for the user Dakh Sheenam (username 'sheend')

This is a disabled account as Dakh left the company some time ago

This is the only account which is able to run the carry out the task of running the required reports

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Photo taken date is null for SELT candidates in IWAS backend.
ProblemDescription: 30 candidates found in IWAS backend (24 Life Skills candidates & 6 IELTS candidates) where photo taken date is null. These candidates are not present in UKVI backend as photo taken date is null in IWAS. PFA the list of candidates (Photo_Null_SELT.xls).

Resolution: Raised as IELTS-10975, added to the backlog.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ucv701prd failed battery
ProblemDescription:
This SAN supports EPS - IBM have warned of potential data loss if we were to proceed with the battery replacement so we're keen to schedule the replacement of this during the next major EPS maintenance outage so data flows etc. are already stopped. 
- Each PSU in a control enclosure contains a battery that kicks in during a temporary / short term power outage. Hence without the battery we have lost part of the resilience of that controller. 
- The IBM manual which is attached states that though the power supplies are hot swap-able, if the system is performing I/O operations swapping or removing the PSU can result in loss of access to data.
As this is the first of such an incident and because of the above we will require an IBM engineer to replace the battery and preferably at a time that is not service impacting.
RootCause: A battery has passed the end of its useful life, so needs replacing.
Resolution: Battery replaced under RFC 37850

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: [Inc-582598] - ZG Aberrant Examiner Cases on SAP -item task error - PRD
ProblemDescription:
To Investigate why ZG case types for an Aberrant Examiner for Test date 12.05.2018, May_2018_CAE2_Z2.  The cases have been created on SAP correctly.  However, the item task status of these candidates is stuck in 'RES'.  This should automatically change to 'PROC' to prime RMA so the examiner is flagged as Aberrant and the scripts marked originally by the examiner goes back in the live marking pool for remarking exercise. 
PR is raised to perform UAT for incident 582598.
Workaround:
HANA - Changes have been done in filter expression of CA_REP_ABERRANT_EXAMINER View based on ITEM GROUP ID to fetch the required output.

Fix has been done to handle the issue which sends multiple requests due to Not processed status from SAP end.
RootCause:
Issue was due to software malfunction which has sent duplicate requests to RM
HANA - BOBJ report wasn’t pulling any data after October’18 and found that the filter  in projection2 was modified in PP1 around October where additional conditions were added based on Start Date and Item Group ID. 

Issue: For ZG Aberrant Marker case, remark request should be sent only once for a combination even if multiple cases are created.
When a remark request is sent to RM, once it reaches RM it will update the status as ‘Processed’ in respective notification case(s). However there are few instances wherein due to connectivity issues, request will not reach RM and it will update the status as ‘Not Processed’ in notification case.
If the above instance occurs, then we have issues where the request is sent multiple times to RM for the failed Item Group.
Resolution:
Fix has been done to restrict the duplicate remark requests sent to RM. 

HANA - Changes are made under FILTER EXPRESSION PROJECTION_2 in CA_REP_ABERRANT_EXAMINER View such that if ‘item group id’ is provided as NULL it should fetch all entries (business requirement) and if a value is filled in ITEM GROUP ID column, only the corresponding data is fetched.

Fix has been done to handle the issue which sends multiple requests due to Not processed status from SAP end.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange: Some NCT Move Up/Down entries are made in Interchange with ReEntry code '0R'
ProblemDescription:
It has been observed that when centre is making a Move Up or Down entry, then in some cases, these entries are treated as Re-entry as they are having the 0R against them.

If User makes Move up entry for a scheme say ‘5824U’ and mistakenly makes the move up entry for the same scheme ‘5824U’ again. In this case the earlier entry record gets deleted and new record gets inserted for scheme code ‘5824U’ as Re-Entry (i.e. with ‘0R’). Same happens for Move down.
Workaround:
Update records with Move Up/Down entries in Interchange and make UnitNo blank by running the below script:
update forms_NQF1Detail set UnitNo='' where ID= @ID
RootCause:
The Interchange Cambridge Technicals Entry functionality checks if an Entry for the scheme code already exists in Interchange. If Yes, then system deletes the existing entry record and makes a new Entry against the scheme code as Re-Entry with code ‘0R’.
Therefore the Move Up /Down is made with Re-Entry code can be made for the following scenarios:
1.       User makes Move up entry for a scheme say ‘5824U’ and mistakenly makes the move up entry for the same scheme ‘5824U’ again. In this case the earlier entry record gets deleted and new record gets inserted
for scheme code ‘5824U’ as Re-Entry (i.e. with ‘0R’). Same happens for Move down.

2.       Candidate makes move up down within family in such way that same scheme has been moved up /down twice e.g.  05825-> 5824D -> 5825U-> 5824D. Here the second entry made for 5824D is inserted as Re-Entry. However, this appears to be very rare scenario, though you need to confirm this.

This problem impacts unit entry attempt count (due to the re-entry code with Move Up/Down). 
E.g. Candidate sits for 05825 and makes 1 unclassified attempt at tested unit 1, then moves down to 05824 (where the move down entry has been made twice mistakenly, resulting move down with re-entry code’0R’) . Now even if candidate makes the second unclassified attempt of unit 1 under 05824, it gets treated as 1st attempt due to the ‘0R’ re-entry code and full Unclassified award won’t get generated in this case.
Resolution: Added to backlog Jira# OCR-863

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Shows Incorrect Dates (exam date and date of birth).
ProblemDescription: The issue is regarding new Results Verification Portal  where  ‘Date of Exam’ and ‘Date of Birth’ candidate's are adjusted by one day(previous day). This is due to Time Zone issue.
RootCause:
The Date of Exam and Date of Birth shown is RO Portal as a html page which is implemented in viewcandidate.html and viewCandidateProfile.html. So, when a RO is accessing the portal then it is showing incorrect values(one day less than the actual dates) as this is due to time zone issue as identified in our investigation. 

Note:

Server Time : In application terminology ,server time is the time of that locale(timezone) where that server is located . For example if my server is located in India then it will come under the IST(Indian Standard Time) timezone.
Client Time : In the same context , client time refers to the timezone of the locale from where my client is accessing the application. For example if my client is accessing from Los Angeles USA, then their timezone will be Pacific Time Zone.
Resolution:
Service Request# 202121 raised for RCA. Added to Jira backlog with reference CER-293.

eg Date of Birth does not store time, so applying '-' timezone could move date to previous day. Fix applied to manage the scenario.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange is generating invalid check digit for some candidate UCI
ProblemDescription:
The Problem has been found through SR# 200644

We have found that the logic of generating the check digit (the last of the 13 characters) by Interchange is a little different to that of EPS.
 
We ran a couple of tests for some random candidates (given below) for generating the check digit from Interchange and then did the same by following the logic in EPS. For all the candidates, the check digit created by Interchange matched with that generated from EPS code logic:
 
365120177016C
A33221070703C
IE0300040001M
Q08500990075W
 
However, this failed for the three candidates that you have provided: X33570040900T, Q33520040500L, Q33531000700M. We have found difference in the check digit generated by Interchange and EPS.
 
Now, I have confirmed from Interchange Dev team that this code has not changed. Assuming that the logic in EPS has also not changed, then we can come to the conclusion that the logic in Interchange end needs to be in sync with the logic in EPS for all scenarios of candidate UCI string.
Workaround: None. Code fix required.
RootCause:
RCA required by Dev team under Spike for Jira# OCR-836.  
The logic for generating the check digit for UCI numbers in Interchange differs from EPS. So we need to change the logic in the interchange end for generating the check digit and implement the algorithm to generate the correct check digit.
Resolution: Resolution planned under backlog Jira# OCR-822.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: FAO Metrica APO team - Suspended session groups
ProblemDescription:
It is seen that at the moment that if a session group is suspended then all sessions currently within the session are suspended at the same time and any entry codes on these sessions cannot be used (expected behaviour).  However if a session is then added to the suspended session group they are added with the status of New and any logins created in this new session group can be used straightaway.

APO have been able to replicate the issue reported in this incident where new sessions created under suspended sessions are active by default. We believe this is a code issue and found that there isn’t  any check that’s in place while setting session status to check for session group statuses.

Resolution: Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-8876

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Beijing connection to external websites
ProblemDescription: Beijing Genesis office had reported they are unable to connect to external sites from China such youtube, google, training sites, etc. beginning 2019.
Workaround: Use Citrix application to access external sites using CA desktop or Internet application inside Citrix.
RootCause: The China government has intensified its policies with regards to connecting external internet sites from China.  The current MPLS service by BT includes internal access to CA resources only.  The Beijing office had a local internet connection provided by local ISP in which restrictions on specific internet sites are applied.
Resolution:
As confirmed by Service Delivery Manager and with advised from Legal, we are not to use any options that will circumvent the policies and legislation of China government with regards to restrictions on accessing external sites from China.  (Please refer to email).

On the other hand, CE is looking on some ways how they can provide resources to our Chinese colleagues. 

In that regards, Citrix is the only option that can be used by China staff to access external sites that are restricted from their local internet connection.

Subject: Innapropriate accounts added to local administrators group on PRISMASAT SQL Servers
ProblemDescription: On the PP2 and Production Prismasat availability groups the application accounts are not using database level permissions. They are instead added to the local administrators group on the servers and the builtin\Administrator SQL Server login, which should be disabled under our standard build, is present with the sysadmin role. Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IWAS: Performance Issue - Results management.
ProblemDescription:
IDP India reported a latency issue in IWAS. Major latency is when they click on Result Management > enter Result tab, it is taking a long time to load candidate details, hence delaying the result entry process.

They have confirm that there is no delay in logging in IWAS or navigation.

Here are the listed IDP India centres affected:

1.      IN855
2.      IA023
3.      IA024
4.      IN526
5.      IA027
6.      IA009
7.      IA008
8.      IN525
9.      IA025
10.   IA026
11.   IA003
12.   IN856
RootCause: Apache HTTPD Module mod_deflate was not specified in the apache configuration the new servers meaning the module was not in use. This module is enabled by default in Debain (old servers) but not in RHEL (new servers). Mod_deflate is used to compress webpages when accessed by users so without the compression users were seeing lengthy download/rendering times.
Resolution: Change made and implemented in Production.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: User Work Log empty for usernames in capital letters
ProblemDescription: User Work Log report generates an empty report, against a username that is in capital letters.
Workaround: Updated the usernames in the database of active users that were in uppercase to lowercase
RootCause: This is due to an error in code logic. The code logic responsible for accepting ‘username’ as input from frontend holds the value in lower case regardless of the case of the input. This is then passed to the code logic that queries the database with the input. Since usernames at the database end can be in any case, and since the input is directly compared with the values from the backend, the comparison fails when cases don’t match and no data is returned in the User Work Log report.
Resolution: In agreement with the business owner, as we now know the root cause, we have added the solution for this problem on Jira STS backlog. STS-153

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESOLCR Push Hanging
ProblemDescription:
The push is hanging and causing failures.
Error is not related to data, but seems to be due to process polling on NET-AP-01 - webservice has to be re-started
Workaround: Workaround is to restart the DataTransfer Windows Service hosted on server NET-AP-01.
RootCause: There is a known Microsoft issue related to MSMQ timeouts that may impact Responder implementations. By design, MSMQ disconnects every five minutes of inactivity and waits 60 seconds before attempting to reconnect. During this wait time, any Responder communication attempts would result in reach queue timeout errors.
Resolution:
Jira item MEPS-293 created.

1. To alleviate this issue, Microsoft recommends setting the wait time to 4 seconds (rather than the default setting of 60). 
2. Open the Registry and browse to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\Microsoft\MSMQ\Parameters.
3. Right-click the Parameters key and select New > DWORD value.
4. Name this DWORD value: WaitTime.
5. Right-click WaitTime and select Modify.
6. Set the Value Data field to the number of seconds (e.g., 4) MSMQ should wait before attempting to reconnect.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Deleting items in multiple-interaction items with image assets causes problems for test forms
ProblemDescription:
Greetings,

We've noticed another issue that we consider P2, possibly even P1 priority level. Details are below.

Description of the issue:
Deleting one question from a set is breaking any image links in the stimulus, and deleting more than one question from the set is breaking the entire print render, causing a runtime error and preventing the item (and any items after it) from appearing on a test form export.

Metrica URL affected:
https://protect-eu.mimecast.com/s/6FguCqYRRHLWRvwFZfZ8q?domain=metrica.cambridgemichigan.org
Version: 19.2.0.12086

Steps to reproduce:

1.       Log in

2.       Select Assessment Staff role (or other role with access to editing both Items and Tests)

3.       Search for/create an item with multiple interactions and an image in the stimulus

4.       Set the screen to display content on the left side and the print render on the right side

[cid:image001.jpg@01D4E963.6BC42DC0]

5.       Click Edit on the left content pane

6.       Delete one of the questions to delete and click the X on the question to delete it.

7.       Click save.

Expected Outcome: Deleted question/interaction is no longer displayed and images remain visible in print render.

Actual Outcome:  Deleted question/interaction is no longer displayed and image does not display in print render.

[cid:image002.jpg@01D4E963.6BC42DC0]

Additional steps:

8.       Click Edit in Content pane

9.       Delete additional question(s)

Expected Outcome: Additional deleted question/interaction is no longer displayed with no other effects on content or print render views.

Actual Outcome: Additional deleted question/interaction is no longer displayed in content view, and error message appears in print render view.

[cid:image004.jpg@01D4E963.6BC42DC0]

Additional steps:

10.   Navigate to Tests

11.   Open/create test form

12.   Add test section if necessary

13.   Add the item modified in above steps to the test form

14.   Add other items to the test form, below the modified item

[cid:image006.jpg@01D4E963.6BC42DC0]



15.   From the task drop-down menu at the top of the page, select "View this test as PDF"

16.   Click Submit

17.   Click OK

18.   Wait for download

19.   When download is complete, open PDF of test form

Expected outcome:
PDF displays all items included in test form

Actual outcome:
PDF displays only times ordered BEFORE the item with questions removed. Neither the item with questions removed nor any items ordered after it appear on the PDF.

[cid:image007.jpg@01D4E963.6BC42DC0]


NOTE: the same is true of the associated html bundle.

Impact on users/work:
We manipulate items with images and delete interactions on item sets as a part of test construction for multiple major test programs. Without a reliable way to compile and export constructed tests, we cannot meet our deadlines.

We're also very concerned about the repercussions of seemingly breaking items in the bank, as we don't have a way to get the item content out of the item bank except as an export on a test form. If the content doesn't show up on a test pdf OR HTML export, it seems that we no longer have a way of exporting test content, which is essential for creating paper-based tests, as we do for all our major test programs.

When was this last working?
Prior to the release of 19.2.

Operating System: Windows

Browser: Firefox (cannot currently try in Chrome, due to incompatibility of current version of Metrica with current version of Chrome). Once broken, problems with display and export persist in browsers other than Firefox (Explorer, Edge)

Thanks for looking into this.

APO Comments:
We have been able to replicate this issue in our environments. The Problem happens because of an incorrect item xml generation when any question is deleted. The problem occurs in stimulus area, where the xml changes to the below:
 
  <div class="stimulusarea">
        <div class="stimulus1"><div id="stimulus" bordertype="stimulus1" class="context-menu-one box menu-1">
          <img alt="" src="/MetricaadminSUP/item-content/6c/6c377a55-5a98-4015-8bc1-9ddcb90276db/1/TRS11_0005_A.png" /> <img alt="" src="/MetricaadminSUP/item-content/6c/6c377a55-5a98-4015-8bc1-9ddcb90276db/1/TRS11_0005_B.png" /> <img alt="" src="/MetricaadminSUP/item-content/6c/6c377a55-5a98-4015-8bc1-9ddcb90276db/1/TRS11_0005_C.png" />
          </div></div>
 
 
Whereas it should have been below,
 
<div class="stimulusarea">
        <div class="stimulus1"><div id="stimulus" bordertype="stimulus1" class="context-menu-one box menu-1">
          <img alt="" src="TRS11_0005_A.png" /> <img alt="" src="TRS11_0005_B.png" /> <img alt="" src="TRS11_0005_C.png" />
          </div></div>
        </div>
 
This is the reason the images are not getting displayed and the print render is throwing off the error.
RootCause: Issue identified and resolved under backlog item MET-8668.
Resolution: Issue identified and resolved under backlog item MET-8668. Fix deployed on 18/04/2019 under RFC# 34710.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CECP - change of schedule dates
ProblemDescription:
Issue: Certain deadline dates associated with bookings appeared to have changed since the bookings were first created. 
More details in the linked incident 665942.
Workaround: No workaround required as the deadline dates eventually are correct.
RootCause: In the BPM process flow, when amendment of a candidate is rejected and candidate status updated, all candidates in that booking is provided as input to the RFC - Z_PRE_UPDATE_STATUS. This makes withdrawn/submitted candidates to confirmed status in portal.
Resolution:
During booking amendment, status of old booking will be changed to ‘Amendment in progress. New booking will be created and status will be changed to ‘Amendment in progress’ and then to ‘Confirmed’. All the status changes are done by BPMUSER and not by network allocation process.

In order to make the network allocation process to confirm the booking status, Status change by BPMUSER should be restricted. Restricting ‘Confirmed’ status change alone will not allow the network allocation process to confirm the booking. So ‘Amendment in progress’ status change should also be restricted for BPMUSER. 

Booking status Amendment in progress and Confirmed change should be restricted in RFC Z_PRE_UPDATE_STATUS for BPM user. This will prevent booking gets confirmed by BPMUSER and allow network allocation process to confirm the booking.

This status change restriction makes bookings gets disappeared from CECP until it gets confirmed.  In order to make the booking gets displayed in CECP during amendment, Booking order no and schedule 25 date should get updated in ZPRE_VBAP table.

New RFC Z_PRE_UPD_BOOKING_NO should be created to update ZPRE_VBAP table with Booking Order No(VBELN) and Schedule 25 date (SCH_DATE_25) with system date temporarily in order to make the bookings visible in CECP. Later after booking confirmation, network allocation process will update the SCH_DATE_25 date from activity FSDE2S (As per the existing design).

RFC Z_PRE_UPD_BOOKING_NO should be called in BPM orchestration process during booking amendment after the RFC - Z_EXP_RFC_CREATE_BOOK_ORDER call to pass input parameter as VBELN (which is created from create booking rfc).In case of any error retry mechanism should be handled for 3 times.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-6305 - IWAS- Memory Leaks on TestAdmin nodes.
ProblemDescription:
We have re-occurances of the issue that was previously reported under PR 5824.
This is being investigated under JIRA 6305.
Nodes become unresponsive as GC runs and exhausts heapdump. From the Java doc:

"Excessive GC Time and OutOfMemoryError
The parallel collector will throw an OutOfMemoryError if too much time is being spent in garbage collection: if more than 98% of the total time is spent in garbage collection and less than 2% of the heap is recovered, an OutOfMemoryError will be thrown. This feature is designed to prevent applications from running for an extended period of time while making little or no progress because the heap is too small. If necessary, this feature can be disabled by adding the option -XX:-UseGCOverheadLimit to the command line."

The GC overhead limit exceeding generally happens when java virtual machine is not able to allocate memory in the heap space.
Workaround: Restart application.
RootCause: No identifiable issues in the code or configuration. Only explanation provided by support team: "The issue might be caused by too many users on the host on the site."
Resolution: Tomcat Memory settings were adjusted under 36104. Since then there have been no further incidents.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Incorrectly charged Late Fees
ProblemDescription:
Entry file was loaded for a centre containing candidates for syllabus R012. The centre then submitted an amendment file which contained an entry for a new candidate for R012. All the candidates took R012 in the January 2019 exam series, so their resitting of R012 in June 2019 series should not have applied late fees (until after the extended resit deadline of 21st March).

However, invoice generated charging R012 late fees for the original candidates on entry file but not for the candidate on amendment file.

Looking at the code logic, it seems that: for entry files, there is no check for re-take whereas, amendment files go through this check. This seems to be the reason why late fees is being genereated for the candidates in entry file but not for the candidates in amendment file.

For entry files, EPS calls a stored procedure to load the fees i.e. CADENZA_INVOICES.LOAD_FEES which then again calls a stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES which generates fees on a per assessment basis. Procedure GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES explicitly passes value 'N' for the parameters P_TIER_CHANGE_IND, P_RETAKE_IND and P_RETAKE_SES_IND. Whereas, these values are not hard-coded as 'N' in the case of amendement files. Instead, in the case of amendment files, EPS calls the stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.MAINTAIN_FEES which then runs a check (AUDIT_CHANGES_QRY.IS_RETAKE) to see if the current assessment is a valid retake. This check (function) then returns appropriate values for the parameters P_TIER_CHANGE_IND, P_RETAKE_IND and P_RETAKE_SES_IND which are later used in the stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.MAINTAIN_FEES to call CADENZA_INVOICES.GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES.
Workaround: Refund the late fees.
RootCause:
Looking at the code logic, it seems that: for entry files, there is no check for re-take whereas, amendment files go through this check. This seems to be the reason why late fees is being genereated for the candidates in entry file but not for the candidates in amendment file.

For entry files, EPS calls a stored procedure to load the fees i.e. CADENZA_INVOICES.LOAD_FEES which then again calls a stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES which generates fees on a per assessment basis. Procedure GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES explicitly passes value 'N' for the parameters P_TIER_CHANGE_IND, P_RETAKE_IND and P_RETAKE_SES_IND. Whereas, these values are not hard-coded as 'N' in the case of amendement files. Instead, in the case of amendment files, EPS calls the stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.MAINTAIN_FEES which then runs a check (AUDIT_CHANGES_QRY.IS_RETAKE) to see if the current assessment is a valid retake. This check (function) then returns appropriate values for the parameters P_TIER_CHANGE_IND, P_RETAKE_IND and P_RETAKE_SES_IND which are later used in the stored procedure CADENZA_INVOICES.MAINTAIN_FEES to call CADENZA_INVOICES.GENERATE_ASS_INVOICE_LINES.
Resolution: the EPS code is working correctly - we have asked OCR (Sharon Green) to raise a change request.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Empty place holder is appearing at Connect+ end due to changing test version/ module/ session transf
ProblemDescription:
According to present implementation, centre users are able to change both module and test version and session transfer after generating the attendance registration number. Due to this changes a new QPVID or test version is generated and candidate enrolment is processed with that new QPVID and also ATP publish the test bundle for the same or the latest QPVID. However, the original (now redundant) QPVIDs were already primed to C+, and when ATC/P was triggered no content was produced for them - leaving content placeholders in C+ without any content.
 
Steps:
  1. Login to Centre admin as a Center user.
  2. Enroll a candidate with candidate details against available session.
  3. Generate the attendance registration number.
  4. Candidate INSERT feed should be processed with both details and enrollment
  5. Now 57hrs before of the test date center user either change the module  or test version or transfer the session of respective candidate.
 
As suggested by Ed, we have to restrict not to change any test version, session transfer and module change after generating attendance registration number.
Workaround: Libs user need to publish the missing test bundle manually.
RootCause:
As per current business logic, the ESOL admin users can change module/ test version/ session transfer after 57 hrs. cut-off time period. 

This issue occurred due to the change in the module/test version by the user after 57 hrs. cut-off period. Because of this change, new QPVIDs were generated and tagged with those candidates, who were already present in the Connect + end with old QPVIDs. Due to this empty place holders were created on Connect + end for old QPVIDs.
Resolution: Fix included in IWAS R6 (June 2019), and/or handled via business process. (see attatched email).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BIZMQ-194 ASFA - AWS Priming issue with same Principal examiner in different components
ProblemDescription: When the Principal examiner (position 1.01) is same for two different components in an exam series in the EPS extract for AWS and ASFA priming, the priming completes but incorrect data is setup in ASFA backend and user creation is not done for one of the principal examiner in AWS. This results in ASFA backend to insert incorrect setup data and the ASFA admin and ASFA examiner portal is impacted.
Workaround:
Performing manual update in ASFA database. Create the Principal examiner entry in ASFA DB which is missing as ASFA creates only one entry for the Principal examiner. This is achieved by replaying the the missing Principal examiner data from BizTalk. Then update the orphaned examiner entries with the user credential of the created Principal examiner. Create AWS user  manually and update the database with username, password, accesskey and secret key. Update the portal pasword for the impacted user email in the ASFA User master table. Query sample:
--update [dbo].[AWSIAMUserCredential] set 
--AWSUserPWD = 'ZuuyCX4ITWQEpTj3l/LAUg==',
--AccessKeyID = 'AKIASUAUK5EYWK3YDRN3',
--SecreteAccessKey = 'mCkYBJ80hLUblQe4vcv6Apan6frw6f0sTkiEzsdS'
--where UserCredentialId = 810
-----
--update [dbo].[AWSIAMUserMaster] set PortalPWD = 'ZuuyCX4ITWQEpTj3l/LAUg=='
--where UserId= 752
-----
--UPDATE ASFA_ROLE_HIERARCHY set PARENTCREDENTIALID=963
--where USERCREDENTIALID in(836,
--959,
--960)
RootCause: CIE tactical configurator and ASFA currently is not able to handle the data scenario where same PE exists for two different components in the same exam series.
Resolution:
Code change targeted for BizTalk Release 4(October) 2019
Jira - BIZMQ-194

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Rates Manager transfer to EPS.
ProblemDescription:
In Rates Manager application in production, Static table refresh approximately take 1 hour to complete but since 02/04/2019 it is taking more than 12 hours which lead to Rate Manager not able to push recently updated rates into the EPS.

APO have investigated this and found that there is a service RatesManagerExportService which refresh the Static table every day. Earlier when it was running normally took approximately 40 min. to complete the refresh but since 02/04/2019 it was abruptly taking more than 12 hours. Because of this lag in refreshing the static table, OWB job fails to pick up the data and push into EPS.

We consulted this with the database services team  to check for blockages or performance issue at the data source. Gary Christopher Tunac and Gavin investigated this and found there was a problem with the db standard threshold and the time when this job was running the threshold was getting exceeded. We have attached the investigation email from Gary in this PR.
All relative incidents attached.
Further investigation and fix suggestions needs to be provided by Database Service team.
Workaround: Once Static table get refreshed completed, we need to change the OWB job Rates pulling date windows by running a script such that EPS pulls the recently updated/created rates.
RootCause: APO have investigated this and found that there is a service RatesManagerExportService which refresh the Static table every day. Earlier when it was running normally took approximately 40 min. to complete the refresh but since 02/04/2019 it was abruptly taking more than 12 hours. Because of this lag in refreshing the static table, OWB job fails to pick up the data and push into EPS
Resolution:
Maintenance tasks including running a statistics update against the Fear database have been completed by the DBA's

The RatesManagerExportService performance was improved and took 40-45 minutes to refresh static table instead of 12 hours from 24th April. Incident lead 664769

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Test bundle missing in Connect Plus
ProblemDescription:
Test bundles are missing in connect plus even when the corresponding request ID in ATP is showing completed processing status.
 
The effected QPVID’s provided by Connect Plus are 52JBTRGT , 52QOLRGT and 52RMVL
The corresponding ATP request ID’s that were effected are
8912624b-affd-4c0b-aa7c-c3604669ab66, b327ca74-4e80-46cc-a134-0fd7af1892e7,
cce83e39-20ee-4bc8-ab3b-0188e2b9fa6a, 0b437f44-e29d-45e6-90d7-584f5e4a30c0
RootCause: The behavior experienced in this problem is an issue but it directly doesn't involve ATP, it is a bundle builder issue.  If the ATP status of the request is “Completed” and the outcome is “9004” this means that the ATP engine has finished processing the request (COMPLETE) but still the outcome is partially published to the downstream application(9004). In this particular case, the request was partially published because the bundle builder was down. For this reason, ATP engine failed to publish the Test Bundles(as it requires the involvement of the Bundle Builder application) but was able to publish the AnswerKeys(as it does not requires the involvement of the Bundle Builder application).
Resolution: Created KA (1607) for the team to be aware and do proactive monitoring/handling accordingly.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange: Sometimes claims get stuck in 'Finalized' status
ProblemDescription:
It has been observed that sometimes claims gets stuck in 'Finalized' status and does not get 'Processed'. The most common issues identified for this are following:
1. Malpractice flagged. Centre review is required.
2. Other Awarding Body claim
3. Examiner is not allocated to the scheme and centre
4. NULL or Invalid RSA Candidate Number in Claim
5. Candidate added to claim but no unit selected.
Workaround: Workaround is to run a script to remove the erroneous record.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM imports of Session Setup for a particular session fails on Mondays due to EPS Maintenance Window
ProblemDescription:
ESM imports like PopulateESMAssignments, PopulateESMControl, PopulateItemMarksReportStructure fails on Monday.

This happens because of the EPS Maintenance Window which starts at Sunday 16:30 and ends at Monday 08:00. Now since the import schedules are set to run daily, if it runs on Sunday before 16:30 and then the window starts before the import could end, it fails. Then again on Monday when it tries to run, if it is still in the window interval, then the job fails again. It successfully runs on Tuesday.
Workaround: Workaround is to manually start the Import from the ESM Portal - Session Setup screen on Monday.
RootCause: Duplicate of 6778
Resolution: Duplicate of 6778

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Candidate enrolment push from IWAS INSERT feed is not working properly. In some scenarios INSERT fee
ProblemDescription:
When IWAS send INSERT feed the operation type sent from IWAS to BizTalk is “C” (Create) and for DELETE feed it is “W”(Withdraw).
While IWAS are sending the INSERT feed from IWAS to BizTalk we can see the operation type is “W” which supposed to be “C” for version change of any candidate in IWAS.
 
For candidate enrolment re-push below steps need to follow:
 
·         For candidate enrolment re-push first we need to insert a DELETE feed in “IWAS_MESSAGE” for the particular candidate where intend=’DELETE’.
·         Take the IWAS_MESSAGE_ID from the above DELETE feed and make an entry into “IWAS_MESSAGE_CANDIDATE_SAFE” with previous version which we want to delete.
·         Now check in “IWAS_MESSAGE” table for successful process of the DELETE feed.
·         Now make an entry for INSERT feed for the same candidate in “IWAS_MESSAGE” with intend=’INSERT’.
Workaround: Re-pushing the delete and insert feed respectively using pre-approved script by Mick Edwards.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IWAS: Result Management - Latency Issue
ProblemDescription: The result management query is using a bad execution plan and it was taking 1000 times longer to execute.
Workaround:
After limited TOMCAT restarts, the execution plan for the application code was used by Oracle and performance return to normal.
(Future reoccurance investigations show follow the plans in https://cambridgeassessment.sharepoint.com/:w:/s/csd/bts/onesource/EW-VvNsKl5ZGrCfiS3E47LYBhKmM4i8j_-IQDhu453kUOA?e=uRFZc9 )
RootCause: Oracle Optimiser selected a poor execution plan for a regularly run piece of application code. Instead of it taking less that one second per execution it to over one minute. Resulting in the server becoming CPU bound, causing across the board slow application performance.
Resolution:
Long term: Once RCA confirmed, permanent fix to avoid reoccurrence to be considered.(options include pinning execution plan, using baselines, or hinting application code).

Plan to be baselined upon recommendation from Oracle. RFC37905 raised to implement the change on 28 Oct 2019.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: DO_LOAD_PACKET function failure which disrupts the half hourly job.
ProblemDescription: EPS sends yellow label packets (packets that contain consignment_number), which are successfully populated in STS end. Eventually EPS resends the same packet as a white label packet (packet without consignment_number). This results in an exception in DO_LOAD_PACKET function code logic as it fails to update the yellow packets to white packets in STSPACKET table when trying to update the packets as per new details in ALL_EPS_SCRIPT_PACKET_ALTS table.
Workaround:
There are two possible solutions:
1. Update the error packet in the STSPACKET table with consignment_number field as null after customers’ consent. This converts the existing yellow packet to white packet. 
2. Or Ask EPS to send these as yellow label packets as per the business requirement
RootCause: So the RCA (on the STS side) is that EPS sent the wrong data, specifically, a packet was initially sent as a yellow label, then then sent as a white label.
Resolution:
So the RCA (on the STS side) is that EPS sent the wrong data, specifically, a packet was initially sent as a yellow label, then then sent as a white label.  And the workaround was to adjust the data to make the whole thing a white label.  And although we don’t know the overall root cause of why EPS behaved this way, the analysis by Cognizant Support makes the following points: (1) STS is working properly (2) the incident is fully resolved (3) the root cause from an STS perspective has been identified as bad data from EPS, and (4) this is rare.

Based on this happy to resolve PR 7508.  However, if we see this happening several more times and it looks to be a systematic/reoccurring issue that’s impacting the team, we will need to engage EPS to address the overall root cause.

STS-207

We need to introduce a check in here so that if any of the group codes are missing in the combination chosen, it gets disqualified
Resolution: Code change required - needs to be prioritized into a release.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Discrepancy in ‘Download CSV of all Submissions’ link under ‘History’ tab.
ProblemDescription: The "overview report" generated from ‘Download CSV of all Submissions’ link under ‘History’ tab is fetching duplicate entries records per candidate wise on the basis of first entry record pulled against a candidate.
Workaround:
): The report can be extracted using backend script (as mentioned below) and can be provided to the customer.

SELECT SubmissionDate,
  ShortName      AS Qualification,
  AssCode        AS SyllabusCode,
  AssessmentName AS SyllabusName,
  OptCode        AS Optioon,
  DeleteIndicator,
  CanNo AS CandidateNo,
  CandidateName,
  Dob                           AS DOB,
  Sex                           AS Gender,
  FirstLanguageEnglishIndicator AS English1stLang,
  UCI,
  NationalId,
  ULN,
  SchoolPrivInd AS Status,
  PreviousCnuId AS PreviousCentreNo,
  PreviousCanNo AS PreviousCandNo
FROM ReportHistoricSubmissionOverview
WHERE CnuId = 'US686'
AND SesSid  = '16844'
ORDER BY SubmissionDate,
  CanNo;
RootCause: The "overview report" is fetching duplicate records for candidate entries.  This happens when the id element in the entity class is not a primary key in the Database Table. Hibernate treats all rows with the same ID as the same object. The current code has a column ‘CsSid’ in the entity class (Code_snapshot.png) of the corresponding view in the database named ‘ReportHistoricSubmissionOverview’ from where the record is getting retrieved, is declared as a primary key that is not unique.

Subject: Interchange: Unable to export data to Excel
ProblemDescription:
Following the Interchange server upgrade, the ability to export to Excel gives an error.

This was nottested during the upgrade project.

RootCause:
The old servers had Excel 2003 installed.   Excel 2003 is not supported and tests with Excel 2010 or 2016 give an error.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM CPU utilization spikes to 100% with increased loads
ProblemDescription:
The CPU for ESM Application server SPJNTIS011 spikes to 100% when the we have increased loads of data.
We have identified that the Facade services are causing these spikes.

Current workaround -
1. Automatic scheduling of recycling of application pool every 15 mins is in place. 
2. Monitoring alerts (P2) to Service desk for when ESM hits 85% CPU utilization is also in place. 

These 2 workarounds have been working well since 24th May and now we would like to proceed with root cause investigation.
Workaround:
Automatic scheduling of recycling of application pool every 15 mins is in place. 
Monitoring alerts (P2) to Service desk for when ESM hits 85% CPU utilization is also in place. These 2 workarounds have been working well since 24th May and now we would like to proceed with root cause investigation.
RootCause:
1. Panel 9389/41 and 9389/42 had circular hierarchy in ESM
2. PE was assigned to the panel in EPS and assignments were submitted on ESM
3. PE was later changed to become an examiner in the same panel BUT ESM was not updated to reflect the same
4. My understanding is scenario like #3 warrants a manual intervention when panel administrator requests BTS for the change to be reflected in ESM assignments.
5. Because Step # 4 didn’t take place – in ESM the hierarchy became circular and hence we received 100% CPU hikes.
6. BTS was informed on 6th June to modify the panel in ESM and after 6th June we haven’t seen any CPU hikes.
Resolution:
Ensure the correct existing business process is followed within panels team.
Application pool recycle to revert to its default setting.

Jira backlog ESM 114 , ESM 115 & ESM 116 for looking at future work into increase CPU

Subject: Entry file is not getting uploaded
ProblemDescription:

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BizTalk SQL Backup Job completion issue in Production
ProblemDescription: The backup job is taking much longer to complete and in some cases its exceeding the time limit of 5 hours and hence not completing at all. As a result the backup file size is increasing and subsequent backup time is increasing. Once the database log file size increases it occupies more disk space and the messagebox db fails to work for lack of space in the disk. Once this happens the whole BizTalk processing shuts down impacting all the flows.
Workaround:
As a temporary workaround the  followed things were done:
1> Stop all processing in BizTalk
2> Increase the diskspace in the impacted database server
3> let the backup of the logs complete
4> shrinks the log file
5. kill the running backup job and start a fresh one.
RootCause:
On further analysis, what is found is:
1> The backjob is running on the primary server instead of the secondary.
2> The most used database Bamprimary DB is regularly hitting high 90% CPU.
3> The allocated diskspace for messagebox dbs is not adequate in high load scenario.
Resolution:
1. Emergency RFC to Increase RAM in sqesbsq205 and sqesbsq215 to 128 GB 
2. F: drive disk increase to 1 TB in Primary and Secondary servers of Msg_01, msg_02, BAM Primary and ESB Exception DB 
3. Back job monitoring alert set up as P2– if it run more than 2 hours 
4. Backup preference change in all BizTalk SQL server to secondary after we have watched the performance at noon 
5. Active monitoring of DB performance during 12:00 – 3:00 PM today – Chris and Integration Team

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BWP Garbage Collector warning - increase in potential blockers since 27 May 2019
ProblemDescription: An alerting system exists that tracks the number of potential garbage collector blockers in the HANA environments everyday. If it exceeds a predetermined threshold, an alert is sent out. Since the 27th of May, what was on average +- 1 blocker per day has suddenly increased to +- 200 per day.
RootCause:
There were transactions hanging around in the database after the app servers had unexpected failures. The trick is to use the SM12 SAP transaction to track these transactions and remove them. The garbage collector will help identify when this happens again in the future.
Since the transactions have been terminated, we have no longer had any garbage collector blockers.
Resolution:
There were transactions hanging around in the database after the app servers had unexpected failures. The trick is to use the SM12 SAP transaction to track these transactions and remove them. The garbage collector will help identify when this happens again in the future. Also added to the daily checks in SAP.
Since the transactions have been terminated, we have no longer had any garbage collector blockers.
See incident 685624 for more detail around faulty transactions.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IWAS ATP Failure - Application halts processing.
ProblemDescription:
ATP Application servers halt processing and only log lines once every ~10 mins as opposed to normal 15 seconds per line. This means requests don't get picked up by the application servers with the issue. This means the application runs with degraded performance causing delays leading to failure notifications.
No issues can be found in the application logs to determine issues.
The application logs often stall but then recover without any obvious reasons. In this case, incident have not been logged but logs are checked to ensure application is running correctly.
This is linked closely to the ATC PR, 7193 which will likely have the same root cause. All of the application logs are in the attached incidents.
Workaround: We have created a monitoring script which will determine when logs are not writing correctly. If this is noticed then the affected application server will be restarted.
RootCause:
Investigating the issue, it is found that few framework level tasks are getting stuck while updating the database, thus causing the primary process to halt.  
As it can be seen that these tasks have started as they have create_time and start_time but have not finished as there are no end_time, thus causing the main job to hang. We also cannot confirm the exact error due to which the task got stuck as there is also no exit_code or exit_message.
There are few data tables in TC_PRD schema, which are entirely used by the spring-boot framework to store metadata related to the framework execution. As time goes the amount of data in these tables are continually increasing, and thus, these jobs sometimes get hanged while trying to access these tables. Hence as time goes size of these tables are growing and so are the frequency of occurrence of this issue.
Resolution: Indexes were applied to LIBS database which greatly improved the performance of the ATC code and in-turn has stopped the application stalling.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ROs not receiving results via Results Service
ProblemDescription: Due to improper working of POLLER job some ROs are unable to see as well as download shared results in the IELTS Result Services site. TRFs for those specific ROs are present in the IBASE database, but those are not flowing to the IRS database as the Poller job which is responsible for this flow is not working correctly.
Workaround:
We can backfill the results for each individual ROs by the following steps 
 1. Log into server upirsap100
 2. Run the following command by providing the RO id and the date from which to backfill results.

wget -T 7200 -t 1 http://localhost:8080/api/manage/jpJElZSfhge3uIdF/event-replay/org/5/?start=2017-05-25T00:00:00Z

We also  have provided a script /home/rspoller/backfill_ro/backfill_ro.sh where by you can specify the list of ROs that need backfilling in the ro_list.txt file and then adjust the time in the script. This will then run the api for each RO.
RootCause:
If there is an error in processing candidate results, and/or poller component is not able to insert data in AWS RDS, there was no retrying mechanism available in the old poller code to repush the candidate results. In absence of proper logging and retrying mechanism, it was not possible to determine the exact root cause of the of the missing candidates.

As part of the IRS stabilisation work, the old code has been lifted and shifted to new supportable technology with enhanced monitoring and logging. No changes were made in poller logic.

As part of further enhancement to IELTS Result service, exception handling has been made robust and retry mechanism has been added to repush candidate results automatically to AWS RDS in case of failure. The new change is expected to go live in Nov 2019.
Resolution: Appropriate change to be made to the Poller application. JIRA IELTS-11397 raised.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Brahms went down
ProblemDescription:
Description of fault: Monitoring alert for Brahms

Application / URL affected: brahms.ucles.internal

Error message: brahms.ucles.internal : Critical: Host Monitored State Changed

What is the impact of this incident to business operations: 
the following EPS environments are NOT available:
·         MDEV  
·         MUAT  
·         MSUP  
·         ODEV  
·         OUAT  
OSUP
Production EPS is not affected
RootCause:
The packets are being dropped due to insufficient Receive buffers. This needs to be tuned according to the workload. The packets drop is not seen on dev_vios2, but It's suggested to be tuned there also.

Please run the below commands in the following order for dev_vios1 and dev_vios2

#chdev -l ent4 -a min_buf_tiny=640 -P

#chdev -l ent4 -a max_buf_small=4096 -P
#chdev -l ent4 -a min_buf_small=4096 -P

#chdev -l ent4 -a max_buf_medium=512 -P
#chdev -l ent4 -a min_buf_medium=256 -P

#chdev -l ent4 -a min_buf_large=48 -P

#chdev -l ent4 -a min_buf_huge=48 -P
Resolution: Parameters were changed under RFC

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-11079/10310-Candidates stuck in Second Entry Pending state for all result components
ProblemDescription:
Candidate’s all four result components were stuck in SECOND_ENTRY_PENDING state.
 
The following two candidates were stuck in Confirm Results and moved onto View Complete Results despite the scores having been entered.

13/06/2019 - Barodda, Gujarat : 076207
13/06/2019 - Ahmedabad, Gujarat : 081460

When looked into IWAS back-end, it was seen that all the result components (R, L, W, S) was in SECOND_ENTRY_PENDING state.
 
PFB the data analysis against this issue from PRD audit records:
1.      076207 Candidate (Centre – IN001, Test Date – 13th June, 2019):
a.       Writing marks submitted for 2nd entry at first (17-JUN-19 11.11.52.124000000) by Sagar.Kumar@in.britishcouncil.org.
b.      Speaking marks submitted afterwards for 2nd entry (18-JUN-19 07.10.22.600000000) by Girijesh.Kumar@in.britishcouncil.org.
c.       Speaking result state changed to 2nd entry pending on 18-JUN-19 07.17.17.385000000.
d.      Reading and Listening marks submitted at the same time (19-JUN-19 07.47.45.155000000) by same user (shambhu.bera@britishcouncil.org) next.
e.       Rest 3 components’ (i.e. Writing, Reading and Listening) result state changed at the same time (19-JUN-19 07.52.25.430000000) to 2nd entry pending.
f.       And Writing result state changes just few millisecond later (19-JUN-19 07.52.25.449000000).
 
2.      081460 Candidate (Centre – IN001, Test Date – 13th June, 2019):
a.       Writing marks submitted for 2nd entry at first (19-JUN-19 05.44.00.553000000) by shambhu.bera@britishcouncil.org.
b.      Speaking marks submitted afterwards for 2nd entry (19-JUN-19 06.08.10.200000000) by vijay.kumar1@britishcouncil.org.
c.       Speaking result state changed to 2nd entry pending on 19-JUN-19 06.12.41.372000000.
d.      Reading and Listening marks submitted at the same time (20-JUN-19 09.54.44.327000000) by same user (Sagar.Kumar@in.britishcouncil.org) next.
e.       both components’ (i.e. Reading and Listening) result state changed at the same time (20-JUN-19 10.00.59.013000000) to 2nd entry pending.
f.       And Writing result state changes just few millisecond later (20-JUN-19 10.00.59.039000000).
 
Both the cases, the order of submission of marks for each component of each candidate is same. The pattern is identified from audit records of IWAS backend. As per result component state flow, 4 components cannot be at 2nd Entry Pending state at a time and the state should be result complete or jagged entry for each component. But here all the component stuck into 2nd Entry Pending, which is not an expected scenario. This is the reason these candidates are not move into View Complete result section. But we still unable to establish any reason for 2nd entry pending status of each component at a time.
Workaround: Candidate score wipe out through back-end script execution
RootCause: RCA completed by development team and also confirmed  that this is an existing issue in PRD - concurrency bug and  which is currently planned for R7
Resolution: Fix to be deployed with IWAS R7 as IELTS10310.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ATC Failure - Application halts processing. (logs not writing)
ProblemDescription:
We established a pro active monitoring on our ATC servers where in we will be alerted if logs suddenly stopped. This is for us to track down if there are issues such as high memory consumption. 

We are receiving quite a lot of alerts since we implemented this. The issue we note of as of the moment is the logins from Foglight server when the time the logging of ATC application somehow stopped. There were times that ATC resumed the processing after the login entries from foglight but there are cases where it requires service restart before it starts processing again (recent occurrence is Incident 686286). Please note that ideally, ATC should be logging activities every 10 to 20 seconds gap. If it halted for about a minute or more that could indicate a problem either on the server or in the application. 

No issues can be found in the application logs to determine issues. The application logs often stall but then recover without any obvious reasons. In this case, incident have not been logged but logs are checked to ensure application is running correctly.
This is linked closely to the ATP PR, 7149 which will likely have the same root cause. All of the application logs are in the attached incidents.
Workaround: Restart ATC Service on the affected server.
RootCause: There are few data tables in TC_PRD schema, which are entirely used by the spring-boot framework to store metadata related to the framework execution. As time goes the amount of data in these tables are continually increasing, and thus, these jobs sometimes get hanged while trying to access these tables. Hence as time goes size of these tables are growing and so are the frequency of occurrence of this issue.
Resolution: Indexes were applied to LIBS database which greatly improved the performance of the ATC code and in-turn has stopped the application stalling.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Auth0 EMails
ProblemDescription:
The email templates being used by DNPD Remote Speaking which use the Cambridge English tenant were overwritten by the CE Results Service. 

Issue is summarised by Shaun Russell as below:

To summarise the problem for which an incident has been raised, I will bullet-point what the scenario is below:
 
  • Auth0 runs on the concept of tenants.  A tenant represents a way of isolating the Auth0 containers, and we do this based on a business unit such as Cambridge English, Cambridge international etc.
  • The e-mail template section within Auth0 is based at the tenant level, and offers 7 examples such as password reminder, welcome email and so on.
  • As we have multiple applications (websites, portals) running within the Cambridge English tenant there is a clash on which application uses the built in e-mail template as the CE RVS project has overwritten the Cambridge English Listening Files templates.
  • The way to get around this is to disable the built in e-mail templates and provide them through the applications specifically. This avoids any templates being overwritten.
At present we have Remote Speaking and CE RVS within the Cambridge English tenant, and there are more coming on-line soon that will also require their own e-mail templates.

I understand the best solution for this is to switch to use Amazon SES email with Auth0.  We need central help and guidance to do this.

This may also affect IELTS Results Service (IELTS Tenant).

Raised in DNPD project as RSPK-877.  Impact is that trial examiners when added to our system get emails that they think are phishing emails (see attached).

In the above command LinkField was set to 3. LinkField 3 refers to Xplan field User3, since the User3 is not provided in the above command this updated all the records where the User3 field is empty. For permanent employees User3 field empty this all the permanent employee cards were deleted.
Resolution:
Deleted cards were restored from XPLAN deleted card column in the table XPLAN09.

Below SQL command executed to restore the cards XPLAN staging table.
INSERT INTO [XPLAN].[dbo].[XPLAN36]
(UpdateID,
Action,
LinkField,
CardNo,
ExpiryDate,
User1,
RecordStatus)
SELECT CardID,3,1,DeletedCard,'20390630',User1,'0' FROM [XPLAN].[dbo].[XPLAN09]

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: [IELTS-11071] Length of Identity number should be changed to 20 characters in ORS.
ProblemDescription:
1.      1.  Created candidate in ORS with ID Doc having 21 characters 
  1. The candidate is loaded successfully in IWAS via API, and 201 success messages are received back into ORS.
  2. When checked in IWAS, the candidate is saved in the session. However, there is a Warning message next to the Passport/ NIC number  (Value too long ("Pilottest9-updated now"), please reduce to 20 characters)

IWAS only accepts up to 20 characters.

Resolution: Fix included i IWAS R7 (Nov 2019) as IELTS-11071.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM: Centre Exclusions not importing to ESM from EPS
ProblemDescription:
It has been observed that not all centre exclusions set in EPS for CIE June 2019 session have imported to ESM. Most of the centre exclusion data are missing in ESM.

User wants this PR to be raised to Priority 3.
Workaround: Workaround is to Clear Down Centre Exclusions table in ESM and then re-import them from the ESM Portal.
RootCause: Business was unaware that Panel's apportionment must be approved.
Resolution:
Awareness of EPS filter criteria:
Please find the filter criteria for marker availability in EPS.

1. Invitation-response of Session-panel-member should have value between ‘A’ and ‘V’. 2. Either Session-panel-member invitation-response should have value between ‘R’ or ‘N’ or session-panel-member should be withdrawn. 
3. USE-ESM-INDICATOR of session-panel-member table should have value and should be not equal to "NONE". 
4. Regarding panel, it should be a UK panel.
5. Panel's apportionment must be approved. 
6. USE-ESM-INDICATOR of panel should have value and should be not equal to "NONE". 
7. Panel's entry-count should be greater than zero. 

Note : Point 1 and 2 are mutually exclusive. It means if the record satisfies 1 it does not meet 2 and vice versa.
