Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Unable to generate SoRs
ProblemDescription:
We are sending notification emails to candidates on result release days to say their results are ready to view before Print Systems have produced the candidate PDFs. This leads to high levels of customer frustration and significant contact for the CE Customer Support Team

- When ESOLCR receives the result release date from SAP via PRDB on session setup it converts the date format to datetime meaning that SAP sessions all get set with a default result release time of 00:00 for candidates.

- The EmailNotification service on the legacy portals looks to see if this date and time has passed (along with some other criteria) before emailing the candidates to say their results are ready.

- This means that on a result release day when SAP (via PRDB) transfers the result information to ESOLCR we send notifications to candidates immediately even though it’s likely that the PDFs for the candidates are still in the process of being compiled by Print Systems.

- Result release time in ESOLCR was updated via script under SR 211239 but the PRDB extract job reverts the time back to 00:00.
Workaround: Workaround is to disable notification service, and reeenable once results pushed.
RootCause:
Once results pushed from PRDb to ESOLCR the notification email is sent to candidates saying SoR available, but when candidate views the SoR it is not yet generated as it is on the generation queue. This is because the release date defaults to midnight, and does not contain a time portion of when results wil actually be available.
The results is viewable on the portal, it is just the SoR pdf that is not available.
Resolution:
Once One PDF goes live (eta Feb 2020), then PR #7218 no longer required as CE Portals will no longer generate SoR's. James Loose is checking if workaround is manageable in the meantime.

If workaround not manageable, then will add to integration team backlog for software fix.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP PI database performance
ProblemDescription:
This query below is the top query in PI and it is being executed over 1000 times a day and check whether it can tuned:

SELECT M.DBKEY, M.NAME1, EK.OP_MODIFIED, EK.UDDIKEY_V3, M.DESCR, M.TM_NAMES FROM BC_UDV3_TM_MAIN M INNER JOIN BC_UDV3_ELEM_KEY EK ON (M.DBKEY=EK.DBKEY) INNER JOIN ( SELECT DISTINCT M2.DBKEY FROM BC_UDV3_TM_MAIN M2 INNER JOIN BC_UDV3_ELEM_KEY EK ON (M2.DBKEY=EK.DBKEY) INNER JOIN BC_UDV3_ELEM_CB EC1 ON (M2.DBKEY=EC1.PARENT_DBKEY) INNER JOIN BC_UDV3_ELEM_IB EI1 ON (M2.DBKEY=EI1.PARENT_DBKEY) WHERE ( ( /* catbag */ (/* group for OrLikeKeys*/ (EC1.KR_DI_LVALUE = :1 AND EC1.KR_TM_DBKEY=:2 ) )/* group for OrLikeKeys*/ ) /* end catbag */ AND ( ( (EI1.KR_DI_LVALUE = :3 AND (EI1.KR_TM_DBKEY=:4 )) ) ) AND (M2.HIDDEN='0')) ) M_SUB ON (M.DBKEY=M_SUB.DBKEY) ORDER BY LNAME1 ASC , OP_MODIFIED ASC
Workaround:
-> Export/Import of service registry in PID system.
-> In PIQ we are not able to do because SR tables are so high so we can't perform this action.
-> we have tried re-initialise the SR in PID system. Table size have been reduced but the services are not registered in SR.
-> We are analysing how to register the services in SR
RootCause: We need to reduce the number of executions of the query. i.e - Need to reduce the tables involved in the Service Registry.
Resolution: This is now identified as a continuous improvement and will be tracked under SR 220261 for QA1 re-initialization.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Category: CEO Online Centre Portal - non SAP
Subject: CEO: Candidates given wrong ID and secret number
ProblemDescription:
We have investigated the issue but unfortunately could not find the actual root cause.
 
From the logs we found that due to some reason, there was a mix up of candidates of centres CH008 and CH017.
 
For example, both centres have entries for the session CB BEC H June B (AM1) 2019. Centre CH008 has 49 candidates (9701 - 9824) and centre CH017 has 16 candidates (9701 - 9716). On 02 July, when centre CH008 downloaded the report, for some reason the candidates 9701 – 9716 were assigned the ID number and PIN of centre CH017’s candidates. But later, the report had the correct UCIs. This can be confirmed from the logs of Candidate Results Service on 02 July:
 
2019-07-02 08:47:13,681 [20] INFO  UCLES.ESOL.CandidateResults.Services.ResultsService Session id: 10001954; Qualification id: 5334; Centre id: CH017; Candidate Numbers: 9701|9702|9703|9704|9705|9706|9707|9708|9709|9710|9711|9712|9713|9714|9715|9716|9717|9718|9719|9720|9721|9722|9723|9724|9725|9801|9802|9803|9804|9805|9806|9807|9808|9809|9810|9811|9812|9813|9814|9815|9816|9817|9818|9819|9820|9821|9822|9823|9824|
2019-07-02 08:55:49,672 [33] INFO  UCLES.ESOL.CandidateResults.Services.ResultsService Session id: 10001954; Qualification id: 5334; Centre id: CH017; Candidate Numbers: 9701|9702|9703|9704|9705|9706|9707|9708|9709|9710|9711|9712|9713|9714|9715|9716|9717|9718|9719|9720|9721|9722|9723|9724|9725|9801|9802|9803|9804|9805|9806|9807|9808|9809|9810|9811|9812|9813|9814|9815|9816|9817|9818|9819|9820|9821|9822|9823|9824|
2019-07-02 09:49:43,579 [21] INFO  UCLES.ESOL.CandidateResults.Services.ResultsService Session id: 10001954; Qualification id: 5334; Centre id: CH008; Candidate Numbers: 9701|9702|9703|9704|9705|9706|9707|9708|9709|9710|9711|9712|9713|9714|9715|9716|9717|9718|9719|9720|9721|9722|9723|9724|9725|9801|9802|9803|9804|9805|9806|9807|9808|9809|9810|9811|9812|9813|9814|9815|9816|9817|9818|9819|9820|9821|9822|9823|9824|
2019-07-02 10:04:21,353 [29] INFO  UCLES.ESOL.CandidateResults.Services.ResultsService Session id: 10001954; Qualification id: 5334; Centre id: CH017; Candidate Numbers: 9701|9702|9703|9704|9705|9706|9707|9708|9709|9710|9711|9712|9713|9714|9715|9716|
 
As you can see,
·         when centre CH017 downloaded the report at 08:47, the candidates passed in the request are from 9701 to 9824 i.e. these candidates actually belong to centre CH008 for the same session and qualification.
·         Same thing happened again at 08:55.
·         At 09:49, centre CH008 downloaded the report and got the correct candidates and UCIs.
·         When centre CH017 again downloaded the report at 10:04, this time candidates sent in the request are from 9701 to 9716 which indicates that the correct candidates were sent in the request.
 
Now since we cannot replicate the issue in our local environment (as we are getting correct result now), so it is extremely difficult to find what exactly happened which resulted in the mix up. We would suggest to treat this issue as intermittent and let us know immediately in case it occurs again in future.
RootCause:
SR #212579 raised for Root Cause Analysis.

Root cause could not be found as could not be replicated.
Resolution: Suggested code changes could be made. To close PR and add to backlog with reference CEP-527, for onward prioritisation in the stack.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: scandmsp TEMP tablespace keeps running short on space.
ProblemDescription: The TEMP tablespace is used by Oracle for managing any large sorts that cannot fit into memory.  The PR has been raised as we have been receiving this alert for a few weeks now. Root cause to be investigated.
RootCause: A shortage of TEMP space. This could have been related to an inefficient query but after adding some space and having no reoccurrence in 3 weeks it looks to be a simple temp space shortage.
Resolution:
The database is 2.5Tb big, 150Gb allocated to TEMP space was perhaps insufficient for such a big database.
~ 90gb was added on the 22/7 and there has been no reoccurrence since.

OLD :

SQL> select sum(bytes)/1024/1024/1024 GB from dba_temp_files;

        GB
----------
156.061523

NEW :

SQL> select sum(bytes)/1024/1024/1024 GB from dba_temp_files;

        GB
----------
241.999023

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CAE Metrica - Adaptive Algorithm Simulation performance impact
ProblemDescription:
The adaptive algorithm simulation run on the production CAE metrica_admin database is causing DTU spikes. George Winchester has requested that this be raised as PR to be added to the Metrica Team queue.

The top CPU consuming query at the time this was last noticed was:

SELECT TOP 1000 * FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT I.ITM_ID, I.ITM_CURRENT_VERSION, I.ITM_INTERACTION_COUNT, I.ITM_USAGE_COUNT, I.ITM_LINKED_ITEMS, I.CTY_ID, V.ITV_DIFFICULTY, V.ITV_IS_CALIBRATED, A.IAT_VALUE, A1.IAT_VALUE AS IAT_VALUE1, IC.ITC_COUNT AS ITEM_COUNT_VALUE, 0.0 AS WEIGHTING, NEWID() AS RANDOMIZATIONVALUE, 0.0 AS PREF_WEIGHTING FROM ITEMS I INNER JOIN ITEM_VERSIONS V ON I.ITM_ID = V.ITM_ID AND I.ITM_CURRENT_VERSION = V.ITV_VERSION LEFT OUTER JOIN ITEM_ATTRIBUTES A ON I.ITM_ID = A.ITM_ID AND A.ATT_ID = @ATT_WEIGHTING_ID LEFT OUTER JOIN ITEM_ATTRIBUTES A1 ON I.ITM_ID = A1.ITM_ID AND A1.ATT_ID = @ATT_WEIGHTING_ID1 LEFT OUTER JOIN ITEM_USAGE_COUNTS IC ON I.ITM_ID = IC.ITM_ID AND IC.ITC_KEY = @COUNT_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE INNER JOIN ITEM_ATTRIBUTES TIA1 ON I.ITM_ID = TIA1.ITM_ID AND I.ITM_CURRENT_VERSION = TIA1.ITV_VERSION AND TIA1.ATT_ID = @TIAATT_ID1 AND ( TIA1.IAT_VALUE LIKE @TIAT_VALUE1_1 ) INNER JOIN ITEM_ATTRIBUTES IA1 ON I.ITM_ID = IA1.ITM_ID AND I.ITM_CURRENT_VERSION = IA1.ITV_VERSION AND IA1.ATT_ID = @IAATT_ID1 AND ( IA1.IAT_VALUE LIKE @IAT_VALUE1_1 OR IA1.IAT_VALUE LIKE @IAT_VALUE1_2 ) INNER JOIN ITEM_ATTRIBUTES IA3 ON I.ITM_ID = IA3.ITM_ID AND I.ITM_CURRENT_VERSION = IA3.ITV_VERSION AND IA3.ATT_ID = @IAATT_ID3 AND ( IA3.IAT_VALUE LIKE @IAT_VALUE3_1 ) WHERE V.ITV_DIFFICULTY >= @MIN_DIFFICULTY AND V.ITV_DIFFICULTY <= @MAX_DIFFICULTY AND V.ITV_IS_CALIBRATED = 1 ) AS A ORDER BY NEWID()

It executed 100683 times between 08:50 and 10:10 on 9th July 2019 and caused the DTU to max out for the duration. This was all CPU usage. 

The strange thing is that appears to be using the same parameters each time it executes. These are ad-hoc queries, but it’s only ever using one execution plan. As FORCED PARAMETERIZATION isn’t enabled, we’d expect to see a lot of plans generated if the parameters were different.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: The ESM supervision payment report has many duplicated lines of data which needs to be investigated.
ProblemDescription:
ESM supervision payment report (id: 50371) for OCR has many duplicate lines of data.

Manual workaround is applied, but this needs further investigation to find the root cause, to avoid future occurrence as to why there are duplicate report rows for this report id.
Workaround: Manually delete duplicate rows from required report and send it to business.
RootCause:
Steps to replicate the issue in ESM SUP environment are as follows -
ESM SUP database: SSJNTSQ008\SQL01
This issue happens only once for Report Id 50371, under incident 691921.
So we have replayed the same Report Id in ESM SUP environment by changing the ReportStateId to 10 (i.e. Pending) in Payment.ReportRow table and by making required modification in related tables like : Payment.MarkerActivityPending, Payment.ReportRowActivity etc. under MarkerPaymentsV2 database.
 And by running two windows services hosted in support server ssjntis001 - 
i) ESM WCF Services Host
ii) ESM Marker Payments Processor
But the duplicate rows were not same all the time.
Every time we found different rows having itemwise marker and payment information in duplicate. So it is very difficult to find out the exact data issue.
As this is an intermittent issue and happens only once, so it will be better to keep an eye for further monitoring.
Resolution:
Workaround is in place to manually delete duplicate rows from required payment report (Here, Report ID : 50371) and sent it to customer.  

Further investigation was underway in Jira entry ESM-119 with RCA SR# 213963. This is an issue that has occurred once for a particular Report ID which was manually resolved.

The issue is not replicable in support environment and appears to be a one off .  This information was taken to the dev group who were happy to close the PR and should this issue re-occur raise a new record.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Centre cannot log into Secure Exchange
ProblemDescription:
Hi,

Centre 26233 is having trouble logging into the Secure Exchange.

The centre's password was reset and tested within Cambridge International and logging in was possible, however when the centre tries to log in they get the following error message. The exams officer has been able to log in to the system via a 4G network on her phone which suggests there is a problem with the school's network which is preventing log in.

[cid:image001.png@01D4CD18.9718C880]

Details are on zendesk ticket #998800 which I have attached as a PDF.

Thanks,
Katherine

Katherine Mcleod
ASP & Marking Coordinator

Cambridge Assessment International Education
The Triangle Building, Shaftesbury Road, Cambridge, CB2 8EA
Telephone: +44 (0) 1223 553560
Email: katherine.mcleod@cambridgeinternational.org

www.cambridgeinternational.org

Cambridge Assessment International Education prepares school students for life, helping them develop an informed curiosity and a lasting passion for learning. We are part of the University of Cambridge.
Workaround: None
RootCause:
Issue is that both the external users internal & external ip addresses are being passed through in the http header, MOVEit Transfer only expects one ip address, so view it as an invalid connection.

An iRule needs added to remove the internal ip address from the http header.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: [IELTS-11105] More than 2 QPVIDs assigned per CB IELTS test sitting.
ProblemDescription:
When trying to create two CB sessions through ORS with same allocation group, test date, sitting and both module (AC & GT) for different location at the same time(concurrently), 16 versions are being created in the back end for both Reading and Writing instead of 8 versions in total.
The same is happening for the listening version where ideally there should be four versions present in the backend, but six versions are being created.
 
The ORS will request IWAS test sessions to be created via a web-service.
RCA and Replication Steps:
1.       Request two sessions creation (JSON format) from ORS with the same allocation group, test date, sitting, and both module (AC & GT) for a different location concurrently.
2.       Sixteen versions will be created in the back end instead of eight versions in total for Reading and Writing.
3.       Six versions are being created in the back end instead of four versions in total for Listening.
4.       There is an existing validation to check if the same version is available already for any specific request, but if the requests are multiple concurrent for the same version that validation does not work, it creates versions for each requests.
 
Only 2 QPVIDs should be assigned per unique combination of the fields, as mentioned in the description.
 
Note :The  RCA has been done for both AC & GT combined sessions and not for AC  sessions and GT sessions separately.
Workaround:
1) Delete redundant QPVIDs from table DEFAULT_VERSIONS before they get allocated to candidates.
2) Delete redundant QPVIDs from table LISTENING_VERSION before they get allocated to candidates
RootCause:
RCA and Replication Steps:
1. Request two sessions creation (JSON format) from ORS with the same allocation group, test date, sitting, and both module (AC & GT) for a different location concurrently.
2. Sixteen versions will be created in the back end instead of eight versions in total for Reading and Writing.
3. Six versions are being created in the back end instead of four versions in total for Listening.
4. There is an existing validation to check if the same version is available already for any specific request, but if the requests are multiple concurrent for the same version that validation does not work, it creates versions for each requests. 

Only 2 QPVIDs should be assigned per unique combination of the fields, as mentioned in the description.

Note :The  RCA has been done for both AC & GT combined sessions and not for AC  sessions and GT sessions separately.
Resolution:
Confirmed as a defect by ELS investigation under IELTS-11105.
To be added to an ELS release.

Implemented as part of IWAS 6.1.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS Error within Products - Timetable - Date Marks Due
ProblemDescription:
User is able to enter the first date (Date marks are due for component), however the second date (Second date marks are due for component) throws error.

1. No error appears on entering the first date

Please see attachment .1.

2. Error on entering the second date

Please see attachment .2.
Workaround: By clicking 'Find' and then locating the syllabus again and entering the date in the second field.
RootCause:
When adding the dates from EPS screen, after entering the first date, the form (FNSPS005) calls the stored procedure TIMTABLE_MAINT.SET_DATE_MARKS_DUE, this internally calls stored procedure CREATE_TIMETABLE_COMPONENT which inserts data into table TIMETABLE_COMPONENTS. When inserting the second date, this process is repeated and this throws a unique constraint error on table TIMETABLE_COMPONENTS.

This may require a change in background code of form FNSPS005.
Resolution: Jira backlog item MEPS-289 created.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SAP ERP and BWP paging issue
ProblemDescription:
ERP and BW servers are facing paging issue. Due to this work process are getting in private mode.

All BW process chain are failing due to this
RootCause: When a centre clicks on the results tab within CECP and the candidates do not have any results available yet, the application tries to fetch ALL candidate results for ALL centres for ALL sessions. This causes problems to the BW system, i.e. process chain failures, etc.
Resolution: Enhanced the program so that if the centre clicks the results tab within CECP and the candidates do not have any results available yet, the application will not do anythin, i.e. it will not try to fetch any results data from BW.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Candidates.Unique_Identifier sequence issue.
ProblemDescription:
Entries fail to load on EPS. Note this affects all 3 BUs

This is because Candidates.Unique_Identifier allows 14 char. If the sequence exceeds a particular value (more than 7 digits), the entry load process fails because the unique id ultimately exceeds 14 char (UCLES-A, UCLES-B forms the first 7 char).

At present the first 7 chars were set to UCLES-A which has now been changed to UCLES-B and the sequence reset to 2. This will give us approx. 2-3 years of breather. But we need to device a solution that should auto take care of all alphabets (A-Z and may be AA-ZZ.. AAA-ZZZ.. etc)
Workaround: as done on I695992
RootCause: When the upper number is reached it fails to wrap around to the next character to continue with the sequence number.
Resolution:
Resolved for OCR under RFC 36360. 
Still to be resolved for CI.
Jira backlog item MEPS-299 raised for CI.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: J19 ADIP candiadte not using 9239
ProblemDescription:
Please refer to incident for the sample candidate where the issue occurred.
background:
During ADIP aggregation, EPS checks if the candidate has passed in Group 0. If so, EPS proceeds with preparing the combination sets, assuming all the sets will include group 0 syllabus. This assumption now fails. EPS is preparing sets with no group 0 syllabus. This set is then picked up as the final set or the best set. This is the issue
There should be a check to discard all the groups who don't have syllabus from mandatory group 0. This check however should be then at the end just before identifying the best group

Also, when you ignore any such set, ensure that all the other possible combinations are in place else we will be missing best set
Workaround: User can manually override the results
RootCause: RCA attached

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: June 2019 Certificate issue
ProblemDescription:
Can you please investigate why the national ID has not pulled through from EPS MPRD entries onto the Certificate for the below Pakistan candidate. The National ID is in the correct format and should have printed on CRT 190 in the Citizenship Number field in the bottom right hand corner of the certificate.

To get here go to:

* EPS
* Entries

[cid:image003.jpg@01D54E20.14CEE100]


Example of how it should have looked on the certificate below:
[cid:image004.png@01D54E1F.EC826960]

PK281/0001 Citizenship Number (National ID field on EPS) is entered in the same format as candidate P1000/0001 in the Entries screen and has correctly printed on the CRT190 certificate in the bottom right hand corner, as expected.

I believe the logic in EPS for Pakistan centres is below:

If we receive a 13 character number containing no dashes, EPS assumes that it is a citizenship number and converts it to the standard format. Example xxxxxxxxxxxxx converts to xxxxx-xxxxxxx-x on statements of entry and certificates.

Please can you urgently investigate the following:


* why this has not printed?
* who else is effected (which candidate)?
* what action will need to be taken to fix this issue?

CRT190 is a general certificate format, used for centres throughout the world, but Pakistan centres ONLY have the addition of a Citizenship Number (PKxxx, P1xxx, P2xxx, P3xxx, P4xxx, P5xxx and P6xxx are all Pakistan).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ADIP points incorrectly appearing
ProblemDescription:
Please can we urgently look into why points are appearing for ADIP candidate UCLES-A4223608 - 9703 U13 as candidates should not recieve points for a U13.

Issue is that candidates who have received an outcome/point score against a contributing child syllabus, when have their results updated so that the point score is now NULL, EPS is unable to do so.
This is due to an update clause in cand_ass_opt_measures_maint.calculate_outcome (called from group_award_cand_aggregation.calculate_outcome). This update clause is as follows:

UPDATE candidate_ass_opt_measures caom

SET caom.outcome =

( SELECT caps.point_value

FROM child_assessment_point_scores caps

WHERE caps.qgs_sid = caom.qgs_sid

AND caps.qgr_seq_no = nvl( caom.qgr_seq_no_manual,

caom.qgr_seq_no_derived )

AND caps.ass_code = p_ass_code_parent

AND caps.asv_ver_no = p_asv_ver_no_parent )

WHERE ( caom.ass_code,

caom.asv_ver_no,

caom.ses_sid,

caom.can_unique_identifier ) IN

( SELECT caps.ass_code_child,

caps.asv_ver_no_child,

caps.ses_sid,

caps.can_unique_identifier

FROM candidate_assessment_parts caps

WHERE caps.ass_code_parent = p_ass_code_parent

AND caps.asv_ver_no_parent = p_asv_ver_no_parent

AND caps.ses_sid_aggregating = p_ses_sid_parent

AND caps.can_unique_identifier = p_can_unique_id )

-- MISP1063.15 Added below != Clause

AND NVL(caom.outcome,9999) !=

( SELECT NVL(caps.point_value, 9999)

FROM child_assessment_point_scores caps

WHERE caps.qgs_sid = caom.qgs_sid

AND caps.qgr_seq_no = nvl( caom.qgr_seq_no_manual,

caom.qgr_seq_no_derived )

AND caps.ass_code = p_ass_code_parent

AND caps.asv_ver_no = p_asv_ver_no_parent ) ;


This needs to change as below to account for a not null to null change:

UPDATE candidate_ass_opt_measures caom
   SET caom.outcome =
     ( SELECT caps.point_value
       FROM   child_assessment_point_scores caps
       WHERE  caps.qgs_sid    = caom.qgs_sid
       AND    caps.qgr_seq_no = nvl( caom.qgr_seq_no_manual,
                                     caom.qgr_seq_no_derived )
       AND    caps.ass_code   = p_ass_code_parent
       AND    caps.asv_ver_no = p_asv_ver_no_parent )
   WHERE ( caom.ass_code,
           caom.asv_ver_no,
           caom.ses_sid,
           caom.can_unique_identifier ) IN
     ( SELECT caps.ass_code_child,
              caps.asv_ver_no_child,
              caps.ses_sid,
              caps.can_unique_identifier
       FROM   candidate_assessment_parts caps
       WHERE  caps.ass_code_parent       = p_ass_code_parent
       AND    caps.asv_ver_no_parent     = p_asv_ver_no_parent
       AND    caps.ses_sid_aggregating   = p_ses_sid_parent
       AND    caps.can_unique_identifier = p_can_unique_id )
       -- MISP1063.15 Added below != Clause
     AND NVL(caom.outcome,9999) !=
     nvl(( SELECT NVL(caps.point_value, 9999)
       FROM   child_assessment_point_scores caps
       WHERE  caps.qgs_sid    = caom.qgs_sid
       AND    caps.qgr_seq_no = nvl( caom.qgr_seq_no_manual,
                                     caom.qgr_seq_no_derived )
       AND    caps.ass_code   = p_ass_code_parent
       AND    caps.asv_ver_no = p_asv_ver_no_parent ), 9999) ;
Workaround: Update cand outcome to NULL using script and re-derive ADIP for the cand
RootCause: RCA attached

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: C4C EPS Contact Deduplication Issue
ProblemDescription:
EPS provides C4C with a daily extract of contact data. At centre level, existing contacts are compared with incoming EPS data based on the job title - where a match is found, the existing contact is updated and if no match exists, a new contact is created.


This isn't working correctly in all cases as C4C has a 40char field length for job title whereas EPS allows 60 characters - C4C truncates the received title to 40 characters and when EPS sends that same contact again, the comparison happens between the truncated 40char value and the received 60char value, so a match is not identified and a new contact is created. Example centre AE001 where 20 duplicate contacts have been created.
Workaround: Merge/delete duplicated contacts as and when identified
RootCause: The deduplication compares values of different maximum lengths.
Resolution: Code change in C4C to truncate incoming EPS value to 40 characters before deduplication checks take place.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Results PDF fails if there are unsupported centre/candidate names
ProblemDescription: The result PDF generation process in CIE CM fails if there are unsupported characters in candidate or centre names. As a result, presence of few unsupported characters cause failure for the entire cohort. As a workaround, all the candidate names are scanned for unsupported characters and corrected prior to result pdf generation to ensure smooth generation of result pdf. The data also is corrected in EPS, as otherwise there is always a chance of incorrect data flowing back to Direct database. The remit of this PR is to investigate the reason why the result generation fails, publish a list of characters that is not supported and suggest possible measures to make the characters supported.
Workaround: Checks candidate names in advance and correct those that are unsupported.
RootCause: The candidate and centre names are looked up from CIE Direct database to generate the Result PDFs. If any non-supported characters (not supported by “cp1252” encoding) are found then that would cause the PDF job to fail.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CIE Direct does not support certain characters
ProblemDescription: CIE Direct final entries do not allow certain characters like quotes (‘) to be inserted. It converts the quotes entered by the end user to its html equivalent automatically. So if a candidate’s name is entered as Pralay’ then it is automatically converted to Pralay& #39; as shown in the screenshot below. This incorrect data flows through to EPS and is also reflected in candidate’s results. Although it doesn’t impact any of the processes like result pdf generation, but it displays the html code to the end user making the name incorrect. This is a defect in CIE Direct final entries, and the remit of this problem record is to identify the reason behind such conversion, list out the set of characters that are automatically converted and then suggest possible measures to fix the issue.
Workaround:
Ad-hoc Service Requests are raised before every results release to check the presence of & #39; in candidate names and as an action of that Service Request candidate names are updated in “candidates_trans” table through backend DB script.

This is already in place.
RootCause:
Escape directive is causing the apostrophe (‘) to get converted to its equivalent ascii code 
& #39; while creating candidates in CIE Direct Final Entries

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: For Further Mathematics syllabus H245 and H645 grading calculation was incorrect
ProblemDescription:
Incorrect Grade is generated for two Further Mathematics syllabus H245 and H645.

This candidate has over entered so the system should have worked out the combination of units that would give them the best grade rather than award the combination that gave the highest total marks.

Example:-
The specific candidate is:
Our candidate is: Centre 43417 Candidate7208
His scores are:
Y540 64 a*
Y541 53 a
Y542 59 a
Y543 54 a*
Y545 59 a*
algorithm seems to have taken his highest two scores (Y542+Y545) for a total of 235 and grade A. This is the grade he was given.
In fact, using Y543+Y545 gives a lower total of 230, but a better grade of A*
Workaround: Manual data manipulation from EPS end.
RootCause: These Further Mathematics syllabus H245 and H645 were not included for the revised gradation process.
Resolution: Code change is required for including these syllabus, so that the grading will be calculated properly.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: J19 Candidate appearing in unconfirmed
ProblemDescription:
Please can you investigate why candidate UCLES-92796690 is appearing in unconfirmed grades when we are not aware of any changes being made to the record.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++
The issue is because there was a record for this candidate in the diverted aggregated param table. This record was inserted from the WRM_TRIG2. This record remained in the table and was submitted only when a results job was triggered (and ended). When the results job ended, it caused the data to aggregate and thus audit (because the results was just released)
Workaround: Report back the records from DAP table to user
RootCause: RCA Attached
Resolution:
Jira backlog- item MEPS-290 created.
We should create a mechanism to submit the data from diverted area for aggregation as soon as we can. However, when re-submitting we should also ensure that the results are not running. Also, we can report the records from DAP area (before and after submitting) to users

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cannot Scan SAP Packets through RF Gun with Move Items menu
ProblemDescription:
SAP sends packets to STS containing few wrong scripts with a different product combination than the rest of the scripts in the packet. This results in the packets to have two different Question Paper Versions (QPV) associated with it. When these packets are scanned through RF Gun with Move Items menu it results in an error and the packets cannot be scanned and processed further.
 
The Root Cause of the issue has been observed that SAP manually prepares data of few scripts prior to pushing it to STS. Error in this manual process results in wrong data to be pushed to STS.
Workaround: The discrepant scripts can be manually fixed in the STS database by changing the associated product and QPV to match that of the rest of the correct scripts in the packet after confirmation from SAP.
Resolution: backlog item STS-210

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: BIZMQ-327 OMR Messages not getting archived in all cases
ProblemDescription: There are some cases where the messages received for OMR processing is not getting archived. So the trace whether a OMR messages was received or not is getting lost.
RootCause:
Whenever there is some database connectivity issue with the BAMPrimaryImport DB, the data received for OMR processing is not getting archived. On further checking the pipeline configuration in the receive port for OMR processing, we have observed that the order of steps executed is incorrect. The order with which the steps gets executed is:
1> track the data in ProcessSummary table in BamprimaryImportDb
2> archive the data received in archive store
So whenever there is some connectivity issue with the BAMPrimaryImport DB, the first step is failing and hence the archiving is not happening.
Resolution:
The order of the steps in the pipeline configuration of the receive port for OMR processing needs to be changed so that:
1> archive the data received in archive store
2> track the data in ProcessSummary table in BamprimaryImportDb

Once the change in the port configuration is made, a round of testing needs to happen for both happy path and failure path.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: FAO Mterica APO Team - Candidate responses not been returned to the marking pool
ProblemDescription:
Hello,

In JIRA https://metrica.atlassian.net/browse/MET-7758 the functionality was introduced to return a candidate response to the examiner marking pool if the examiner the response was assigned to has not submitted a mark and one of the following occur:


1. When an examiner logout occurs (initiated by the examiner), as part of that logout, the system must immediately de-allocate any items that are still allocated to that examiner
2. When an examiner logout is forced by the system (after 20mins of inactivity), allocated items must remain allocated until the system timeout of 3hrs (see next bullet). This will enable an examiner to log in again and recommence marking if so required.
3. The system must also monitor allocation periods, with a timeout of 3hrs for an allocated item - the monitoring script can run every 30 minutes. Any items allocated for more than 3hrs must be de-allocated, regardless of login state.

It states that any item that is de-allocated must be automatically returned to the respective marking pool for reallocation and the returned item must become the next item in the pool that is awaiting marking (first in the queue).

After some testing in Live QA a query has arisen as to whether or not this functionality is working or not.

In the Linguaskill General Speaking DMS it has been observed that items are not returned to the pool when not marked by the examiner they were originally allocated to.

For example yesterday examiner AP_ExaminerQA1 say a part 2 response but didn't mark it. Today when logging in as APExaminerQA2 the examiner sees the message that there are no items to be marked.

If the return to pool functionality was working we believe that the response should be available to APExaminerQA2 for marking.

Please could you investigate and see if this functionality is indeed working or not?

Please note I am out of the office until the 27th August please could you cc Annabelle Pinnington Pinnington.A@cambridgeenglish.org into any replies on this.

Thank you

Best Regards
Becca

Rebecca Patrick
Systems Support Specialist
T: +44 (0) 1223 553039
The Triangle Building, Shaftesbury Road, Cambridge, CB2 8EA

Cambridge Assessment English
Part of the University of Cambridge
www.cambridgeenglish.org
Resolution:
<ExaminerItemDeallocationElapsedTime></ExaminerItemDeallocationElapsedTime>
Value missing in the properties file in QA of MetricaWinService should be populated with the value as in Live.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESM fails to receive IMRBs at Sunday 09:02 BST
ProblemDescription: BizTalk has successfully sent the candidate IMRBs to ESM on 08/09/2019 09:02 BST. But ESM fails to receive the IMRBs. This has now happened thrice i.e. for the past three Sundays, ESM has failed to receive the messages at exactly the same time 09:02 BST.
Workaround: Biztalk reprocessed the IMRBs.
RootCause:
--update 28/11/2019

There was heavy resource pressure at that time on Sunday morning. Quite often the standard full backup, the weekly integrity checks and the extra full backup for the SUP refresh would all overlap and combined with the BAU activity that was running at that time would lead to high I/O and low memory. On SQL Servers which are participating in an availability group, resource pressure can sometimes lead to a lease timeout whereby the cluster service and the SQL Server service have not been able to contact each other for a certain amount of time. This will cause the replica to trasition to the resolving role temporarily and when this happens all connections will be closed.


In the absence of a recurrence of the issue, to provide more specific data., I would say that the issue was down to the memory pressure experienced by these servers every Sunday, when the database integrity checks are performed.
Resolution:
Update 28/11/2019
As mentioned above  the standard full backup, the weekly integrity checks and the extra full backup for the SUP refresh would all overlap and combined with the BAU activity that was running at that time. I have now taken the extra SUP full backup out of the mix by creating a SUP refresh job that relies on the existing full backups. Since then I have seen no recurrence of the issue.



Have changed the Sup refresh process to use existing backups to use exiting files father than take new backups. Have also upped the number of retries on the integrity checks job. Everything is much more stable now.
No incidents have occurred for some time now. Have confirmation from APO that we can close.

As a permanent solution, ESM team needs to check with DBA where the bottleneck is and accordingly fix the issue. This issue has started occurring regularly now.
incidents reported for the same:705469,704406

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: MLA Live Metrica Issue: HTML Test Exports Introduce Missing/Incorrect Characters to Test Content
ProblemDescription:
Greetings,

In the current version of Metrica, we have noticed that the content of items as they appear within Metrica does not consistently match test form exports.
Details are below.

Description of Issue:
The html export from Metrica doesn't apply correct character entities for punctuation. It gives most punctuation the same underlying entity (em dash, en dash, ampersands, apostrophe/possessive, quotation marks, etc.). It also sometimes eliminates the character (at least visually) altogether: https://protect-eu.mimecast.com/s/1aL3CnrQQI6k9kEtJJ448?domain=screencast.com. (from Eric Lagergren, Operations Manager)


Priority level:
P1

Impact on users/work:
Form reviewers must painstakingly attend to minute details on typeset reviews of test forms in order to visually detect errors introduced upon exporting html. All such errors must be reported to the Production team, and corrections must be made manually each time an affected item is used on a test form. This type of error is easily missed, so this may result in undetected errors appearing on published and distributed test forms. Please note that all of our high-stakes tests are given in paper based form, so this affects nearly all of our products.

URL affected: https://protect-eu.mimecast.com/s/pwQQCoQRRfKQ2QnFVIshC?domain=metrica.cambridgemichigan.org

Browser(s) affected: all

Metrica version: CAMLARelease version 19.2.0.12217

Steps to reproduce:


1. Login to https://protect-eu.mimecast.com/s/pwQQCoQRRfKQ2QnFVIshC?domain=metrica.cambridgemichigan.org

2. Navigate to Tests

3. Open a test form

4. Select "View this test as a PDF"

5. Click "Submit"

6. Check the "Export as HTML bundle instead of PDF" box

7. Click "OK"

8. After the export is complete, open the html version of the test form

9. Compare text content with punctuation with items in Metrica (or with pdf export of form)

Expected outcome:
Content text in html export matches content in Metrica exactly (as well as in the pdf export).

Actual outcome:

(a) Some punctuation characters are absent in the html version.

(b) Some punctuation characters are incorrect in the html version.

Examples:

(1) The screen shot below shows part of an item as it appears in the html version (left) and the pdf version (right) of the test export, with affected punctuation highlighted.

(2) The attached html version of a sample MET form (from which the below example is taken) contains many similar errors - as can be seen when the html version is compared with the attached pdf version.

[cid:image002.jpg@01D564CF.D88F1040]


Thanks for looking into this!

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Performance issues of IELTPRD1 on upileor010
ProblemDescription:
Investigating causes.


CPU on upileor010 increased substantially from around 5:30 AM. Opened call with Oracle to find causes of the bringing down of IELTPRD1 on upileor010
RootCause:
Oracle have confirmed (SR 3-20974069101) that the cause of the server restart was a Linux protection mechanism, see below :

"
I've been investigating on information captured by logs and could identify cause of the crash. 
 Behavior is documented in notes below. 

 Cause 
 =============== 
 Issue is similar to the issue described in below note: 
 OOM Killed DBWR, Causing Instance Termination ( Doc ID 1622379.1 ) 

 OOM killer, is a Linux feature that is enabled by default. It is a self protection mechanism employed by the Linux kernel when under severe memory pressure. 

 The general Solution: is to add more RAM / swap to server to avoid this issue. 

 Kindly go through below note that talks about this feature. 
 Linux: Out-of-Memory (OOM) Killer ( Doc ID 452000.1 ) 

 Solutions you can take into consideration 
 =============== 
 1. Increase the amount of physical RAM inside the server. 

 2. Add swap space if that is not in use (not the best solution!). 

 3. Turn off the OOM killer in the sysctl configuration. 

 4. If you want OOM functionality, but don't want it to affect Oracle engine, then engage your sysadmins to configure it accordingly 

 5. If the server is not dedicated to Oracle database, look at moving other services off the machine to other areas. 

 6. Monitor the memory usage in /proc/meminfo, free, and /proc/buddy to make sure that memory is being used effectively. 

 7. Watch to see if there are any memory leaks happening in any of the software currently on the system.
"
Resolution:
If this issue reoccurs (which  has not happened since the last incident), then memory can be increased/changed as per the recommendations from Oracle above.

The reason for the excessive memory usage has been addressed under PR7052.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Scripts stuck as 'Pending' in ATS PDF Status screen of ESM
ProblemDescription:
Over 100 script requests made on ESM this morning (between 8:21am & 9:16am) have been stuck on pending for hours, whereas new script requests made after this period have been successful and then downloaded. Workaround: Asking the filepath xmls from Biztalk and process them manually through SOAP UI.

2. BizTalk team sends us the XML 
3. We call the service http://spjntis011.ucles.internal/UCLES.ESM.Facades/AtsService.svc from SoapUI and pass the XML message to the operation SaveAtsReturnOfScript.
4. The PDF filepath then gets updated in the table ATS.Files table and the script is then ready to be downloaded from ESM Portal.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: SCALE Production - Interface Up Shipments
ProblemDescription:
Good Afternoon BTS Service Desk

We have noted that the time taken for SCALE production to create the xml interface files for confirmation of shipping to SAP to taking an excessive time to complete (scheduled job for this task shown below).

The volume of SAP shipments being processed has increased considerably this session and we are finding that once a SCALE shipping load has been confirmed the scheduled job is taking a number of hours to complete.

This is now having an operational impact as SAP needs to reflect the despatch status of shipments, which if SCALE takes a number of hours to produce these files will be out of sync.

An example yesterday (12 June) various shipping loads were confirmed around 18.30 (containing 1000+ shipments) , the xml files have been produced at 14.18 on the 13th June, it has taken almost 20 hours.

I appreciate these are large volumes but that is what the warehouse is now processing and volumes will only rise in the future.

One additional item to mention is that Manhattan previously delivered a fix for this interface to address the problem of it timing out and not completing the task. This was a serious issue as it could not be retriggered and shipments in SAP had to be updated manually. Since the fix was applied this interface has been 100% reliable and not missed a beat, producing all the xml files successfully.

Although we want this to run faster the execution must maintain the 100% reliability.

Please can we forward this to Manhattan for investigation.

Thanks

Iain

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Unable to delete any candidate from target session while transferred from another session.
ProblemDescription:
Logging to the Centre admin, as a Centre user ‘CENTREUSERL1/ L2’ following below steps, getting Technical exception while trying to delete any candidate from target session.
 
Steps:
1.       1.   Logging to Centre admin as a CENTREUSERL1/ L2’ >>
2.       2.  Go to ‘Candidate Entry’ under ‘Candidate Management’ tab to enrol a candidate for any specific session>>
3.       3.  Then go to ‘Candidate Transfer’ under ‘Candidate Management’ tab>>
4.       4.  Now select the source session against which candidate has enrolled with respective module and select the target session.
5.       5.  You should find the enrol candidate under source session. Then transfer to target session by clicking on right arrow button and save the changes.
6.       6.  The application will return an error message ‘An error occurred during candidate transfer’.
7.       7.  It seems to the user that the candidate might be not to transfer the target session. But from backend we can see that candidate transfer to target session.
8.       8.  Now go to ‘Candidate Search/ Update’ under ‘Candidate Management’ tab, and you can see candidate appear to target session instead of source session.
9.      9.   Now click on Delete button to delete the candidate.
10110. The application will through Technical exception against these changes.
RootCause:
As per the expected behavior, once candidate has been transferred to another session CANDIDATE_SESSION_SLOT table should update candidate's SESSION_MODULE_ID reflecting the new session's assigned SESSION_MODULE_ID from SESSION_USAGE table. This will only happen if the attendance registration number was filled up during the candidate transfer to another session. 

On this reported issue, SESSION_MODULE_ID of the old session is still the one registered on the candidate's record on CANDIDATE_SESSION_SLOT even though it was transferred to another session despite of the error message prompted during the transfer (An error occurred during candidate transfer).

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Rates Manager transfer to EPS not working
ProblemDescription:
In Rates Manager application in production, Static table refresh  should takes approximately 1 hour to complete but since 11/10/2019 it is taking more than 12 hours which lead to Rate Manager not able to push recently updated rates into the EPS.

APO have investigated this and found that there is a service RatesManagerExportService which refresh the Static table every day. Earlier when it was running normally took approximately 40-60 minutes to complete the refresh but since 11/10/2019 it was abruptly taking more than 12 hours. Because of this lag in refreshing the static table, OWB job fails to pick up the data and push into EPS.

We had raised a PR 6981 in which as a resolution  a job had scheduled for  FEAR database statistics refresh every weekend (Sunday 6AM).

DBA need to do complete analysis for Rate Manager Database server(UTLPRD01A\SQL01) that why Static table refresh taking this much of time as we have already a stat refresh  scheduled weekly.
RootCause: APO have investigated this and found that there is a service RatesManagerExportService which refresh the Static table every day. Earlier when it was running normally, tooks approximately 40-60 minutes to complete the refresh but since 11/10/2019 it was abruptly taking more than 12 hours. Because of this lag in refreshing the static table, OWB job fails to pick up the data and push into EPS

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ESOLBMUReporting - IELTS Provisional Entry Numbers Issue
ProblemDescription:
Incident Details:
Hi BTS,

I have looked at the Provisional Entry Numbers in the ESOLBMUReporting database for IELTS products.

These are flagged with a CSVId as IELTS in the Entries table, and EntryType of P.

The numbers look fine up to Jan 2016, but then stop after that.

The actual entries on the other hand (EntryType = 'A') continue to the present day.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Spare OMR PDF-Transform fails to create directory (Windows restricted keyword) for Packcode
ProblemDescription:
Issue:

- Transform creates spare PDF file for OMR as an electronic copy and place that within '\\spprtfs003\d$\TFS\SAPcengOMR\PRD\P\Spares\' within Centre name.


In case the SAP data file consists of windows restricted keyword as packing code (example shown below), transform unable to create a folder with similar name. This results controlled exception generated by Transform and error being triggered on COSMOS.

Following are few such restricted keywords used for pack codes:
1) CON
2) PRN
3) AUX
4) NUL
Workaround:
As resolution:
Append '_CA' to the packing code to enable this to be recognized as a valid folder name.
RootCause: Windows restricts some special word, not to use for creating directory
Resolution:
Append '_CA' to the packing code to enable this to be recognized as a valid folder name.
This is being handled through Jira ticket PRS-1764.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Certificates reprinting in error for RoR candidates
ProblemDescription:
Centre reported that they have received duplicate certificates. The centre requested early certificates so they were printed at the beginning of September. The centre then requested a review of results after results were issued and the certificates have printed again, regardless of whether the grades changed or not.

An example of this is candidate 1201 who had a RoR for J560 but didn't have a grade change but has received a second certificate.
Workaround: Code change required
RootCause:
EXISTING BEHAVIOR

Scenario 1: 
1. The candidate is not picked up by the main run because it has an 'Open' RoR
2. Then the RoR closes
3. Since the candidate was never printed, it gets picked up by the mop-up job.

Scenario 2: New RoR for same candidate
1. Certificate generated for the candidate through main run
2. RoR opened
3. Results changed because of RoR
4. RoR is closed
5. Certificate gets reprinted (with the result change)

Scenario 3 (INCORRECT): New RoR for candidate
1. Certificate generated for the candidate through main run
2. RoR opened
3. Results not changed
4. RoR is closed
5. Certificate gets reprinted

IDEAL BEHAVIOR

Scenario 1: 
1. The candidate is not picked up by the main run because it has an 'Open' RoR
2. Then the RoR closes
3. Since the candidate was never printed, it gets picked up by the mop-up job.

Scenario 2: New RoR for same candidate
1. Certificate generated for the candidate through main run
2. RoR opened
3. Results changed because of RoR
4. RoR is closed
5. Certificate gets reprinted (with the result change)

Scenario 3: New RoR for same candidate
1. Certificate generated for the candidate through main run
2. RoR opened
3. Results not changed
4. RoR is closed
5. No certificate gets printed

This functionality perhaps works correctly for CIE. The code there can be used as reference.
Resolution: Jira Backlog item OEPS-356 created.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: COSMOS - Unable to release balancer Server
ProblemDescription:
COSMOS reports error, while releasing the load balancer (SLB),  after completing the transform composition. This results block of the specific load balancer, and any jobs cant be used use the load balancer group.


Canon SR '1-86994167789' is requested to investigate this further.
Workaround:
1) Check if any job running on Transform (Check filter: Using Transform)
2) If NOT: 
2.1. Stop the input channel, that stops any new jobs to ingest (Both application servers)
2.2. If any jobs is in 'ready to run' , hold them back changing status to 'Hold'
2.3. Stop the Job processors (Both application server)
2.3. Go to Step (3)
3) Go to form perspective -> Load balancer
3.1. Stop the Load balancer on both application server
3.2. Restart the load balancer on both application server.
RootCause:
RCA to be done by Canon.
SR is requested from Canon and reference number is yet to be received:
Resolution: Workflow modification is required for exceptional scenarios for forcefully releasing balanced server item as suggested by Canon.For this additional effort is required and will be handled through JIRA backlog item PRS-802.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: New Versions of Scholarships in SAP not pushing through to EPS
ProblemDescription:
Setting up new version of Sholarships in SAP are not correctly pushing through to EPS. The push states that it is successful yet the data is not populating correctly in EPS Load Products screen.

The consequence of this is that the product has to be pushed numerous times to get it to successfully push through to EPS.
Workaround: Repush as an Update
RootCause:
Seems like the modifications to procedure ADD_ASV and ADD_OPT to include scholarship data as part of I421136 must be incomplete which leads to this issue.

Data which is not getting populated comes from:
assessment_vers.single_sex_entry_ind,
assessment_vers.nominated_cands_ind,
assessment_vers.no_of_scholarship_cands 
from ASSESSMENT_VERS table in EPS.

SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.LOAD_PRD_ASV_DATA is responsible for loading ASSESSMENT_VERS staging data to EPS.

The SP then internally calls SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.ADD_ASV procedure to insert new data.

SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.ADD_ASV then checks if the scholarship indicator has been set or not using the function SCHOLARSHIP_QUERY.SCHOLARSHIP_IND. If this function returns no value (i.e. NULL) then SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.ADD_ASV creates an assessment version by calling ASS_MAINT.CREATE_ASSESSMENT_VERSION. This populates the required columns in ASSESSMENT_VERS table and the push from SAP is successful.

But, when SCHOLARSHIP_QUERY.SCHOLARSHIP_IND returns a value (for a scholarship assessment), SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.ADD_ASV calls SCHOLARSHIP_MAINT.ADD_ASSESSMENT_VERSION. This is where it fails to populate the required columns in ASSESSMENT_VERS and the push from SAP fails.

The issue can be rectified by re-pushing the data in the form of an Update which is initiated by SAP_PRD_INTERFACE.AMEND_ASV which then calls ASS_MAINT.AMEND_ASSESSMENT_VERSION that runs an update statement and populates the required columns with correct values.
Resolution: please note 7519 is duplicate of PR 3644

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: MLA Metrica Issue: Fields that should be auto-populated do not display for most items in bank
ProblemDescription:
This is raised for updating the Answer key of the items showing null values in 'Answer Key' field.
 
The complete issue is described below:

Some fields that are typically automatically detected/populated, such as Answer Key and Interaction Count, appear blank for many items, both in the Items list view and in the Items CSV export or Item Status report. This is true for the vast majority of items that were part of the 2017 mass migration of data from our previous item banking platform; this affects over 15,000 items.

Impact on users/work:

Some of these auto-populated fields are critical considerations when constructing test forms, and not being able to view/access this information in list view or exports adds hours of work for staff for each test form compiled.
Additionally, we intend to incorporate automatized test form compilation into our BAU processes, which will require that this information is accessible as metadata for all current items.

URL affected: https://protect-eu.mimecast.com/s/r1_tCMQDDf6EoM6hwh68z?domain=metrica.cambridgemichigan.org

Browser(s) affected: all

Metrica version: CAMLARelease version 19.2.0.12217

Steps to reproduce:

1.       Login as Assessment Staff user

2.       Navigate to Items

3.       Clear filter/ensure that Pre-determined filter is set to: Current items and Tests

4.       Make auto-populated columns, such as Answer Key & Interaction Count, visible

5.       Page through Items list view and observe results

Expected outcome:
Auto-populated fields should display for all items to which the fields are relevant. For example, Answer Key should display for all multiple choice items, and Interaction Count should display for all items with multiple interactions.

Actual outcome:
Auto-populated fields such as Answer Key and Interaction Count are blank for many items, including many items for which the fields should display.

Workaround (not at all feasible):
We are aware that these fields can be populated for an item by opening it, clicking Edit, and clicking Save, but it is not feasible to do this manually for more than 15,000 items.
Workaround: These fields can be populated for an item by opening it, clicking Edit, and clicking Save but this has to be done manually by opening each item.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Failed to copy temporary job file to PRISMAsatelite server
ProblemDescription:
A) Background:
COSMOS ingests job and creates a job folder into Prin System Input File Share. COSMOS keeps the datafile into job folder and request to transform to generate PCL file for print job. Transform generates the PCL files and saves this into the job folder.
Hence COSMOS submits this job into PSAT. PSAT copies the PCL files into their own server during the PSAT submission.
 
B) Issue:
PSAT unable to copy the PCL file from COSMOS job folder to the temporary directory in PSAT application server on 24/10/2019 at 19:51:03 and resulted error code ‘err <59>’
Temporary location: D:\Program Files (x86)\OcePRISMAsatellite\tmp
 
C) Impact:
One job failed to submit into PSAT from COSMOS and status is  ‘Processiong Error’
 
Service Request will be raised to Canon with SR number: 1-87034015182
 
The screenshot details are attached.
Workaround:
Log collection:
- Collected Trace files and log from PSAT server
- Collected COSMOS logs (COSMOS.log and wrapper.log) from both application servers

The action was taken:
1) Changed the Status of the impacted job to ‘Ready to run’ to recompose and submit to ‘PSAT’

Post validation:
1) Verified the job submitted successfully into PSAT and appeared in the ‘PSAT’ queue.
RootCause:
CANON response: This is related to network issue reported by Windows:

In this case the error code 59 indicates that the copy of a remote file aborted due to a network failure.
The explanation for the error code can be found at https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/debug/system-error-codes--0-499-
ERROR_UNEXP_NET_ERR
59 (0x3B)
An unexpected network error occurred.
Resolution:
The issue occurred only once (25th Oct 2019) and within last 1 month there is no reported incident being logged. Hence we are closing this PR.

As par the log says and responded by Canon PPP, its is related to network issue (Error code 59), hence no action is required in this ticket.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IWAS allocating same QPVIDs multiple time for the same component and module
ProblemDescription:
IWAS is assigning the same QPVID (version) more than two times for same component and module. This potentially means that the wrong band score could be used to calculate the final score of the candidate for Reading and Listening.
For example:
The candidate has been allocated reading version 59L60RGT (General Training) and has been flagged because the Reading band score in IWAS does not match the band score when calculated using the 59L60 BSCT.
 
“59L60RGT” is actually used for two tests:
 
19_0382_01_360853
19_0382_01_370053
 
The two tests are made up of different tasks, and so the Band Score Conversion Tables differ
Workaround: There is a potential workaround under discussion is to identify the affected candidates and update the scores manually.
RootCause:
Multiple ‘create session’ requests are processed concurrently and the underlying table providing QPVIDs duplicates the QPVID when accessed concurrently.
This issue was thought to be fixed with the implementation of a ‘business lock’ to separate processes but the lock did not prevent the underlying table access issue.
This was not detected in test as it was not realised that a performance-style test to provide concurrent requests is required to recreate the issue.
Resolution:
IELTS 2017 Programme CR036 is expected to change version allocation processing, so a different approach will be implemented.
Should this not progress, a separation of session creation and QPVID generation would be required so that sessions are created in a performant manner and QPVIDs are allocated by a separate asynchronous process.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTS-11460 IWAS ATP Failure - Application halts processing.
ProblemDescription:
ATP Application servers halt processing due to ‘IO Error: Connection reset’ exception and only log lines once every ~15 mins as opposed to standard 15 seconds per line. This means requests don't get picked up by the application servers with the issue. This means the application runs with degraded performance causing delays leading to failure notifications.
The application logs often stall but then recover without any apparent reasons. In this case, the incident has not been logged, but logs are checked to ensure application is running correctly. This is linked to PR#7149
Workaround: We have created a monitoring script which will determine when logs are not writing correctly. If this is noticed, then the affected application server will be restarted.
RootCause:
Investigating the issue, it is found that ATP Application halt processing due to ‘IO Error: Connection reset’ but the retry mechanism continued every 15 mins to process any failure or ON HOLD request. 
Here a few framework level tasks are getting stuck while updating the database, thus causing the primary process to halt.  
As it can be seen that these tasks have started as they have create_time and start_time but have not finished as there are no end_time, thus causing the main job to hang. We also cannot confirm the exact error due to which the task got stuck as there is also no exit_code or exit_message.
There are few data tables in TC_PRD schema, which are entirely used by the spring-boot framework to store metadata related to the framework execution. As time goes the amount of data in these tables are continually increasing, and thus, these jobs sometimes get hanged while trying to access these tables. Hence as time goes size of these tables are growing and so are the frequency of occurrence of this issue.
A scheduled purge job to terminate the old framework metadata would help us to clear the DB tables and thus decrease the chances of such conflict.
Resolution: IELTS-11460 created to progress the data purge process in parallel to the ongoing investigation to identify the true route cause.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Duplicate data from SAP not recognised in STS (resulting in missing data)
ProblemDescription:
Duplicate records has been pushed through IF297 interface between STS and SAP Functional PI.

As they were allidentified as duplicates, STS did not process any of them resulting in roughly 1400 "missing" records between SAP and STS.
Workaround: Error records shared with CTS SAP Functional Team. Relevant dataset removed from STS end to allow SAP to re-push failed data.
RootCause:
RCA: The team agrees that the root cause for the bulk of the issues is duplicate records from SAP to STS.  This may be related to the SAP retry logic combined with connection issues.  But the main point being that this issue is a result of SAP sending STS the same file with the same content and idoc.  For the remainder of the issues, this is covered by the SAP CR9000905, which has been raised as a high priority CR.

Key Actions:

• Service Protection - interim preventive measures :
o A SAP to STS reconciliation process and report will be in place on Monday, Nov 11, 2019.   Although this is an interim measure, it is still a fairly robust solution that will protect our service for now.  Stakeholders, including SAP and STS managers, will be on this report for at least two weeks build confidence in the process.

• Service protection - permanent preventive measures:
o The JAVA support team will automate the reconciliation report.  This will become part of the standard health checks.  Forever (or as long as STS and SAP exist).
o The SAP team will progress CR9000905.
o The JAVA support team will create a PR, recommend it be prioritised, and STS Application management will push to get this prioritised in the next JAVA development sprint.
Resolution:
STS needs to implement better exception handling to handle duplicates.  If the same file and data comes from SAP, do not identify ALL of them as duplicates and do nothing resulting in missing records.  Instead at least process one of them.

JIRA STS-313 created and we will prioritize this for the next sprint.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Scaling Not Applied
ProblemDescription: Scaling hasn't been applied to a centre resulting in the candidate's marks/grades not having been updated in EPS.
Workaround: Candidate re-derive
RootCause:
As mentioned in Incident# 722015, it seems no aggregation was run for these affected centre/candidates after the last scaling factor adjustments were made. This resulted in the candidate's marks/grades not having been updated.

From database perspective, column candidate_component_measures.last_aggregated_datetime holds values less than the values in column scaling_entry_batches.created_datetime indicating no aggregation was run after the scaling factor adjustments were made.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica - When Updated issue in Workflow projects
ProblemDescription:
In projects with a workflow (EliT Speaking) in Live and UAT, editing an item's content no longer updates the When Updated date. This is an issue as it means that, if a task has edits made to it, it cannot be republished via the Publish Items screen. Metrica is no longer recognising that the item has been changed and needs republishing to Live or to QA.

The only way that it can is if the task is pushed through the workflow to create a new version. This is not a valid workaround for colleagues in MLT, as there are limited stages within the workflow before the item is published to Live, and new version should be created only when ready and necessary - not as a workaround.

This issue with When Updated does not happen in projects without workflows, only in projects that have them.

Can this be investigated, please?

If you need more information, please let me know.

Thanks,
Alistair

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica - EliT Writing - SLA checker firing too early
ProblemDescription:
Hello,

This incident relates to the two issues we have encountered with the ElIT WRITING RESULTS table introduced as part of the 19.4 release (MET-8256).

First, the WHEN_RECEIVED field does not seem to work correctly in some cases. See, for instance, the records for TIN ID = 7441772, copied below.  Both Score Groups show the same WHEN_RECEIVED value, but  The results for Score Group a541... came in at least 4 hours after the results for Score Group 1d37d... (there is an "Return code not received within 4 hours from the writing submission action" error message in EliTSubmitText and an associated RULES MATCH, see below). This field should record when precisely the results for each separate Score Group are received.

TIN_ID                  TSG_ID                                                                                 SUBMISSION_ID                                                              WHEN_RECEIVED
7441772                1de7d031-7e91-4034-8e19-7325db1f60dd            6e62db12-f53a-40e9-8497-e08fd1c94acd                Oct 31 2019  2:41AM
7441772                a541e347-5497-4a66-ae61-e090b329020c             1a4bec33-4d7c-403d-8fec-1190cda97205                Oct 31 2019  2:41AM

MATCH_ID          TIN_ID                  TSG_ID                                                                                 RULESSET_ID     RULE_ID                DATE_TRIGGERED                           OUTCOME_ID
617                         7441772                a541e347-5497-4a66-ae61-e090b329020c                                                                             31OCT2019:06:50:50.583               2

Second, the TIN_ID and WHEN_RECEIVED fields in this new table are the wrong datatypes. They are both Character fields when they should be Numeric and Date, respectively, as they are in other tables in the database. This causes issues for our processing of this table.
RootCause:
RCA provided to Metrica team further action under MET-9294

See attached
Resolution: Appropriate prioritisation by Metrica team, backlog reference MET-9294

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CCMS - Support Docs/Forms Performance
ProblemDescription: User can attach supporting documents and forms to workflow templates and running deliverables. Clicking the add forms or add support docs opens up the select a document window but this is taking up to 5 minutes to load. It seems that once the first load is done users can access it quickly again for subsequent uploads but only within the current user session.
RootCause: Optimizer adaptive features parameter was set to true in DB.
Resolution:
Incident fix 726489 work carried was:
1. Increase in JMS memory allocation from 2GB to 8GB
set parameter USER_MEM_ARGS="-Xms8192m -Xmx8192m -Xss256k -XX:+DisableExplicitGC"  in /opt/documentum/Shared/wildfly9.0.1/server/startMethodServer.sh 
2. Disable optimizer adaptive features parameter in database
alter system set optimizer_adaptive_features=FALSE scope=both;

Work will continue to do more enhanced work under CCMS-8916

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Unable to log in to SAS Portal
ProblemDescription:
NOTE: This has happened once in UAT (#722249), and now twice in PRD.  Restarting SAS services has resolved the issue on each occasion.

Several users have reported that they are unable to log into the SAS Portal this morning
http://statistics/SASPortal

Access is required to support live marking and grading activity in Cambridge International.
Workaround: Restarting SAS services.
RootCause: Dgemfire timeout setting missing.
Resolution:
Please do the following:
 
1.  Stop all services running on your SAS Middle Tier server
 
2.  On your SAS Compute Server, stop the SAS Cache Locator process
 
3.  Modify D:<SAS-Config-Dir>\Lev3\Web\gemfire\instances\ins_41415\wrapper.conf on your SAS Compute Server to include the following additional parameters;
java.additional.x=-Dgemfire.conserve-sockets=false
java.additional.x=-Dgemfire.member-timeout=60000
 
*where x is a sequential number, continuing on from the existing JVM parameters.  I have attached an example of wrapper.conf which shows the additional options on lines 63 and 64 for reference.
 
4. Start the SAS Cache Locator process on your SAS Compute Server
 
5. Modify D:<SAS-Config-Dir>\Lev3\Web\gemfire\instances\ins_41415\wrapper.conf on your SAS Middle Tier server to include the same additional parameters as above.  Again ensuring that x is the next sequential number.
 
6. Modify D:<SAS-Config-Dir>\Lev3\Web\gemfire\instances\ins_41415\wrapper.conf on your Middle Tier Server, this time adding only the -Dgemfire.member-timeout=60000 option (the conserve-sockets option should already be in this file).
 
7. a. Finally repeat step 6 for each Web Application Server instance that is configured on your SAS Middle Tier server (SASServer2_1, SASServer12_1 etc.).
    b. set: -Dgemfire.member-timeout=30000
    c. I can see Dgemfire.conserve-sockets=false is already set, please double check this.
 
8. Re-start all services on your SAS Middle Tier server.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Metrica - EliT Writing Automarker - Duplicated submissions
ProblemDescription:
I’ve just received the attached email from EliT (Tim Parish). Since the 19.4 release (30 October 2019), we have evidently attempted to resubmit the same answer multiple times using a different submission IDs. 

I’ve done some initial analysis and it looks like the duplication is coming from Metrica Azure. There is only a single record for each Submission (TIN_ID+Score_Group) in Metrica sql db, but there are indeed multiple records for in Azure. See attached. Yellow is from EliT (email below), Green is Metrica sql (EliT_WRITING_RESULTS table) and blue is Metrica Azure (EliTSubmitText table).
 
I don’t think this reduplication is having any negative impact on the results processing for these tests – please confirm –but obviously we don’t want it to occur.
Could you please investigate further and remedy the issue ASAP?

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: CP10 component styling wrong on ATS live
ProblemDescription:
The CP10 "Meet the Team" component was recently implemented for Admissions Testing and we've put a page live using it at:

https://www.admissionstesting.org/for-institutions/case-studies-and-testimonials/

However, we have found some styling problems, which aren't fixed by republishing the stylesheet style.css and clearing the browser cache.

Problems:
1) If you hover over the "Read more" buttons within the CP10 tiles, the text goes very dark so you can't see it.   The buttons should behave as all the other "Read more" buttons on the site: the background goes slightly less dark, but the text remains white.  See for example the "Contact us" button on the same page.

2) If you view the tiles on mobile (either actual mobile or in the Chrome dev tools device emulator) you will see that the images do not fill the entire width of the tiles (see attached screenshot).  However for Cambridge English (https://www.cambridgeenglish.org/research-and-validation/meet-the-team/) the images do span the full width of the tiles on mobile..  Note that the images are the same size in Admissions Testing and Cambridge English.

Can you investigate these issues please?

Thanks

Graham
RootCause: This feature was implemented under https://btsservice.atlassian.net/browse/WEB-3787. I have a discussion with developer that they have missed this as it was not mentioned in acceptance criteria.
Resolution: Style code need to be fixed under WEB-4198 so that the image still doesn’t pull all the way across on mobile devices  when selecting iPhone 6/7/8 Plus and the image width is less than the resolution.

Only IGCSE and some O Level syllabuses are eligible for this Group Award and syllabus 8682 is part of A & AS Level qualification. Please can you investigate how an A Level syllabus is overarched in the ICE Group Award? Please see below candidate details:

Centre: PE0011
Cand: 66
Series: November 2019



++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Analysis

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

The incorrect child syllabuses are linked and created in CAP table from FNORD115 form. When entries come in, EPS creates correct data in CAP table. However, using the above form, when the Overarching is removed (using Remove Overarching/ Remove Single Assessment button) and then recreated using Overarch Centre or Candidate button, incorrect child syllabuses are linked with ICE in CAP table.

This form and background code needs to be checked and amended
Workaround: Information to user. No action taken by BTS
RootCause: Error on form FNORD115
