Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Teleform Page Linking Issue
ProblemDescription:
1/ Overview:

Context (RCA / Permanent Fix): Two incorrect teleform batches were identified in November with page linking issues (i.e. the wrong pages linked together) and incident 724215 was raised on November 19, 2019, escalated, investigated and root cause was identified as a code bug introduced by EPC (see below).  This was fixed, tested, and the issue permanently fixed in production on November 20, 2019 via emergency RFC 38441.   The associated non-conformant candidates associated with the initial incident were addressed in our production systems by Nov 28, 2019, however an investigation and clean-up exercise to go through ALL the batches that may have been impacted was initiated.

Problem Scope: As the RCA and the permanent fix have already been completed, the scope of this problem record covers the internal investigation and clean-up of the batches between July 19 and Nov 20 2019.

Internal Investigation results:

  • A review of all the batches 450+ since July 19 to Nov 20, 2019 found 15 batches matching the criteria of this edge case.  This is our scope (at the batch level).

  • A review of the teleform incidents found that 711830/724215/727511 were related to the same “page linking” production incident; incident 727511 was escalated to a P2 for visibility.

 

Clean-Up / Non-conformant candidate remediation:  This requires the 15 batches to be resubmitted in PP2/UAT, processed by Corporate Services/SAP and Cambridge English to identify the non-conformant candidates, and then address them.   This requires support from GPAO, Content COE and EPC.   This is in progress. 

 

2/ Root Cause Analysis: the short version is that a bug was introduced by EPC in February 2019, went into PP2 on June 21, 2019 (RFC 35726) and then production July 19, 2019 (RFC 35923).   Specifically: multi-page forms with single image errors resulting in unclassified statuses requiring operator intervention are at risk of triggering this bug, leading to a page linking issues for the affected record as well as subsequent records in that batch.

Long version of RCA from EPC:  “So what I can see is that we created a build in February this year that had the bug…    TeleForm has an entry point at which we can run our code.  This code includes many validations and checks (e.g. checking absent isn’t ticked if there are responses etc.) but also the assignment of the Scan ID that comes from your Postscan system to the images, which TeleForm then used as a page link value to ensure the pages are linked together correctly.  The logic being that all pages from a multi-page form will have the same Scan ID.

Another detail of the way TeleForm works is that there is a EvaluateBegin entry point that runs upon every image going through the system and we can use this to run our checks.  But the problem is, for multi-page forms, we cant run our code on every page as some checks may require all pages to be present to work (like the absent check, which checks all fields across all pages).  So for this there is a PagesLinked entry point which runs once all pages have been evaluated and linked.  But this only applies to multi-page forms and won’t run for single page forms.  So, we have to run our checks for single page forms at EvaluateBegin but only when the page-count is 1 and again at PagesLinked for forms where the page-count is > 1.  We can’t just blindly run it in both places as this would be inefficient and it would error on a page 2 if we referenced a field (like the Absent tick box) which is on page 1.

The breaking change was to move all our checks in to a single module, which then gets called in either one of these conditions.  This saved having more or less the same code all written out twice, in each entry point.  But the problem was, the code that sets the page link was included in this optimisation and where a two-page form came through, but only had one image (because the other was unable to read due to the candidate scribbling over the ID barcode) the page link value was never assigned to the images so it fell through a crack!”

 

3/ Analysis and Clean-Up Info:  A review of batches between July 19 to Nov 20 2019 to identify batches potentially containing non-conformant candidates found the following:

We have a maximum of 15 batches containing bad images that match the basic page linking criteria (i.e. Incidents 711830/724215/727511).  These batches may not all contain non-conformant candidates, but they represent the maximum scope of the issue:

  1. TELEGM0626 CN987:D422/01

  2. TELEGM0640_3 CN355:D422/01

  3. TELEGM0612 CN720:D422/01

  4. TELEGM0637 CN195:D422/01

  5. TELEGM0629 CN195:D422/01

  6. TELEGM0653 CO101:D426/01

  7. TELEGM0438 :D432/01 (IT064:D432/01) and TELEGM0438 :/ (IT064:D432/01)   (note: although this is one scan batch (known as TELEGM0438) by the time it gets to TeleForm it is actually split in to smaller batches for each centre and component.)

  8. TELEGM0496 ES040:D426/01

  9. TELEGM0518_2 CN940:D422/01

  10. TELEGM0521 CN940:D422/01

  11. TELEGM0531 ES439:D431/03

  12. TELEGM0535 CZ101:D431/01

  13. TELEGM0533 14537:D435/03

  14. TELEGM0541 FJ005:D435/01

  15. TELEGM0560 IT326:D426/01

 

 

Other.  Working with EPC, the following batches had issues, but were not related to the page linking issue as these did not contain similar corrupted images as the page linking issue.  The first is likely deployment synchronisation related and has been addressed going forward.  The second is an edge case when a non-absent candidate shows up but never fill in any details leaving completely blank results; as per the original design, documtum interprets it slightly differently to teleform.  A low priority backlog item will be raised for documentum to handle this slightly differently.

Supplementary information from EPC as follows:

  • “TELEGM0439:  This batch was verified on the 22nd of July, the next working day after the last system update, on the 19th July…  We can see that the updated script did not run for this batch.  The verification operator may have noticed this, as certain scripted rules and warnings wouldn’t have appeared as normal, but they completed verification of the batch and it was exported in an invalid state.  As this has not re-occurred since, and as it is so easy to spot within the data if it had, we are confident this was a deployment issue.  In order to prevent this happening again, we have since had permission changes made so that updates can deploy to workstations automatically, rather than requiring admin intervention.  This will help prevent a re-occurrence of something like this happening again.” 

  • “TELEGM0608: There was a single form in this batch which was exported as absent, even thought the form was not actually marked as absent.  This is because if a form is completely blank and not absent (which is an unusual case, only occurring when a candidate is present but for whatever reason doesn’t attempt to answer a single question!) the verification team can press the F5 hot-key to clear the form and save it in one key-press.  The system was designed such that if this option is used, as the audit-trail for this form confirms it was, the absent field is explicitly set to false (i.e. ‘0’) rather than leaving it blank as with a normal non-absent form or ‘1’ for an absent form.  It appears that Documentum interprets the existence of any value at all for absent as an absent, so these forms will have been interpreted by Documentum as absent.  The good news is that this wouldn’t have effected marks at all, as the marks would be zero in either event, it just triggered as an anomaly when the data was being searched for other potential absent errors.”
Workaround: The issue has been permanently fixed already.
RootCause:
2/ Root Cause Analysis: the short version is that a bug was introduced by EPC in February 2019, went into PP2 on June 21, 2019 (RFC 35726) and then production July 19, 2019 (RFC 35923).   Specifically: multi-page forms with single image errors resulting in unclassified statuses requiring operator intervention are at risk of triggering this bug, leading to a page linking issues for the affected record as well as subsequent records in that batch.
Long version of RCA from EPC:  “So what I can see is that we created a build in February this year that had the bug…    TeleForm has an entry point at which we can run our code.  This code includes many validations and checks (e.g. checking absent isn’t ticked if there are responses etc.) but also the assignment of the Scan ID that comes from your Postscan system to the images, which TeleForm then used as a page link value to ensure the pages are linked together correctly.  The logic being that all pages from a multi-page form will have the same Scan ID.
Another detail of the way TeleForm works is that there is a EvaluateBegin entry point that runs upon every image going through the system and we can use this to run our checks.  But the problem is, for multi-page forms, we cant run our code on every page as some checks may require all pages to be present to work (like the absent check, which checks all fields across all pages).  So for this there is a PagesLinked entry point which runs once all pages have been evaluated and linked.  But this only applies to multi-page forms and won’t run for single page forms.  So, we have to run our checks for single page forms at EvaluateBegin but only when the page-count is 1 and again at PagesLinked for forms where the page-count is > 1.  We can’t just blindly run it in both places as this would be inefficient and it would error on a page 2 if we referenced a field (like the Absent tick box) which is on page 1.
The breaking change was to move all our checks in to a single module, which then gets called in either one of these conditions.  This saved having more or less the same code all written out twice, in each entry point.  But the problem was, the code that sets the page link was included in this optimisation and where a two-page form came through, but only had one image (because the other was unable to read due to the candidate scribbling over the ID barcode) the page link value was never assigned to the images so it fell through a crack!”
Resolution: This was fixed, tested, and the issue permanently fixed in production on November 20, 2019 via emergency RFC 38441.   The associated non-conformant candidates associated with the initial incident were addressed in our production systems by Nov 28, 2019, however an investigation and clean-up exercise to go through ALL the batches that may have been impacted was initiated.

Subject: Warnings generated during BWP HANA consistency check
ProblemDescription: For the last 3 weeks only, we have started receiving warnings as per the error message above during the BWP HANA consistency check. According to the documentation, this can be safely ignored as it is most likely a temporary table that is dropped during the consistency check process. The question is why this has started happening suddenly ?
Workaround: No action required.
RootCause: The nature of the error very dependent on what is running during the consistency check process.
Resolution: The consistency check has been running for many months. It only occurred for 3 Sundays and then hasn't occurred again for the last 3 Sundays. this may have just been down to abnormal application activity on the weekends affected.

Subject: EPS Close Posting period error
ProblemDescription:
[cid:image003.png@01D5B4E5.31E57750]We have been notified today that the posting period for 2020 January & March EPS Invoice closes are being incorrectly posted to 2010 financial period from EPS into SAP (see files attached) and below screen print of cadenza report.  Is this a mapping issue?

[cid:image002.png@01D5B4E5.31CC9820]


----------------------------------------------------------


EPS passes 1 digit to represent the academic year which SAP translates to a full year. Hardcoded (in SAP) at the moment so 0 becomes 2010 not 2020. This transfer from EPS needs to be altered to pass the full year to SAP. On the EPS side, the systems needs to be altered to store the full year. All tables, views and code need to be checked and updated.


Original EPS documentation:

https://cambridgeassessment.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/sites/csd/bts/service/coes/ep/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B617C2A7D-1CC6-40D5-A5E1-D670A7F06DE6%7D&file=Release%20ORD17.2%20Design.doc&action=default&mobileredirect=true&cid=3a9a8efe-ed4c-4c66-adef-8d887dd170e3

RootCause: RCA attached

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: 4037/22 IGMD Trigger
ProblemDescription:
An incident was created for the 4037/22 issue . Business have reviewed all possible changes that would trigger an IGMD feed for an individual or a panel and can confirm:

*         No new invitation responses

*         No changes to the awarding schedule

*         No updates to centre exclusions for the series

*         No updates made in ESM Assignments for the component

Need to investigate what has caused the IGMD feeds to trigger panel wide for 4037/22. There is a suggestion from Assessment they have seen this with other panels, but not aware of a wider issue.

No update log at EPS end, and Biztalk got correct response while requesting (Please find in the activity history)
Workaround:
Seems the panel was updated from ESM by clicking on Push to scoris button in Assignment screen. 
After modified by import type run Populate ESMAssignments, and the modified by user name got updated by text 'Update' by SP ESMAssignments.[dbo].[AcknowledgeIGMD]. So a new column 'Updated By' should be added in ESMAssignments.[dbo].[Availabilities] table and all state should be logged 
 in Esmassignments.dbo.AvailabilityHistory table (Including 2).
RootCause: There is only one incident 729879 for this. Updates could not be tracked properly due to lack of some logging information.Column ‘Updated/Modified By’ should be added and all the marker_availability_status_id (Currently not tracking status 2, i.e.SentSuccessfully) changes should be tracked into [dbo].[AvailabilitiesHistory] table of ESM.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: iDRAC firmware update caused unexpected reboot of spavufs001
ProblemDescription: Raise with Dell so they can investigate why the crash occurred.
RootCause: Dell have said the difference in BIOS and iDRAC firmware caused the issues with inventorying hardware, which then caused the host to reboot
Resolution: ensure BIOS is no more than 4 versions/increments lower than the iDRAC firmware being applied - i.e. if BIOS versions is "1" and iDRAC is "6", the BIOS should be updated to a minimum of "2" before the iDRAC update to "6" is applied, however it would be best practice to install the latest BIOS rather than the minimum required as all BIOS updates require a reboot regardless. Firmware should also not be updated in leaps of more than four, so if BIOS version was "1" and needed to be updated to "6", it should be incrementally updated to "5" or lower before being updated to "6".

Subject: Centre 28121 Invoicing Query
ProblemDescription:
Centre 28121
Candidate 15617474 has correctly been invoiced for his unit 2 second attempt. He previous attempts in June 2018 and June 2019 and so has rightly been invoiced for the 3rd test entry:


However the following candidates who have all had previous entries/attempts at the units listed, have not been invoiced for the January 2020 entries:

15664340 - units 1 and 2
15664339 - units 1 and 2
15664334 - units 1 and 2
15664333 - units 1 and 2
15664331 - units 1 and 2
15664330 - units 1 and 2
15664329 - units 1 and 2
15664328 - units 1 and 2
15664324 - units 1 and 2
15617474 - unit 2 only
RootCause: Whenever EDI files and interchange spreadsheet have entries with move up/down scheme code before full entry code then entrytype for the full entries incorrectly gets updated in database. This causes the database function(fnNumberOfAttempts) to malfunction and incorrectly consider every attempt for a scheme/unit as the first attempt. This leads to further malfunction during Invoicing run, where Invoice is not generated for the impacted candidates.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Cambridge Technicals Test Entries
ProblemDescription: Unable to find candidates for making New Cambridge Technicals test unit entries from Interchange, for which FULL entries has been already created from Interchange. Issue occurring in case of Web based entries and Spread sheet entries.
Workaround: We validate the data in between these 3 tables only for candidates and qualifications associated with New Cambridge Technicals and then modifying or inserting the data accordingly to ensure that the candidate details data and Entry data are synchronised to enable centers to make unit entry post full entry is made.
RootCause:
On checking from the back end we found that there are  some candidates for which the entry data and the candidate details data are not in sync in the following tables ( dbo.forms_NQF1Detail, dbo.CandidateSyncMap, dbo.CandidateCentre ). It is the mismatch of data amoing these tables which is subsequently not providing the candidate details for a unit entry.
he functionality of New Cambridge Technicals was slightly different as here for the first time the candidate search was used using the data of these 3 tables to make a unit entry post a full entry. (For other quals there is no feature of unit entry post full entry ) Thus the data mismatch between candidate details caused these Incidents.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: Interchange: A different claim gets updated when Moderator samples a Submitted claim
ProblemDescription: It has been observed that if there are two claims of a centre for same scheme code, candidate and Unit where the first claim is Processed and the second claim is in Submitted status, then when the moderator samples the Submitted claim, the Processed claim gets updated to Sampled and its Sampled Date gets changed to the current date. The Submitted claim remains unaffected.
Workaround:
Manually run the below script in the back-end to fix the issue:
update ClaimPackage set ClaimPackageStateId=6, SampledDate=XXXX where ClaimPackageId=XXXX

Get the Sampled Date from the ClaimPackageAudit table of the affected claim.
RootCause: The issue is happening due to incorrect logic written in SP [dbo].[eClaims_UpdateUnitSampled]. The ClaimPackageId is not passed to the SP. Rather it is set in the SP based on the Centre, Scheme Code, Unit and Candidate Number. Now when there are two claims with same Centre, Scheme Code, Unit and Candidate Number, then both claims are returned and the top most ClaimPackage ID is selected, which happens to be the one which already has been processed.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: EPS extract not pulling default grading thresholds
ProblemDescription:
As mentioned under Incident# 732744

We have discovered that 'default' grading thresholds do not show on the Product Detail Spreadsheet generated in Load Products.
For example, 6890(2) has two components: 01 and 02. No set up had been completed against this product in EPS as grading is not needed.
When I first pulled the extract, neither components 01 or 02 appeared on the Grading(Comp.) tab. The tab was completely blank.
When I went into the grading thresholds screen and unticked and ticked A* for component 01, saved and pulled another extract, component 01 appeared on the Grading(Comp.) tab. Component 02 did not.

This is an area of risk for us because components/options/grading options that have not had their grading thresholds set will be harder to pick up in quality checks as they do not appear at all.
Workaround: N/A
RootCause:
Under Incident# 732744, it was reported that ‘default’ grading thresholds do not show on the Product Detail Spreadsheet which is generated in Load Products.

For example, 6890(2) component 01 and 02 did not show up on the report.
This is because after the product was set up, the necessary background table was not populated. User has to complete certain steps for the background table to populate.
Resolution:
1. Once a product has been set up, one needs to go to ‘Grade Thresholds’ screen
2. When open, click OK and then File > Save – do note, it is not mandatory to check/uncheck a grade
3. When this is complete, relevant data will be populated in background table
4. Running any report/extract will then fetch data for such products

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: IELTPRD1 query consuming great amount of resources on upielor010
ProblemDescription: During IWAS down, Databse team noticed one stement/ script consumed high volume of resources on upielor010 server and after re-boot the effected server, IWAS become available and the issue got resolved.
Workaround: Database team needs to reboot the effected server.
RootCause:
Hi,

As per the SR with Oracle, We are hitting a bug most likely. Please see the following technical details.

• High waits on cursor: mutex X after upgrading the database to 12.1.0.2, 12.2.0.1, 18c or 19c.
• CPU utilization spikes to 100% due to the mutex waits leading to database hang or application outage.
• Huge version count is seen for the SQL statements during the problem period.
• Login or connection storm is observed during the problem.
• Huge sleeps on functions kkscsAddChildNode & kkscsPruneChild as per 'Mutex Sleep Summary' from AWR report.
CHANGES
 Upgrading the database to 12c and higher.
CAUSE
This is due to below internal bug which is fixed in 20.1.
Unpublished Bug 28889389 : HIGH WAITS ON CURSOR: MUTEX X AFTER UPGRADE TO 12.1.0.2
This bug is hit after having observed that multiple unique sessions are waiting for a parent cursor mutex in exclusive mode on the same cursor under the following stack:-
ksfwaitctx()+28<-kgxWait()+1164<-kgxExclusive()+652<-kkscsAddChildNode()
'cursor: mutex X' would have been taken on the parent cursor to find out the matching child cursor for that particular SQL. Some kind of logon storm where all sessions are executing the same cursor at the same time leading to this mutex contention. The child cursor sharing code has been optimized to reduce the Mutex Contention so that exclusive mutex is not acquired for searching the child cursors for match under the same parent.
Resolution:
SOLUTION
To Apply the Patch 28889389 which has the optimized code for cursor mutex while searching the parent cursor for the match.

Textbox16: Created Problem Records for Selected Services, Total 1865
Subject: ASFA Examiner portal not available intermittently.
ProblemDescription:
The Assessment Specialist File Access site is not accessible. The URL is https://asfileaccess.cambridgeinternational.org/

There are examiners trying to access this site for enquiries about results. we have identified that the application was not connect to the database system which was configured in the configuration file and the above mentioned error log was in the application log.

The monitoring alert indicated that the monitor was down and after checking the logs and detailed investigation we could not connect to the database successfully.
Workaround: The Database team did a fail over to resolve this issue.
RootCause: The application config file is pointing to the secondary instance of the database server (SPEMOSQ002\SQL01) in the connection string instead of the availability group (EMOPRDAG01\SQL01). That's why the application was not able to connect to the database server because the secondary instance was down and primary instance was up.
Resolution: The application config file should update with the Availability Group Listener EMOPRDAG01\SQL01.
